1
00:00:11,553 --> 00:00:13,929
[Military drumbeat]

2
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:36,744
[President Eisenhower's farewell speech,
background]

3
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:58,640
NARRATOR: January, 1961.

4
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:02,728
President Dwight D. Eisenhower's
Farewell Address to the Nation.

5
00:01:02,854 --> 00:01:07,816
This conjunction of an immense military
establishment and arms industry is new

6
00:01:08,234 --> 00:01:10,110
in the American experience.

7
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,945
EISENHOWER: The totaI influence,

8
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:14,907
economic, political, even spiritual,

9
00:01:15,575 --> 00:01:20,287
is felt in every city, every Statehouse,
every government office.

10
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:23,165
EISENHOWER: We must guard
against the acquisition

11
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:27,086
of unwarranted influence,
whether sought or unsought

12
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:29,922
by the military-industrial complex.

13
00:01:30,465 --> 00:01:33,008
We must never let the weight
of this combination

14
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:36,178
endanger our liberties
or democratic processes.

15
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:39,348
NARRATOR: November, 1960.

16
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:42,559
Senator John Fitzgerald Kennedy
of Massachusetts

17
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:46,063
wins one of the narrowest election
victories in American history

18
00:01:46,147 --> 00:01:50,692
over Vice President Richard Nixon
by a little more than 100,000 votes.

19
00:01:51,402 --> 00:01:55,364
Alongside his beautiful
and elegant wife, Jacqueline Bouvier,

20
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:59,118
Kennedy is the symbol
of the new freedom of the 1960s,

21
00:01:59,369 --> 00:02:02,621
signifying change and upheaval
to the American public.

22
00:02:02,705 --> 00:02:04,456
"All men are created equal. "

23
00:02:04,541 --> 00:02:08,127
JFK: Every degree of mind and spirit
that I possess will be devoted

24
00:02:08,211 --> 00:02:10,420
to the cause of freedom
around the world.

25
00:02:10,505 --> 00:02:12,798
JFK: Today, the proudest boast is,

26
00:02:13,007 --> 00:02:14,883
"Ich bin ein Berliner!"

27
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:17,636
NARRATOR:
He inherits a secret war against

28
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,597
the Communist Castro
dictatorship in Cuba,

29
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:24,059
a war run by the CIA
and angry Cuban exiles.

30
00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:26,979
Castro is a successful revolutionary,

31
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:30,482
frightening to American business
interests in Latin America.

32
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:34,194
This war culminates in the disastrous
Bay of Pigs invasion

33
00:02:34,279 --> 00:02:36,113
in April, 1961,

34
00:02:36,531 --> 00:02:41,034
when Kennedy refuses to provide
air cover for the exiled Cuban brigade.

35
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:44,538
Kennedy takes public responsibility
for the failure.

36
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:47,499
He privately claims the CIA lied to him

37
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:52,004
and tried to manipulate him into ordering
an American invasion of Cuba.

38
00:02:52,088 --> 00:02:53,672
[Castro speaks in Spanish]

39
00:02:53,882 --> 00:02:55,841
NARRATOR: In October, 1962

40
00:02:56,259 --> 00:02:59,011
the world comes to the brink
of nuclear war

41
00:02:59,095 --> 00:03:01,013
when Kennedy quarantines Cuba

42
00:03:01,097 --> 00:03:05,225
after announcing the presence
of offensive Soviet nuclear missiles

43
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:07,519
90 miles off American shores.

44
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:10,772
Soviet ships with more missiles
sail towards Cuba

45
00:03:11,065 --> 00:03:13,358
but at the last moment they turn back.

46
00:03:13,443 --> 00:03:15,736
The world breathes with relief.

47
00:03:15,945 --> 00:03:20,365
In Washington, rumors abound
that JFK has cut a secret deal

48
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:22,159
with Russian Premier Khrushchev

49
00:03:22,243 --> 00:03:26,622
not to invade Cuba in return
for a Russian withdrawal of missiles.

50
00:03:26,956 --> 00:03:30,459
Suspicions abound that Kennedy
is soft on communism.

51
00:03:31,961 --> 00:03:35,714
Kennedy also finds himself embroiled
in Laos and Vietnam.

52
00:03:35,924 --> 00:03:38,091
We've got our difficulties there.

53
00:03:38,301 --> 00:03:41,136
Unless a greater effort is made
by the government

54
00:03:41,262 --> 00:03:44,973
to win popular support,
I don't think the war can be won there.

55
00:03:45,141 --> 00:03:48,894
It's their war. They're the ones
who have to win it or lose it.

56
00:03:48,978 --> 00:03:50,896
NARRATOR: Early that fateful summer,

57
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:54,399
Kennedy speaks of his new vision
at the American University.

58
00:03:54,651 --> 00:03:56,235
JFK: What kind of peace do I mean?

59
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,153
What kind of peace do we seek?

60
00:03:58,446 --> 00:04:00,280
JFK: Not a Pax Americana

61
00:04:00,448 --> 00:04:03,909
enforced on the world
by American weapons of war.

62
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:08,163
We must re-examine our own attitudes
towards the Soviet Union.

63
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:10,832
Our most basic, common link

64
00:04:11,209 --> 00:04:13,293
is that we all inhabit

65
00:04:13,378 --> 00:04:15,003
this small planet.

66
00:04:15,296 --> 00:04:17,422
JFK: We all breathe the same air.

67
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:20,133
We all cherish our children's futures.

68
00:04:20,301 --> 00:04:22,177
And we are all mortal.

69
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,187
[Rose sobs]

70
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:34,314
You fucking assholes!

71
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,152
ROSE: Don't leave me here!

72
00:04:42,031 --> 00:04:43,991
ROSE: They've gone to Dallas.

73
00:04:44,158 --> 00:04:45,158
Friday.

74
00:04:46,202 --> 00:04:47,703
[Rose gasps]

75
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:49,871
They're going to kill

76
00:04:50,331 --> 00:04:51,665
Kennedy.

77
00:04:53,501 --> 00:04:55,043
ROSE: Call somebody.

78
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:57,546
Stop them.

79
00:05:01,217 --> 00:05:04,803
These are serious fucking guys.

80
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:08,724
[Rose gasps and moans]

81
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:13,312
DOCTOR: She's been high on something
since they brought her in.

82
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:14,563
Help!

83
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:16,356
Please!

84
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:23,363
[Military drumbeat]

85
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:02,277
[Sirens blare]

86
00:06:50,284 --> 00:06:52,661
[Crowd applauds and cheers]

87
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:05,674
[Gunshots]

88
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:13,849
CRONKITE: [On TV]
Here is a bulletin from CBS News.

89
00:07:14,308 --> 00:07:16,852
In Dallas, Texas, three shots were fired

90
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:19,980
at President Kennedy's motorcade
in downtown Dallas.

91
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:22,524
The first reports say
that President Kennedy

92
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:25,652
has been seriously wounded
by the shooting.

93
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:41,918
[Dramatic music plays softly]

94
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:44,045
[Door opens]

95
00:07:48,551 --> 00:07:49,885
What's wrong?

96
00:07:51,679 --> 00:07:53,472
The President's been shot.

97
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:55,891
In Dallas. Five minutes ago.

98
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:57,559
Oh, no!

99
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,563
How bad?

100
00:08:02,023 --> 00:08:04,566
No word. They think it's in the head.

101
00:08:05,735 --> 00:08:07,194
[Jim sighs]

102
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:14,910
JIM: Napoleon's has a TV set.

103
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:18,163
NEWSMAN 1: [On TV]
Three bullets were found.

104
00:08:18,247 --> 00:08:20,790
Gov. Connally also appeared
to have been hit.

105
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:25,378
The President was rushed to Parkland
Memorial Hospital, four miles away.

106
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:30,091
We are told the bullet entered the base
of the throat and came out the back,

107
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:32,427
but there is no confirmation.

108
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:36,765
Blood transfusions are being given.
A priest has administered the last rites.

109
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:38,517
[Crowd mumbles]

110
00:08:39,727 --> 00:08:41,436
JIM: There's still a chance.

111
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:43,188
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

112
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:44,648
Pull through, Jack.

113
00:08:44,732 --> 00:08:45,774
CRONKITE: From Dallas

114
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:48,318
the flash, apparently official:

115
00:08:48,402 --> 00:08:50,111
President Kennedy died

116
00:08:50,446 --> 00:08:53,573
at 1:00 p.m. Central Standard Time

117
00:08:54,116 --> 00:08:56,284
2:00 Eastern Standard Time,

118
00:08:56,911 --> 00:08:58,912
some 38 minutes ago.

119
00:08:59,121 --> 00:09:01,790
[Dramatic music plays softly]

120
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:04,376
[Woman sobs]

121
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:07,087
Vice President Johnson
has left the hospital.

122
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:11,091
Presumably he will take
the oath of office shortly

123
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:15,720
and become the 36th President
of the United States.

124
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:20,809
WOMAN: [Sobs on TV] He did so much
for this country, for colored people. Why?

125
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:24,271
[Shouting in bar]

126
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:27,649
MAN 1: Good-bye, you sorry bastard! Die!

127
00:09:28,442 --> 00:09:30,151
MAN 2: Shut the fuck up!

128
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:34,239
I'm ashamed to be an American today.

129
00:09:34,448 --> 00:09:37,826
CRONKITE: [On TV] The President
of the United States is dead.

130
00:09:38,452 --> 00:09:41,079
NEWSMAN 2: [On TV]
I just talked to Father Hubert

131
00:09:41,163 --> 00:09:43,415
of the Holy Trinity Catholic Church.

132
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:45,000
He told me

133
00:09:45,334 --> 00:09:48,795
President Kennedy has been given
the last rites.

134
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:52,007
NEWSMAN 3: [On TV] Shortly after 12:30,

135
00:09:53,634 --> 00:09:55,927
near the park in downtown Dallas

136
00:09:56,012 --> 00:09:57,679
the shots rang out.

137
00:09:58,306 --> 00:10:00,181
The President is dead.

138
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:03,768
The bullets came up over our heads

139
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:07,105
from that fence up on the knoll.

140
00:10:07,481 --> 00:10:09,524
I seen his face when it hit.

141
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:15,113
His ear blew off and he turned real white.

142
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:20,535
He flopped over on his stomach

143
00:10:23,122 --> 00:10:25,123
with his foot sticking out.

144
00:10:27,543 --> 00:10:29,919
NEWSMAN 3: [On TV] None ofus
thought it could happen here

145
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:31,796
or any place else.

146
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:35,050
BANISTER: All this blubbering over
that no-count son of a bitch!

147
00:10:35,176 --> 00:10:38,678
They're bawling like they knew the man.
Makes me want to puke.

148
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:42,390
For God's sake, the President was shot.

149
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:44,225
A bullshit President!

150
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:47,604
Nobody's crying for the thousands
of Cubans

151
00:10:48,397 --> 00:10:51,983
that bastard condemned to death
and torture at Bay of Pigs.

152
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:55,028
Goddamn peace treaties!

153
00:10:55,154 --> 00:10:57,614
WOMAN: [On TV]
I heard shots from over there.

154
00:10:57,698 --> 00:11:01,076
MAN: [On TV] I heard shots over there.
TV REPORTER: How many?

155
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:05,497
BANISTER: That's what happens
when you let the niggers vote.

156
00:11:05,998 --> 00:11:09,000
They get together with the Jews
and the Catholics

157
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:11,711
and elect an Irish bleeding heart.

158
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:14,422
Chief, maybe you had too much to drink.

159
00:11:14,548 --> 00:11:16,007
BANISTER: Bullshit!

160
00:11:16,425 --> 00:11:18,593
Here's to the New Frontier.

161
00:11:19,387 --> 00:11:21,388
Camelot in smithereens.

162
00:11:22,682 --> 00:11:24,599
BANISTER: I'll drink to that.

163
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:27,602
[News coverage continues]

164
00:11:29,563 --> 00:11:32,023
NEWSMAN 4: [On TV]
Dallas police have announced

165
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:36,736
they have a suspect in the killing
of Dallas policeman J.D. Tippit

166
00:11:37,571 --> 00:11:41,658
who was shot at 1:15 in Oak Cliff,
a Dallas suburb.

167
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:45,704
Police say there could be a tie-in
to the President's murder.

168
00:11:45,788 --> 00:11:49,666
The suspect,
identified as a Lee Harvey Oswald

169
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:52,460
was arrested by more
than a dozen policemen

170
00:11:52,586 --> 00:11:56,089
after a short scuffle at a movie theater
in Oak Cliff.

171
00:11:57,633 --> 00:11:59,300
NEWSMAN 4: [On TV]
Officer Tippit was killed

172
00:12:00,636 --> 00:12:03,263
by a revolver which was found
on Oswald.

173
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:06,808
MAN 2: Shoot the bastard!

174
00:12:06,934 --> 00:12:09,644
MAN 1: Give him a medal
for shooting Kennedy!

175
00:12:12,356 --> 00:12:13,982
I don't know what I am charged with

176
00:12:14,984 --> 00:12:16,860
but I emphatically deny these charges.

177
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:22,073
BANISTER: The kid
must've gone nuts, right?

178
00:12:23,576 --> 00:12:25,744
I said, Oswald must've flipped.

179
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,078
Right?

180
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:31,624
Just did this crazy thing
before anybody could stop him.

181
00:12:32,209 --> 00:12:34,669
MARTIN: I'm going.
I've got to get home, Chief.

182
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:36,838
BANISTER: What are you talking about?

183
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:39,758
BANISTER: Who'd have ever thought

184
00:12:39,842 --> 00:12:44,137
that goofy Oswald kid would pull
a stunt like an assassination?

185
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:48,850
Goes to show you can never know
about some people. Am I right, Jack?

186
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:50,685
Am I right, Jack?

187
00:12:50,936 --> 00:12:52,937
BANISTER: Well, bless my soul.

188
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:56,983
All these years,
I thought you were on my team.

189
00:12:57,651 --> 00:12:59,444
Are you kidding?

190
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:02,781
I couldn't be more serious, Jack.

191
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:06,868
Your little red eyes have me wondering
about your loyalty.

192
00:13:15,336 --> 00:13:17,378
BANISTER: Look at that, Martin.

193
00:13:20,549 --> 00:13:22,717
Who's been going through my files?

194
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:26,846
BANISTER: You've been looking
through my files, you little weasel!

195
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:30,058
You're starting to get paranoid. Really!

196
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:33,102
You went through all my files!

197
00:13:33,729 --> 00:13:35,063
BANISTER: You're a goddamn spy!

198
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:37,649
Why would I want to look
through your files?

199
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:40,693
I've seen enough here this summer
to write a book.

200
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:43,154
I always lock my files!

201
00:13:43,572 --> 00:13:45,573
BANISTER: You're the only one here today.

202
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,535
What do you mean, you bastard?

203
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:51,162
You're going to write a book?

204
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:53,748
You know what I mean.

205
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:57,418
I've seen a lot of strange things here.

206
00:13:57,837 --> 00:13:59,337
Strange people.

207
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:01,756
[Grunting and groaning]

208
00:14:07,763 --> 00:14:10,181
You didn't see a goddamn thing!

209
00:14:10,432 --> 00:14:11,850
BANISTER: Not a goddamn thing!

210
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:15,395
NEWSMAN 4: [On TV] The full name
is Lee Harvey Oswald.

211
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:19,941
- Did you shoot the President?
- I didn't shoot anybody.

212
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:24,612
They have taken me in
because I have lived in the Soviet Union.

213
00:14:25,447 --> 00:14:27,115
I'm just a patsy!

214
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:30,034
LIZ: He sure looks like a creep.

215
00:14:30,786 --> 00:14:34,998
OSWALD: [On TV] I protested at that time
I was not allowed legal representation

216
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:39,460
during that very short and sweet hearing.

217
00:14:39,962 --> 00:14:41,546
I really don't know

218
00:14:41,755 --> 00:14:43,548
what this situation is about.

219
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:46,801
Nobody has told me anything
except that I am accused

220
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:49,137
of murdering a policeman.

221
00:14:49,221 --> 00:14:50,889
I know nothing more than that.

222
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:54,809
I do request someone to come forward

223
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:57,312
to give me legal assistance.

224
00:14:57,646 --> 00:15:00,565
NEWSMAN 5: [On TV] Were you ever
in the Free Cuba movement?

225
00:15:00,649 --> 00:15:03,067
RUBY: It's the Fair Play
for Cuba Committee.

226
00:15:03,652 --> 00:15:06,154
Why were you in Russia?
What happened to your eye?

227
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:09,157
He seems pretty cool
for a man under pressure.

228
00:15:09,491 --> 00:15:10,700
A policeman hit me.

229
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,577
LIZ: He gives me the willies.

230
00:15:12,661 --> 00:15:15,872
Come on, sugarplums,
it's past your bedtimes.

231
00:15:16,624 --> 00:15:20,168
Mattie, honey, get a hold of yourself.

232
00:15:23,839 --> 00:15:25,298
A fine man.

233
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:31,137
NEWSMAN 6: After a stint in the Marines,
he became fascinated by communism.

234
00:15:31,221 --> 00:15:33,681
He is said to be a dedicated Marxist

235
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:38,102
and a fanatical supporter of Fidel Castro
and ultra left-wing causes.

236
00:15:38,437 --> 00:15:41,356
He spent last summer in New Orleans
and was arrested

237
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:44,525
in a brawl with anti-Castro Cuban exiles.

238
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:50,490
JIM: Lou? Sorry to disturb you this late.

239
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:55,370
Matter of routine. Get on
this Oswald connection in New Orleans.

240
00:15:55,955 --> 00:16:00,458
Check out his record. Find any friends
or associates from last summer.

241
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:04,128
Let's meet with the investigators
day after tomorrow.

242
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,005
LOU: [On phone] On Sunday?

243
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:07,799
JIM: Sunday. 11:00.

244
00:16:08,884 --> 00:16:10,134
JIM: Thanks, Lou.

245
00:16:10,344 --> 00:16:13,471
I would say that he is the killer

246
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:17,016
beyond a reasonable doubt
and to a moral certainty.

247
00:16:17,476 --> 00:16:21,145
NEWMAN: [On TV] I thought a motorcycle
had backfired. I looked to my left.

248
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:23,147
A second shot hit him in the face.

249
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:26,484
NEWSMAN 1: [On TV]
The rifle, a cheap World War ll,

250
00:16:26,568 --> 00:16:28,403
Italian-made Mannlicher-Carcano

251
00:16:28,487 --> 00:16:30,989
was ordered from
a Chicago mailing house

252
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:34,242
and shipped to Oswald's alias, A. Hidell

253
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:37,495
at a post office box in March of 1963.

254
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:41,249
This same rifle was used
to assassinate the President.

255
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:43,251
That ties it up.

256
00:16:43,919 --> 00:16:47,672
NUMA: Another nut. Jesus Christ,
anybody can get a rifle in Texas!

257
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:52,427
LOU: As far as Oswald's associates,
one name keeps popping up: David Ferrie.

258
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:55,847
Oswald was seen with him
several times last summer.

259
00:16:56,223 --> 00:16:59,350
I know David. Strange character.

260
00:16:59,435 --> 00:17:03,187
LOU: He's been in trouble before.
He was a hot-shot pilot for Eastern Airlines.

261
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:05,898
Got canned after an alleged
homosexual incident.

262
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:10,236
NEWSMAN 1: [On TV] These photos
were found among Oswald's possessions

263
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:14,282
in the garage where Marina Oswald
and her children are living.

264
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:17,952
Somebody mentioned Ferrie
on that Texas trip. Find that out.

265
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:21,080
MARINA: [On TV] He no shoot anyone.

266
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:23,624
He good man. Good husband.

267
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:28,379
BILL: So it seems David Ferrie drove off
on Friday afternoon for Texas.

268
00:17:28,547 --> 00:17:31,966
A source said he might have been
a getaway pilot for Oswald.

269
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:34,969
Hold your horses.

270
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:36,721
What kind of source?

271
00:17:36,972 --> 00:17:39,057
The anonymous kind, Chief.

272
00:17:39,308 --> 00:17:43,144
I remember Ferrie speaking
at a meeting of some veterans group

273
00:17:43,312 --> 00:17:46,272
ranting against Castro. Extreme stuff.

274
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:51,319
JIM: They're bringing him out.
Numa, turn it up.

275
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:54,405
NEWSMAN 2: [On TV] Here he comes!

276
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:02,080
NEWSMAN 3: [On TV]
Anything to say in your defense?

277
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:03,247
RUBY: Oswald!

278
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:04,832
[Gunshot]

279
00:18:05,501 --> 00:18:06,959
NUMA: He shot him!

280
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:08,252
[Shouting]

281
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:10,797
NUMA: He shot him on TV!

282
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:16,469
SPECTATOR: [On TV]
There's a man with a gun!

283
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:20,181
LOU: Seventy cops there.
What were they doing?

284
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:26,229
No trial now. Somebody just saved
the Dallas DA a pile of work.

285
00:18:32,319 --> 00:18:34,987
Let's get David Ferrie in here anyway.

286
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:37,907
It's wrong. This is crazy!

287
00:18:40,702 --> 00:18:43,621
[Somber, instrumental music]

288
00:18:52,589 --> 00:18:54,632
NEWSMAN 7: [On TV]
Yesterday, in the midst of sorrow,

289
00:18:54,716 --> 00:18:56,634
the business of government went on.

290
00:18:57,177 --> 00:19:01,973
The President met with Henry Cabot Lodge,
our Ambassador to Vietnam

291
00:19:02,057 --> 00:19:03,724
and members of his Cabinet.

292
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:06,018
The major subject was Vietnam,

293
00:19:06,186 --> 00:19:08,980
a crisis that does not pause
for bereavement.

294
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:10,481
From this meeting

295
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:14,819
came affirmations that
the US would continue aiding

296
00:19:14,903 --> 00:19:19,407
the new government of Vietnam in
its war against the Communist insurgents.

297
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:23,369
[Knock on door]

298
00:19:26,248 --> 00:19:27,748
David Ferrie.

299
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:30,835
JIM: Come on in.

300
00:19:31,753 --> 00:19:33,171
JIM: Thanks for coming.

301
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:38,134
Remember me? We met
on Carondelet Street after your election.

302
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:41,095
JIM: I remember.
You make quite an impression.

303
00:19:41,430 --> 00:19:44,098
I've heard you're a first-rate pilot.

304
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:48,603
Legend has it you can get in
and out of the smallest field.

305
00:19:49,104 --> 00:19:53,274
I'm a pilot myself. Flew grasshoppers
for the field artillery in the war.

306
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:56,068
Make yourself comfortable.

307
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:59,739
FERRIE: Mind if I smoke?

308
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:01,574
JIM: How could I?

309
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:05,786
As you know, President Kennedy
was assassinated on Friday.

310
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:09,123
JIM: A man named Lee Harvey Oswald
was arrested as a suspect,

311
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:12,460
then murdered yesterday
by a man named Jack Ruby.

312
00:20:13,295 --> 00:20:16,255
JIM: We've had reports that Oswald
spent the summer here

313
00:20:16,381 --> 00:20:18,466
and that you knew Oswald.

314
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:23,387
I've never met anyone named Oswald.
Anyone who told you that has to be crazy.

315
00:20:23,472 --> 00:20:27,475
JIM: He served in your Civil Air Patrol unit
when he was a teenager.

316
00:20:27,809 --> 00:20:29,977
If he did, I don't remember him.

317
00:20:30,812 --> 00:20:32,605
Lots of boys in and out.

318
00:20:32,731 --> 00:20:36,984
JIM: Surely you've seen this. Perhaps
you knew him under another name?

319
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:41,572
I never saw him before in my life.

320
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:45,826
Then we must have gotten
mistaken information.

321
00:20:46,119 --> 00:20:48,287
Thanks for straightening it out.

322
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:52,333
JIM: There's one other matter.

323
00:20:54,461 --> 00:20:59,382
JIM: We heard you went to Texas
shortly after the assassination on Friday.

324
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:01,509
True. I drove to Houston.

325
00:21:01,677 --> 00:21:04,095
JIM: What was so appealing
about Houston?

326
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:08,140
I hadn't been ice-skating lately.
Some young friends and I

327
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,976
decided to go skating.

328
00:21:10,143 --> 00:21:12,603
JIM: Why the urge to ice-skate in Texas

329
00:21:12,813 --> 00:21:16,023
during one of the worst thunderstorms
in recent memory?

330
00:21:16,358 --> 00:21:18,109
[Thunder rumbles]

331
00:21:19,027 --> 00:21:20,778
Spur-of-the-moment thing.

332
00:21:20,862 --> 00:21:22,613
Storm wasn't that bad.

333
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,200
Where did you drive?

334
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:27,326
We went to Houston.

335
00:21:28,370 --> 00:21:30,997
FERRIE: Saturday we drove to Galveston,
and stayed there.

336
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:32,873
And Sunday?

337
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:35,835
In the morning, we went goose hunting.

338
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:38,379
JIM: Did you bag any?

339
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:40,631
The boys got a couple.

340
00:21:40,799 --> 00:21:42,717
Boys said they didn't get any.

341
00:21:46,221 --> 00:21:47,471
They're right.

342
00:21:47,723 --> 00:21:51,475
There were thousands
of geese everywhere.

343
00:21:52,644 --> 00:21:55,479
But you couldn't approach them.
They're wise.

344
00:21:56,982 --> 00:21:59,650
Your friends said you had no weapons.

345
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:03,529
JIM: Isn't it difficult to hunt geese
without a shotgun?

346
00:22:08,827 --> 00:22:10,870
I remember now. I'm sorry.

347
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:12,747
FERRIE: I got confused.

348
00:22:12,914 --> 00:22:17,209
We got near the geese, then realized
we had forgotten our shotguns.

349
00:22:18,337 --> 00:22:19,920
FERRIE: Stupid, right?

350
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:23,257
So, of course, we didn't get any geese.

351
00:22:24,217 --> 00:22:26,260
JIM: Thank you for your time.

352
00:22:27,429 --> 00:22:29,597
JIM: Sorry this must end inconveniently

353
00:22:29,723 --> 00:22:33,184
but I must detain you for questioning
by the FBl.

354
00:22:33,935 --> 00:22:35,186
Why? What's wrong?

355
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:37,229
Your story is not believable.

356
00:22:39,107 --> 00:22:40,358
Really?

357
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:45,029
What part?

358
00:22:46,948 --> 00:22:49,784
[Somber, instrumental music plays on TV]

359
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:08,803
FBl SPOKESMAN: This afternoon the FBl
released David W. Ferrie

360
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:10,054
of New Orleans.

361
00:23:10,222 --> 00:23:13,307
After extensive questioning
and a background check,

362
00:23:13,392 --> 00:23:18,437
the Bureau found no evidence
that Mr. Ferrie knew Lee Harvey Oswald

363
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:23,234
or had any connection
with the assassination.

364
00:23:23,318 --> 00:23:26,570
FBl SPOKESMAN: [On TV] The agent
in charge would like to make clear

365
00:23:26,655 --> 00:23:29,240
that Ferrie was brought in
for questioning

366
00:23:29,324 --> 00:23:32,159
by the District Attorney
of Orleans Parish.

367
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:35,121
LOU: I thought we were on the same side.

368
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:37,164
Why are they saying that?

369
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:39,834
Pretty fast, the way they let him go.

370
00:23:40,502 --> 00:23:42,920
JIM: They must know something we don't.

371
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:46,173
So let's get on with our lives.

372
00:23:46,508 --> 00:23:48,676
We have many homegrown crimes
to prosecute.

373
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,594
NEWSMAN:
The President has announced

374
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:54,515
the creation of a commission
to probe the events in Dallas.

375
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:59,437
It will be headed
by Chief Justice Earl Warren

376
00:23:59,521 --> 00:24:04,150
and is expected to head off
several Congressional and Texas inquiries.

377
00:24:04,359 --> 00:24:07,528
On the panel are Allen Dulles,
ex-chief of the CIA,

378
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:10,489
Representative Gerald Ford,
banker John McCloy.

379
00:24:10,574 --> 00:24:11,574
[Dixieland music]

380
00:24:15,871 --> 00:24:20,332
SEN. LONG: Fucking out of control. All of
these hippies running around on drugs.

381
00:24:21,168 --> 00:24:24,211
SEN. LONG: You can't tell a boy
from a girl anymore.

382
00:24:25,046 --> 00:24:29,508
I saw a girl the other day. Pregnant.
You could see her whole belly.

383
00:24:30,010 --> 00:24:33,345
You know what she had painted on it?
"Love Child. "

384
00:24:33,513 --> 00:24:35,055
[Both chuckle]

385
00:24:38,351 --> 00:24:40,227
SEN. LONG: It's a mess down there, Jim.

386
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:44,482
We've bitten off more Vietnam
than we can chew.

387
00:24:44,691 --> 00:24:48,319
It figures with that polecat Lyndon
in the White House.

388
00:24:50,071 --> 00:24:54,158
I sometimes think things have gone
downhill since Kennedy died.

389
00:24:55,243 --> 00:24:56,911
Don't get me started on that.

390
00:24:57,037 --> 00:25:01,040
Those Warren Commission fellows
were picking gnat shit out of pepper.

391
00:25:01,208 --> 00:25:05,669
Nobody's going to tell me that kid
shot like he did from that bookstore.

392
00:25:06,254 --> 00:25:07,755
Thank you, honey.

393
00:25:08,048 --> 00:25:11,258
But the FBl test-fired the rifle
to see if it could be done.

394
00:25:11,384 --> 00:25:14,261
Three experts and not one
of them could do it.

395
00:25:14,763 --> 00:25:18,933
They say that Oswald got off three shots
with world-class precision

396
00:25:19,351 --> 00:25:22,770
from a manual bolt-action rifle
in less than six seconds.

397
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:26,524
According to his Marine buddies,
he got Maggie's drawers.

398
00:25:26,858 --> 00:25:29,193
That means he wasn't any good.

399
00:25:29,694 --> 00:25:32,196
SEN. LONG: Average man would be lucky
to shoot twice.

400
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:34,740
And the first would be the best.

401
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:37,284
Here the third shot's perfect.

402
00:25:37,577 --> 00:25:40,538
And they got that bullet zigzagging
all over the place

403
00:25:40,622 --> 00:25:42,748
hitting Kennedy and Connally
seven times.

404
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:47,294
One pristine bullet? That dog don't hunt.

405
00:25:50,298 --> 00:25:53,467
Something's always bothered me
about that from day one.

406
00:25:54,719 --> 00:25:57,054
JIM: Think other men were involved?

407
00:25:57,973 --> 00:26:02,726
If I was investigating the case, I'd round up
100 of the world's best riflemen

408
00:26:02,978 --> 00:26:05,563
and find out which ones were
in Dallas that day.

409
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:09,149
You been duck hunting.
Oswald's an old-fashioned decoy.

410
00:26:09,401 --> 00:26:12,653
What did he say? "I'm just a patsy!"
Believe it.

411
00:26:16,408 --> 00:26:18,826
[Instrumental jazz music]

412
00:26:24,666 --> 00:26:26,834
LIZ: Dinner's just about ready.

413
00:26:28,336 --> 00:26:31,839
LIZ: Got a surprise for you tonight.
Tried something new.

414
00:26:34,342 --> 00:26:35,509
Jim?

415
00:26:37,137 --> 00:26:38,262
Jim.

416
00:26:38,346 --> 00:26:39,972
JIM: What?
LIZ: Dinner.

417
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:43,726
Smells good. Do you know Oswald

418
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:47,021
was interrogated for 12 hours
after the assassination

419
00:26:47,105 --> 00:26:51,025
with no lawyer present,
and nobody recorded a word of it.

420
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:56,447
I can't believe it. An experienced
police captain and a crowd of FBl agents

421
00:26:56,531 --> 00:27:01,452
had to know that with no record,
what Oswald said is inadmissible in court.

422
00:27:01,536 --> 00:27:04,204
Let's talk at the table. It's getting cold.

423
00:27:04,497 --> 00:27:06,457
LIZ: What are you doing here?

424
00:27:06,541 --> 00:27:08,792
Daddy said it's okay if I'm quiet.

425
00:27:09,210 --> 00:27:10,377
JIM: Sure it is.

426
00:27:10,545 --> 00:27:13,714
If I handled a minor felon that way,
it'd be all over the papers.

427
00:27:13,840 --> 00:27:15,549
This is the alleged murderer
of the President.

428
00:27:22,974 --> 00:27:26,060
JIM: Again and again
credible testimony's ignored.

429
00:27:26,311 --> 00:27:30,981
Leads are not followed up,
conclusions are selective, no index.

430
00:27:31,066 --> 00:27:34,777
It's the sloppiest investigation
I've ever seen.

431
00:27:35,820 --> 00:27:39,239
Dozens of witnesses heard the shots

432
00:27:39,324 --> 00:27:41,992
coming from the grassy knoll
in front of Kennedy

433
00:27:42,077 --> 00:27:44,495
not the Book Depository behind him.

434
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:49,833
But it's broken down and spread around.
You read it, but the point is lost.

435
00:27:49,918 --> 00:27:51,877
MATTIE: I never believed it.

436
00:27:52,212 --> 00:27:54,838
LIZ: I'll do the dishes. You take Eb up.

437
00:27:56,257 --> 00:27:58,509
Elizabeth, your bedtime too!

438
00:27:58,927 --> 00:28:02,846
That was three years ago.
We've tried to put it out of our minds.

439
00:28:03,014 --> 00:28:04,932
You keep digging it up.

440
00:28:05,558 --> 00:28:07,434
You're the DA of New Orleans.

441
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:10,854
Isn't the Kennedy assassination
a bit out of your domain?

442
00:28:11,731 --> 00:28:13,774
All those important people studied it.

443
00:28:13,858 --> 00:28:18,362
I can't believe a man as intelligent
as Earl Warren read those volumes.

444
00:28:19,781 --> 00:28:21,281
Maybe you're right.

445
00:28:21,741 --> 00:28:26,078
You got an hour to solve the case
while I get the kids in bed.

446
00:28:26,913 --> 00:28:30,958
Then you're mine. Mr. Kennedy
will have to wait until morning.

447
00:28:35,714 --> 00:28:37,965
JASPER: Look, Dad. Look what I drew.

448
00:28:38,299 --> 00:28:40,384
That's something. What is it?

449
00:28:40,468 --> 00:28:42,261
It's a rhino in a cage.

450
00:28:42,762 --> 00:28:45,639
- Can I stay up another hour?
- I don't think so, Son.

451
00:28:45,765 --> 00:28:48,058
JIM: Pickle and Snapper, my two

452
00:28:49,144 --> 00:28:50,477
dancing partners.

453
00:28:50,562 --> 00:28:52,563
JIM: Good night, doodlebugs.

454
00:28:53,314 --> 00:28:55,149
LIZ: One hour, you hear?

455
00:28:55,817 --> 00:28:58,152
Some Saturday-night date you are.

456
00:28:58,403 --> 00:29:02,990
Mama warned me this would happen
if I married such a serious man as you.

457
00:29:03,575 --> 00:29:07,578
When I come up, I'll show you
how Saturday night got invented.

458
00:29:19,174 --> 00:29:20,716
[Clock chimes]

459
00:29:31,644 --> 00:29:36,148
BOWERS: I sealed off the area and held off
the trains till they could be examined.

460
00:29:36,357 --> 00:29:40,027
There were some transients taken on
at least one train.

461
00:29:41,613 --> 00:29:46,867
BALL: Mr. Bowers, you already talked to us
about this matter. Is that correct?

462
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:48,368
BOWERS: Yes.

463
00:29:48,495 --> 00:29:50,704
BALL: Is there anything else you told us

464
00:29:50,830 --> 00:29:54,124
that I haven't asked you about,
that you can think of?

465
00:29:55,293 --> 00:29:57,377
Nothing that I can recall.

466
00:29:58,046 --> 00:29:59,630
BALL: Witness is excused.

467
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:02,883
SGT. HARKNESS:
A long freight was in there

468
00:30:02,967 --> 00:30:05,928
and we pulled some people off
and took them to the station.

469
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:08,680
[Shouting]

470
00:30:09,891 --> 00:30:11,141
BELIN: Do you mean some transients?

471
00:30:11,851 --> 00:30:13,227
Tramps and hobos.

472
00:30:13,311 --> 00:30:15,062
BELIN: Were they questioned?

473
00:30:15,146 --> 00:30:17,523
SGT. HARKNESS:
They were questioned at the station.

474
00:30:18,566 --> 00:30:19,775
JIM: Ask the question.

475
00:30:20,902 --> 00:30:23,487
BELIN: Let's go back
to that Amos Euins matter.

476
00:30:25,031 --> 00:30:28,826
BOWERS: Traffic had been cut off
into the area since 10:00.

477
00:30:28,910 --> 00:30:32,371
But three cars came in during this time

478
00:30:33,414 --> 00:30:36,333
from around noon till the time
of the shooting.

479
00:30:36,835 --> 00:30:39,211
They circled the parking lot and left.

480
00:30:39,921 --> 00:30:42,339
Like they was checking the area.

481
00:30:43,091 --> 00:30:44,800
BOWERS: One of the drivers

482
00:30:45,009 --> 00:30:47,761
was holding something up to his mouth.

483
00:30:49,514 --> 00:30:55,269
BOWERS: The last car came in about seven
to ten minutes before the shooting.

484
00:30:56,271 --> 00:30:59,273
It was a white Chevrolet four-door Impala.

485
00:31:00,275 --> 00:31:02,276
Muddy up to the windows.

486
00:31:03,778 --> 00:31:06,905
BOWERS: Towards the underpass,
I saw two men

487
00:31:07,115 --> 00:31:09,741
standing behind a picket fence

488
00:31:10,201 --> 00:31:13,954
looking up towards Main and Houston,
as the caravan came down.

489
00:31:16,624 --> 00:31:18,625
One of them was middle-aged

490
00:31:18,751 --> 00:31:20,043
heavyset.

491
00:31:20,795 --> 00:31:22,045
The other man was younger.

492
00:31:23,381 --> 00:31:26,592
BOWERS: Two other men were
on the east end of the parking lot.

493
00:31:26,801 --> 00:31:28,635
They both had uniforms.

494
00:31:29,262 --> 00:31:31,597
At the time of the shooting

495
00:31:31,806 --> 00:31:34,558
there seemed to be some commotion.

496
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:38,896
I'm just unable to describe

497
00:31:40,481 --> 00:31:43,734
a flash of light or smoke or something

498
00:31:44,485 --> 00:31:47,654
which caused me to feel that something
out of the ordinary

499
00:31:47,739 --> 00:31:49,781
had occurred on the embankment.

500
00:31:49,991 --> 00:31:51,074
Goddamn.

501
00:31:51,284 --> 00:31:54,161
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

502
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,295
[Shouting]

503
00:32:05,089 --> 00:32:06,423
[Gunshot]

504
00:32:06,674 --> 00:32:08,091
[Screaming]

505
00:32:08,509 --> 00:32:09,509
JIM: No!

506
00:32:14,807 --> 00:32:17,601
- You all right?
- Honey, it's incredible.

507
00:32:18,311 --> 00:32:19,478
What?

508
00:32:20,104 --> 00:32:21,688
The whole thing.

509
00:32:22,315 --> 00:32:24,483
A Lt. Colonel testifies that

510
00:32:24,609 --> 00:32:28,779
Oswald had a Russian language exam
as part of his Marine training

511
00:32:28,863 --> 00:32:32,115
only a few months before he defects
to the Soviet Union.

512
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,784
A Russian exam.

513
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:38,789
It's 4:30 in the morning!
I have five kids who'll wake up in an hour.

514
00:32:38,873 --> 00:32:43,418
In all my years in the military, I never knew
a single man who had a Russian test.

515
00:32:44,504 --> 00:32:46,505
Oswald was a radar operator.

516
00:32:46,881 --> 00:32:50,217
He'd have about as much use for Russian
as a cat has for pajamas.

517
00:32:50,385 --> 00:32:53,011
LIZ: These books have gotten to your mind!

518
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:56,682
LIZ: Stop reading.
JIM: He makes it sound like nothing.

519
00:32:56,975 --> 00:32:58,892
Oswald did badly on his test.

520
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:02,521
He got only two more Russian words right
than wrong.

521
00:33:02,897 --> 00:33:06,149
That's like me saying,
Touchdown is not very intelligent

522
00:33:06,234 --> 00:33:10,362
because I beat him three games
out of five when we played chess.

523
00:33:10,738 --> 00:33:14,574
LIZ: Are you going to stay up all night,
every night? For what?

524
00:33:15,159 --> 00:33:18,412
To be the only man who's read
all 26 volumes of the Warren Report?

525
00:33:18,538 --> 00:33:20,872
Do I have to spell it out for you?

526
00:33:21,916 --> 00:33:24,501
Lee Oswald was no ordinary soldier.

527
00:33:25,378 --> 00:33:28,839
He was in military intelligence,
that's why he was trained in Russian.

528
00:33:28,923 --> 00:33:31,091
It was no accident he was in Russia.

529
00:33:31,175 --> 00:33:34,761
LIZ: Go back to sleep.
JIM: I've been sleeping for three years!

530
00:33:35,596 --> 00:33:37,681
[Church bell rings in distance]

531
00:33:52,864 --> 00:33:55,532
'Morning boys. Ready for a walking tour?

532
00:33:55,616 --> 00:33:59,202
7:30 Sunday morning?
Not exactly fresh blood we're sniffing.

533
00:33:59,620 --> 00:34:01,955
Old stains, but just as telling.

534
00:34:09,630 --> 00:34:11,465
JIM: 531 Lafayette Street.

535
00:34:12,133 --> 00:34:14,468
Remember whose office this was in '63?

536
00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:17,721
Sure. Guy Banister.

537
00:34:18,306 --> 00:34:21,141
LOU: Ex-FBl man.
Died a couple of years ago.

538
00:34:23,811 --> 00:34:28,273
JIM: He headed the Chicago office. When
he retired he became a private eye here.

539
00:34:28,566 --> 00:34:32,402
I used to have lunch with him.
John Birch Society, Minutemen.

540
00:34:32,653 --> 00:34:34,029
To the right of Attila the Hun.

541
00:34:34,947 --> 00:34:38,658
JIM: Recruited students to infiltrate
radical organizations on campus.

542
00:34:39,619 --> 00:34:42,621
Headed the Anti-Communist League
of the Caribbean.

543
00:34:42,997 --> 00:34:44,998
All out of this office.

544
00:34:48,169 --> 00:34:50,295
I want to show you something.

545
00:34:55,093 --> 00:34:56,343
JIM: See that?

546
00:34:58,429 --> 00:34:59,971
Take a look here.

547
00:35:00,515 --> 00:35:02,182
544 Camp Street.

548
00:35:03,351 --> 00:35:05,268
531 Lafayette Street.

549
00:35:05,937 --> 00:35:07,771
JIM: Same building, right?

550
00:35:07,980 --> 00:35:12,025
Different addresses, different entrances,
both going to the same place

551
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:14,486
to the office upstairs.

552
00:35:14,862 --> 00:35:16,196
Guess who used it?

553
00:35:18,866 --> 00:35:20,659
JIM: Lee Harvey Oswald.

554
00:35:21,828 --> 00:35:23,662
How do we know that?

555
00:35:23,996 --> 00:35:25,789
This address was stamped on

556
00:35:25,873 --> 00:35:30,544
pro-Castro leaflets he handed out
in the summer of '63 on Canal Street.

557
00:35:31,045 --> 00:35:34,506
The same leaflets they found
in his garage in Dallas.

558
00:35:36,676 --> 00:35:40,971
After the arrest, 544 Camp St.
never appeared on the pamphlets again.

559
00:35:42,390 --> 00:35:45,517
He was arrested for fighting
with anti-Castro Cubans.

560
00:35:46,811 --> 00:35:49,020
But he'd contacted them already

561
00:35:49,105 --> 00:35:52,691
as an ex-Marine trying
to join their anti-Castro crusade.

562
00:35:53,192 --> 00:35:57,320
When they heard he was now pro-Castro,
they paid him a visit.

563
00:35:58,030 --> 00:35:59,489
CARLOS: What's this Fidel shit?

564
00:35:59,574 --> 00:36:01,283
CARLOS: You lied to me!

565
00:36:02,076 --> 00:36:03,743
Liar! Son of a bitch!

566
00:36:04,203 --> 00:36:06,705
Do not take this Communist propaganda!

567
00:36:07,748 --> 00:36:09,499
OSWALD: If you want to hit me, hit me.

568
00:36:09,584 --> 00:36:11,084
CARLOS: You pinko shit!

569
00:36:11,335 --> 00:36:12,919
Go back to Moscow!

570
00:36:13,254 --> 00:36:14,880
JIM: There was no real fight.

571
00:36:15,006 --> 00:36:18,925
The arresting Lieutenant later said
he felt it was a staged incident.

572
00:36:19,427 --> 00:36:21,720
In jail, Oswald has a private session

573
00:36:21,929 --> 00:36:24,764
with Special Agent John Quigley
of the FBl.

574
00:36:25,766 --> 00:36:27,267
Oswald is released.

575
00:36:27,393 --> 00:36:30,270
And Quigley destroys his notes
from the interview.

576
00:36:30,521 --> 00:36:33,356
The arrest gets Oswald a lot of publicity.

577
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:36,109
And he appears on a local TV debate.

578
00:36:36,861 --> 00:36:38,612
You are a Communist, are you not?

579
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:43,700
No, Mr. Bringuier. I am not a Communist.
I'm a Marxist-Leninist.

580
00:36:43,784 --> 00:36:47,245
CARLOS: Communist, Marxist-Leninist,
what's the difference?

581
00:36:48,956 --> 00:36:53,877
What if I told you Oswald was trained
in the Russian language in the Marines?

582
00:36:54,378 --> 00:36:56,713
LOU: I'd say he got intelligence training.

583
00:36:56,797 --> 00:36:58,882
You were a Marine. Who'd run it?

584
00:36:58,966 --> 00:37:00,967
Office of Naval Intelligence.

585
00:37:01,469 --> 00:37:03,470
Look across the street.

586
00:37:04,096 --> 00:37:05,388
BILL: Post Office.

587
00:37:05,806 --> 00:37:09,768
JIM: Upstairs, in 1963,
that was the Office of Naval Intelligence.

588
00:37:10,436 --> 00:37:13,939
By coincidence, Banister,
before he was FBl, was ONl.

589
00:37:14,273 --> 00:37:15,899
What's their saying?

590
00:37:15,983 --> 00:37:17,984
"Once ONl, always ONl. "

591
00:37:18,152 --> 00:37:20,737
He likes working near his old pals.

592
00:37:24,158 --> 00:37:25,825
We are standing in the heart

593
00:37:25,910 --> 00:37:29,496
of the US government's intelligence
community in New Orleans.

594
00:37:29,830 --> 00:37:31,164
That's the FBl.

595
00:37:31,415 --> 00:37:32,832
JIM: That's the CIA.

596
00:37:32,917 --> 00:37:34,584
That's the Secret Service.

597
00:37:34,669 --> 00:37:35,669
That's the ONl.

598
00:37:35,836 --> 00:37:38,255
Isn't this a strange place

599
00:37:38,339 --> 00:37:40,966
for a Communist
to spend his spare time?

600
00:37:44,262 --> 00:37:45,971
What are you driving at?

601
00:37:49,267 --> 00:37:51,268
We're going back into the case.

602
00:37:52,186 --> 00:37:53,770
The murder of the President.

603
00:37:53,854 --> 00:37:56,356
BILL: Lord, wake me. I must be dreaming.

604
00:37:56,649 --> 00:37:59,025
JIM: You're awake. I'm deadly serious.

605
00:37:59,193 --> 00:38:02,696
JIM: Now, let's track down your
anonymous source from three years ago.

606
00:38:02,780 --> 00:38:05,949
How'd you find out David Ferrie drove
to Texas that day?

607
00:38:06,033 --> 00:38:10,120
BILL: I can't remember last night,
let alone three years ago, Boss.

608
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:16,459
JIM: You're not being cross-examined.

609
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:21,047
I need clarification about the night
Guy Banister beat you over the head.

610
00:38:21,382 --> 00:38:23,717
Don't tell me you don't remember.

611
00:38:23,801 --> 00:38:28,638
You called our office from your hospital
bed. You were hopping mad about it.

612
00:38:29,682 --> 00:38:31,349
JIM: Here's my problem.

613
00:38:31,684 --> 00:38:35,020
You told me you and Guy were
good friends for a long time.

614
00:38:35,229 --> 00:38:37,814
- Over ten years.
- And he never hit you before?

615
00:38:37,898 --> 00:38:39,399
Never touched me.

616
00:38:39,984 --> 00:38:42,068
Yet, on November 22, 1963,

617
00:38:42,236 --> 00:38:44,571
the day of the President's murder,

618
00:38:44,697 --> 00:38:46,865
the police report says

619
00:38:47,366 --> 00:38:50,368
he pistol-whipped you
with a. 357 Magnum.

620
00:38:51,162 --> 00:38:54,331
It also says you argued
about the phone bill. Look!

621
00:38:55,708 --> 00:38:59,878
JIM: Is an argument over a phone bill
a believable explanation to you?

622
00:39:00,046 --> 00:39:01,755
[Hooves pounding]

623
00:39:02,923 --> 00:39:04,758
MARTIN: There's more to it.

624
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:07,510
JIM: How much more?

625
00:39:07,928 --> 00:39:09,346
I shouldn't talk about it.

626
00:39:09,430 --> 00:39:12,766
I'd ask Guy. We were friendly.
Heart attack?

627
00:39:13,434 --> 00:39:15,268
You buy what you read in the papers.

628
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:18,605
- You have other information?
- I didn't say that!

629
00:39:18,689 --> 00:39:23,401
All I know is he died suddenly.
Just before the Warren Report came out.

630
00:39:25,946 --> 00:39:27,781
Why did Guy beat you, Jack?

631
00:39:30,701 --> 00:39:33,244
[Distorted voices shouting]

632
00:39:35,706 --> 00:39:37,374
BANISTER: You were the only one here!

633
00:39:37,458 --> 00:39:39,125
The only one here!

634
00:39:39,960 --> 00:39:42,712
[Distorted sound effects]

635
00:39:43,964 --> 00:39:46,049
BANISTER: You didn't see
a goddamn thing!

636
00:39:46,759 --> 00:39:51,304
Hell, Guy's dead, so it don't matter
no more. It was all about those

637
00:39:51,806 --> 00:39:55,600
people that was hanging
around the office that summer.

638
00:39:56,310 --> 00:39:58,395
I was never part of the operation.

639
00:39:58,479 --> 00:40:02,440
I just handled their private-eye work
as it came in for Guy.

640
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:05,151
Not much did, but that's why I was there.

641
00:40:06,070 --> 00:40:07,070
[Shouting]

642
00:40:07,154 --> 00:40:08,947
MARTIN: It was a nuthouse.

643
00:40:09,782 --> 00:40:13,910
Cubans coming, going. And Christ,
they all looked the same to me.

644
00:40:15,579 --> 00:40:18,331
FERRIE: You going to play with this rifle
or pack it?

645
00:40:18,499 --> 00:40:19,999
MARTIN: Dave Ferrie.

646
00:40:20,084 --> 00:40:23,420
- You know about him?
- We know Dave. Was he there?

647
00:40:24,004 --> 00:40:26,506
MARTIN: He practically lived there.

648
00:40:28,008 --> 00:40:30,176
The whole thing was all

649
00:40:30,636 --> 00:40:32,679
cloak-and-dagger stuff.

650
00:40:32,763 --> 00:40:35,473
They called it "Operation Mongoose. "

651
00:40:36,809 --> 00:40:40,979
The idea was to train these Cuban exiles
for another invasion of Cuba.

652
00:40:41,647 --> 00:40:44,441
MARTIN: Banister's office was part
of the supply line

653
00:40:44,525 --> 00:40:47,110
from Dallas through New Orleans
to Miami.

654
00:40:47,194 --> 00:40:49,195
We stockpiled arms, explosives.

655
00:40:49,530 --> 00:40:53,032
JIM: In view of the intelligence community
in Lafayette Square?

656
00:40:53,117 --> 00:40:57,370
MARTIN: Yes. Everybody knew everybody.
They were all part of the network.

657
00:40:57,705 --> 00:40:59,539
All worked for the CIA.

658
00:41:00,374 --> 00:41:05,545
Pilots and black operators
and civilians and the military.

659
00:41:05,629 --> 00:41:08,173
Everybody was running guns then.

660
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:12,051
MARTIN: Ft. Jefferson, Bayou Bluff,
Morgan City, you name it.

661
00:41:12,344 --> 00:41:15,346
McAllen, Texas? Big gun-run operation.

662
00:41:19,685 --> 00:41:22,145
JIM: Where does Banister fit in?

663
00:41:22,229 --> 00:41:24,981
MARTIN: He was running his camp
north of Lake Pontchartrain.

664
00:41:25,065 --> 00:41:26,900
Ferrie did a lot of the training.

665
00:41:27,026 --> 00:41:31,488
They had a shooting range
and tropical territory, like in Cuba.

666
00:41:32,239 --> 00:41:34,491
Some Americans were trained there too.

667
00:41:34,658 --> 00:41:36,576
Nazi types. Mercenaries.

668
00:41:37,661 --> 00:41:40,914
That Ferrie, though,
Jesus, he was the craziest.

669
00:41:42,166 --> 00:41:47,337
Late summer the party was over.
Kennedy didn't want another Bay of Pigs.

670
00:41:48,756 --> 00:41:51,090
He told the FBl, "Shut up the camp.

671
00:41:51,258 --> 00:41:54,344
"Confiscate the napalm, C-4 and all. "

672
00:41:54,428 --> 00:41:58,431
The G-men were just going
through the motions.

673
00:41:58,516 --> 00:42:01,559
Their hearts were still
with their old FBl buddy Banister.

674
00:42:04,188 --> 00:42:05,438
JIM: Oswald?

675
00:42:10,110 --> 00:42:11,861
MARTIN: He was there too.

676
00:42:13,030 --> 00:42:15,448
MARTIN: Sometimes meeting
with Banister.

677
00:42:15,741 --> 00:42:17,867
[Oswald talks to Banister]

678
00:42:18,452 --> 00:42:20,286
MARTIN: With the door shut.

679
00:42:22,581 --> 00:42:26,626
Shootin' the bull with Ferrie, whatever.
But he was there, all right.

680
00:42:26,710 --> 00:42:28,169
Anything more specific, Jack?

681
00:42:28,963 --> 00:42:30,046
It's important.

682
00:42:33,801 --> 00:42:36,594
One time, the secretary got upset.

683
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:39,973
I can't believe it, Mr. Banister,
Oswald is down on Canal Street

684
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:43,309
handing out Communist leaflets
supporting Castro.

685
00:42:48,148 --> 00:42:50,733
It's okay, Delphine, he's with us.

686
00:42:53,404 --> 00:42:54,988
JIM: Was anyone else involved at

687
00:42:55,114 --> 00:42:56,656
Banister's level?

688
00:42:57,575 --> 00:42:59,409
One guy. I don't know who.

689
00:43:00,452 --> 00:43:02,120
MARTIN: Big. White hair.

690
00:43:03,122 --> 00:43:06,457
I saw him in the office once.
He looked out of place.

691
00:43:06,834 --> 00:43:08,793
You know, a society guy.

692
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:12,297
Can't remember his name,
but Oswald was with him.

693
00:43:14,091 --> 00:43:17,927
He had something to do with money,
because Banister never kissed ass

694
00:43:18,012 --> 00:43:19,679
but he kissed his.

695
00:43:27,354 --> 00:43:28,605
MARTIN: Clay something.

696
00:43:28,689 --> 00:43:30,982
That was his name. Clay.

697
00:43:31,066 --> 00:43:32,066
- Bertrand?
- Yeah.

698
00:43:32,151 --> 00:43:34,444
JIM: Clay Bertrand?
MARTIN: I don't know.

699
00:43:34,987 --> 00:43:36,863
MARTIN: Maybe not.
JIM: No, that's right.

700
00:43:36,989 --> 00:43:38,031
MARTIN: I must go.

701
00:43:38,657 --> 00:43:41,951
He was in the Warren Report.
He got Oswald a lawyer.

702
00:43:42,661 --> 00:43:43,953
Was Kennedy discussed?

703
00:43:44,038 --> 00:43:45,955
MARTIN: I don't know.

704
00:43:46,123 --> 00:43:47,874
JIM: The assassination?
MARTIN: No.

705
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:50,460
MARTIN: Not with me. I've got to go.
JIM: Hold on.

706
00:43:50,544 --> 00:43:53,129
MARTIN: That's all I'll say.
JIM: What's the problem?

707
00:43:57,384 --> 00:43:59,469
Do I have to spell it out for you?

708
00:43:59,553 --> 00:44:02,138
Nobody knows what
we're talking about here.

709
00:44:03,724 --> 00:44:05,642
You are so naive.

710
00:44:13,901 --> 00:44:15,860
[Instrumental jazz music]

711
00:44:16,070 --> 00:44:18,279
JIM: When'd you do business
with Bertrand?

712
00:44:18,364 --> 00:44:20,073
DEAN: Pipe the bimbo in red.

713
00:44:21,867 --> 00:44:22,825
DEAN: Lawdy.

714
00:44:22,910 --> 00:44:24,911
JIM: She's not as cute as you.

715
00:44:26,205 --> 00:44:30,249
JIM: You should try a legitimate business.
DEAN: Why are you dancing on my head?

716
00:44:30,376 --> 00:44:32,001
We've been friends since law school.

717
00:44:32,086 --> 00:44:33,252
JIM: Because you're conning me.

718
00:44:33,337 --> 00:44:36,339
JIM: I read your testimony.
DEAN: Grain of salt.

719
00:44:36,423 --> 00:44:40,468
You said Clay Bertrand called you
the day after the assassination

720
00:44:40,552 --> 00:44:43,763
- and asked you to be Oswald's lawyer.
- Right.

721
00:44:44,765 --> 00:44:46,766
That's pretty important.

722
00:44:46,934 --> 00:44:51,521
You told the FBl he's 6' 2".
Then you tell the Commission he's 5' 8".

723
00:44:51,897 --> 00:44:54,440
JIM: How the hell does
a man shrink like that?

724
00:44:54,858 --> 00:44:59,445
DEAN: They put the heat on me, like you. I
gave them whatever popped in my cabeza.

725
00:44:59,905 --> 00:45:01,864
Truth is, I never met the dude.

726
00:45:03,075 --> 00:45:05,785
CLAY: One likes friends that have friends.
DEAN: Indeed.

727
00:45:05,869 --> 00:45:09,038
I don't know what that cat looks like
or where he's at.

728
00:45:09,123 --> 00:45:12,125
All I know is sometimes
he sends me some cases.

729
00:45:12,251 --> 00:45:15,878
One day he calls, talks to me
about repping Oswald in Dallas.

730
00:45:16,130 --> 00:45:18,464
- You ever speak to Oswald in Dallas?
- No.

731
00:45:18,632 --> 00:45:22,301
I told that Bertrand cat right off
this ain't my scene.

732
00:45:22,469 --> 00:45:25,012
