He's taken to a radio factory in Minsk

962
00:58:47,899 --> 00:58:51,235
where he lives as high on the hog
as he ever has.

963
00:58:51,402 --> 00:58:56,114
He's given 5,000 rubles,
a roomy apartment with a balcony.

964
00:58:56,449 --> 00:58:58,450
Has affairs with local girls.

965
00:58:58,618 --> 00:59:00,536
Makes sense. He's a spokesman.

966
00:59:00,620 --> 00:59:01,954
[Chuckles]

967
00:59:02,038 --> 00:59:05,749
SUSIE: But he never does any propaganda
for the Russians.

968
00:59:06,709 --> 00:59:08,210
He meets Marina.

969
00:59:08,628 --> 00:59:11,880
Her uncle is a colonel
in Soviet intelligence.

970
00:59:13,550 --> 00:59:15,842
SUSIE: She thinks he's Russian
by his speech.

971
00:59:15,927 --> 00:59:18,929
Six weeks later they marry,
have a daughter.

972
00:59:19,222 --> 00:59:23,308
JIM: Only explanation for the royal
treatment is he gave them radar secrets.

973
00:59:23,560 --> 00:59:24,935
JIM: Or fake secrets.

974
00:59:25,103 --> 00:59:26,979
Six months after he's in Russia,

975
00:59:27,313 --> 00:59:30,649
Francis Gary Powers' U-2 spy flight
goes down

976
00:59:30,984 --> 00:59:33,443
in Russia. That plane was untouchable.

977
00:59:33,903 --> 00:59:35,529
SUSIE: Powers hinted that Oswald

978
00:59:35,613 --> 00:59:38,574
could've given the Russians
enough data to hit it.

979
00:59:38,658 --> 00:59:43,245
As a result, the peace summit between
Khrushchev and Eisenhower failed.

980
00:59:43,329 --> 00:59:47,499
Perhaps our military didn't want
the conference to happen?

981
00:59:47,834 --> 00:59:48,834
Susie, come on.

982
00:59:48,918 --> 00:59:51,211
SUSIE: Maybe Oswald was part of that!

983
00:59:51,296 --> 00:59:54,673
Stick to what you can prove in court.

984
00:59:54,757 --> 00:59:55,799
SUSIE: You want facts?

985
00:59:56,426 --> 01:00:00,762
Don't get sidetracked.
How'd he get back to the States?

986
01:00:00,972 --> 01:00:03,432
Does he have any problems
with Uncle Sam?

987
01:00:03,516 --> 01:00:07,019
No. The State Department issues him
a new passport in 48 hours

988
01:00:07,353 --> 01:00:09,354
and loans him travel money.

989
01:00:09,981 --> 01:00:15,027
He's never investigated or charged
for revealing classified information

990
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:18,030
or, as far as we know,
debriefed by the CIA.

991
01:00:18,114 --> 01:00:22,200
Bastard should've been prosecuted
as a traitor when he got off the boat.

992
01:00:23,369 --> 01:00:25,287
JIM: Did Marina have problems
getting out?

993
01:00:25,371 --> 01:00:29,708
SUSIE: None, though it's almost impossible
to get Russian sweethearts out.

994
01:00:30,668 --> 01:00:35,213
This is a man who defected once already.
It's crazy. Ordinary people

995
01:00:35,506 --> 01:00:38,800
get blacklisted
for having leftist affiliations.

996
01:00:38,885 --> 01:00:40,135
Doesn't add up.

997
01:00:40,219 --> 01:00:43,972
SUSIE: Next thing, he's living
in Dallas-Fort Worth, October '62,

998
01:00:44,057 --> 01:00:47,059
working six months
at Jaggars-Chiles-Stovall

999
01:00:47,185 --> 01:00:51,396
a photographic firm that makes maps
for the US Army.

1000
01:00:51,898 --> 01:00:55,317
Oswald becomes chummy
with the Dallas White Russian community.

1001
01:00:55,401 --> 01:00:57,277
All rabid anti-Communists.

1002
01:00:57,612 --> 01:00:58,654
It's odd.

1003
01:00:58,738 --> 01:01:04,159
SUSIE: His closest friend is an oilman,
named George DeMohrenschildt.

1004
01:01:04,243 --> 01:01:09,706
He is 35 years older than Oswald,
who is only 23 and supposedly broke.

1005
01:01:10,083 --> 01:01:15,504
He is a part of the Dallas Petroleum Club,
speaks five languages,

1006
01:01:15,588 --> 01:01:18,256
and was a French Vichy intelligence
during the war,

1007
01:01:18,591 --> 01:01:21,927
also rumored to be a Nazi sympathizer.

1008
01:01:24,430 --> 01:01:28,016
DeMohrenschildt draws a picture
of Oswald as an intellectual,

1009
01:01:28,101 --> 01:01:32,354
well read, speaks excellent Russian,
a man who adored JFK.

1010
01:01:36,067 --> 01:01:39,111
I think he's made some mistakes
regarding Cuba.

1011
01:01:39,779 --> 01:01:44,032
I think he's doing a pretty good job.
If he succeeds, in my opinion,

1012
01:01:44,117 --> 01:01:47,452
I think he'd make a great President
and a handsome one, too.

1013
01:01:47,745 --> 01:01:50,288
JIM: That's scenery, Susie.
Now, don't get sidetracked.

1014
01:01:50,707 --> 01:01:54,334
This is the same man that nailed Oswald
to the Warren Commission

1015
01:01:54,419 --> 01:01:57,462
as a potentially violent man
and linked him to the rifle.

1016
01:01:57,714 --> 01:02:01,091
OSWALD: Well,
in that sense Castro is an experimenter.

1017
01:02:03,094 --> 01:02:05,429
It could go any way with that country.

1018
01:02:05,596 --> 01:02:09,391
- It could go the way of the communism...
- What you got there?

1019
01:02:10,226 --> 01:02:12,144
Do you have rifles in there?

1020
01:02:13,146 --> 01:02:18,942
Tell me what I'm shooting at,
rabbits or Fascists?

1021
01:02:20,319 --> 01:02:22,612
- I hunt.
- You hunt?

1022
01:02:23,489 --> 01:02:26,199
We don't know he's CIA.
Let's circle him very probable.

1023
01:02:26,284 --> 01:02:27,951
Call him Oswald's handler.

1024
01:02:28,453 --> 01:02:32,831
SUSIE: The Oswalds are introduced
to Janet and Bill Williams.

1025
01:02:35,001 --> 01:02:39,588
It's through Janet Williams,
in October '63, that Lee gets the job

1026
01:02:39,672 --> 01:02:43,341
at the warehouse on Elm Street
at the Book Depository.

1027
01:02:44,051 --> 01:02:49,264
JIM: So he can now exercise his intellect,
stacking school texts at $1.25 an hour.

1028
01:02:50,600 --> 01:02:53,935
SUSIE: Marina fights with Lee
about many things.

1029
01:02:54,187 --> 01:02:56,146
[Lee and Marina argue]

1030
01:02:56,314 --> 01:02:58,482
His secrecy, their lack of money.

1031
01:02:59,525 --> 01:03:02,527
She says that Lee is not sexually adequate.

1032
01:03:05,323 --> 01:03:07,199
Lee hits her on several occasions.

1033
01:03:08,451 --> 01:03:09,951
SUSIE: At the age of24,

1034
01:03:10,036 --> 01:03:13,497
he rents a room in Dallas
under the alias of O.H. Lee.

1035
01:03:13,873 --> 01:03:17,501
Do you want to watch TV?
Are you all right?

1036
01:03:17,835 --> 01:03:19,795
No, thank you. I'm fine.

1037
01:03:20,713 --> 01:03:24,633
SUSIE: All I know about the Williams
is their tax returns are classified.

1038
01:03:24,717 --> 01:03:28,428
Bill Williams has links to the CIA
through his family

1039
01:03:28,513 --> 01:03:31,139
and does classified work
for Bell Helicopter.

1040
01:03:31,390 --> 01:03:35,894
Bill's convenient separation from Janet
allows Marina to move into her house

1041
01:03:36,020 --> 01:03:38,897
where she suddenly becomes
Marina's best friend.

1042
01:03:39,023 --> 01:03:42,025
There Marina and Lee
have a second daughter.

1043
01:03:43,236 --> 01:03:46,238
OSWALD: I have to go away.
Just for a short while.

1044
01:03:46,906 --> 01:03:48,865
What's wrong with this family?

1045
01:03:49,158 --> 01:03:50,659
MARINA: I love Lee

1046
01:03:50,743 --> 01:03:52,828
and I sorry him.

1047
01:03:53,579 --> 01:03:55,080
REPORTER: Sorry for him?

1048
01:03:55,414 --> 01:03:56,414
MARINA: Yes.

1049
01:03:56,499 --> 01:03:59,501
SUSIE: When he's arrested,
Marina buries him with the public.

1050
01:03:59,585 --> 01:04:03,129
She describes him as a psychotic
and violent man.

1051
01:04:03,339 --> 01:04:04,923
I have too much facts,

1052
01:04:05,049 --> 01:04:09,302
and facts tell me that Lee shot Kennedy.

1053
01:04:09,387 --> 01:04:12,764
JIM: After being locked away
by the feds for two months

1054
01:04:12,849 --> 01:04:14,933
and afraid she'd be deported,

1055
01:04:15,268 --> 01:04:18,436
she was probably suffering
from nervous exhaustion.

1056
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:20,856
JIM: They taught her how to answer.

1057
01:04:20,940 --> 01:04:23,942
When they think she's ready,
they buy her dresses,

1058
01:04:24,068 --> 01:04:26,278
polish her appearance and wheel her out.

1059
01:04:26,612 --> 01:04:28,613
I'd like to thank the Warren Commission.

1060
01:04:28,739 --> 01:04:30,282
JIM: Oswald was no angeI.

1061
01:04:31,617 --> 01:04:32,701
But who was he?

1062
01:04:33,286 --> 01:04:35,620
I'm lost. What are we saying?

1063
01:04:36,747 --> 01:04:40,625
JIM: That when Oswald went to Russia,
he was not a real defector.

1064
01:04:41,252 --> 01:04:46,673
He was an intelligence agent for our
government and remained one till he died.

1065
01:04:47,133 --> 01:04:49,759
So, because Oswald pulled the trigger,

1066
01:04:50,136 --> 01:04:54,389
the intelligence community
murdered the President?

1067
01:04:54,473 --> 01:04:56,808
JIM: I'll go you one better.
Maybe Oswald

1068
01:04:56,934 --> 01:04:58,727
didn't pull the trigger.

1069
01:04:58,811 --> 01:05:02,480
Nitrate tests indicate he hadn't fired
a rifle on November 22.

1070
01:05:02,565 --> 01:05:06,568
And they didn't bother to see
if the rifle'd been fired that day.

1071
01:05:06,944 --> 01:05:10,447
BILL: His palm print was on it.
JIM: It went to the FBl.

1072
01:05:10,907 --> 01:05:13,158
FBl didn't find a goddamn thing.

1073
01:05:13,326 --> 01:05:17,996
It comes back a week later and a Dallas
policeman suddenly finds a palm print?

1074
01:05:18,664 --> 01:05:22,667
It could've been taken at the morgue.
There's no chain of evidence.

1075
01:05:22,793 --> 01:05:26,755
LOU: I can't figure out why he orders
a traceable weapon

1076
01:05:27,340 --> 01:05:31,009
to a P.O. box, when he can go
into any store in Texas,

1077
01:05:31,510 --> 01:05:35,013
give a phony name and walk out
with an untraceable rifle.

1078
01:05:35,139 --> 01:05:36,431
To frame him, obviously!

1079
01:05:36,515 --> 01:05:38,850
A lot of smoke, but some fire.

1080
01:05:38,935 --> 01:05:40,936
We're talking about our government!

1081
01:05:41,020 --> 01:05:43,271
We're talking about a crime.

1082
01:05:44,023 --> 01:05:47,192
You must think on a different level,
like the CIA does.

1083
01:05:47,818 --> 01:05:50,195
We're through the looking glass.

1084
01:05:50,988 --> 01:05:52,280
White is black.

1085
01:05:53,199 --> 01:05:54,991
And black is white.

1086
01:05:55,701 --> 01:05:58,662
Maybe Oswald is just what he said he was.

1087
01:05:59,205 --> 01:06:00,497
A patsy.

1088
01:06:00,831 --> 01:06:02,374
[Eerie sound effects]

1089
01:06:06,295 --> 01:06:08,380
Unbelievable. You were here?

1090
01:06:08,547 --> 01:06:11,049
Yes, this is where I was sitting.

1091
01:06:11,342 --> 01:06:14,719
Shots came from near the wooden fence
over there,

1092
01:06:16,180 --> 01:06:17,847
near the overpass.

1093
01:06:18,057 --> 01:06:21,893
I saw a man run from the fence
toward those railroad cars.

1094
01:06:22,520 --> 01:06:24,771
HOLLAND: I made it clear
to the Warren people.

1095
01:06:24,855 --> 01:06:28,149
One of the shots came
from behind that picket fence.

1096
01:06:28,401 --> 01:06:32,570
I heard the report and saw smoke,
six or eight feet above the ground.

1097
01:06:32,863 --> 01:06:34,739
Out from under those trees.

1098
01:06:34,865 --> 01:06:38,118
DODD: All four of us railroad men

1099
01:06:38,244 --> 01:06:40,245
seen the same thing.

1100
01:06:40,579 --> 01:06:42,664
The smoke came from behind the hedge.

1101
01:06:42,748 --> 01:06:47,085
HILL: I was standing near Mary Moorman,
who took the photo when he was killed.

1102
01:06:49,755 --> 01:06:52,090
I stepped down to the curb and yelled,

1103
01:06:52,425 --> 01:06:54,843
"Mr. President, look over here!"

1104
01:06:56,887 --> 01:06:58,430
Then shots rang out.

1105
01:06:58,764 --> 01:06:59,931
[Gunshots]

1106
01:07:00,558 --> 01:07:05,687
HILL: Mary dropped to the ground, yelling,
"They're shooting! Get down!"

1107
01:07:05,771 --> 01:07:06,771
[Gunshots]

1108
01:07:06,856 --> 01:07:09,024
HILL: I just stood there watching.

1109
01:07:09,608 --> 01:07:11,609
The driver had stopped.

1110
01:07:12,236 --> 01:07:14,571
I don't know what was wrong with him.

1111
01:07:16,782 --> 01:07:18,950
Out of the corner of my eye,

1112
01:07:19,618 --> 01:07:21,161
I saw a flash of light in the bushes.

1113
01:07:22,413 --> 01:07:23,496
And that last shot

1114
01:07:23,581 --> 01:07:24,622
[Gunshot]

1115
01:07:25,249 --> 01:07:26,541
just ripped his head off.

1116
01:07:28,127 --> 01:07:32,130
I looked up and saw smoke coming
from over there, on the knoll.

1117
01:07:32,256 --> 01:07:34,799
SAM: We came around to look for tracks.

1118
01:07:35,301 --> 01:07:38,303
It rained that morning
and we found a bunch.

1119
01:07:38,971 --> 01:07:40,221
Cigarette butts.

1120
01:07:40,306 --> 01:07:42,682
Someone had stood about here.

1121
01:07:49,106 --> 01:07:50,607
That's a good spot.

1122
01:07:51,817 --> 01:07:52,859
LOU: For the head shot.

1123
01:07:52,943 --> 01:07:53,985
[Gunshot]

1124
01:07:54,737 --> 01:07:56,905
HILL: Everything was just frozen.

1125
01:07:57,573 --> 01:08:01,826
Like people weren't breathing.
Like you were looking at a picture.

1126
01:08:04,789 --> 01:08:06,456
Except for one man.

1127
01:08:07,291 --> 01:08:11,753
I saw this one man running
from the corner of the Book Depository

1128
01:08:11,837 --> 01:08:13,254
to the parking lot.

1129
01:08:13,339 --> 01:08:15,340
MERCER: It was about 11:00 a.m.

1130
01:08:15,591 --> 01:08:19,177
I was driving on Elm Street
toward the underpass in a rented car.

1131
01:08:19,804 --> 01:08:21,763
MERCER: A light-blue Valiant.

1132
01:08:22,014 --> 01:08:25,350
I'll never forget that day.
There was a lot of traffic

1133
01:08:25,476 --> 01:08:28,394
and I stopped
alongside a green pickup truck.

1134
01:08:28,687 --> 01:08:32,982
It was very noticeable
because it had one wheel up on the curb.

1135
01:08:33,192 --> 01:08:35,318
When I saw the gun, I thought

1136
01:08:37,446 --> 01:08:39,781
"The Secret Service is not very secret. "

1137
01:08:39,865 --> 01:08:42,617
The next morning, I went to the FBl office.

1138
01:08:42,701 --> 01:08:44,953
They showed me some pictures.

1139
01:08:45,037 --> 01:08:49,207
And I picked out three pictures
that looked like the truck's driver.

1140
01:08:49,875 --> 01:08:50,959
That's the man.

1141
01:08:51,460 --> 01:08:54,045
JIM: You mean you identified Jack Ruby
on Saturday?

1142
01:08:54,171 --> 01:08:55,130
MERCER: That's right.

1143
01:08:55,214 --> 01:08:57,048
The day before he shot Oswald?

1144
01:08:57,174 --> 01:09:00,677
MERCER: That's right.
When I saw him on TV, I was shocked.

1145
01:09:00,886 --> 01:09:04,222
I said to my family,
"That's the man I saw in the truck. "

1146
01:09:05,724 --> 01:09:08,643
You weren't so sure in your statement
to the Commission.

1147
01:09:09,019 --> 01:09:12,063
What about these others?
You said one might be him?

1148
01:09:13,190 --> 01:09:16,484
MERCER: They look a bit like him,
but I'm sure this is the man.

1149
01:09:16,569 --> 01:09:18,903
HILL: It was him I chased
up the grassy knoll.

1150
01:09:20,865 --> 01:09:24,534
HILL: I thought maybe our guys
had shot back and got one of them.

1151
01:09:25,244 --> 01:09:27,036
I got to the parking lot.

1152
01:09:27,830 --> 01:09:31,040
All I saw were the railroad workers
and Dallas' finest.

1153
01:09:32,751 --> 01:09:37,005
- Secret Service. Come with us.
- No! Find the shooter!

1154
01:09:37,590 --> 01:09:39,090
AGENT 1: I want your pictures.

1155
01:09:39,175 --> 01:09:40,258
Son of a bitch!

1156
01:09:40,426 --> 01:09:42,719
HILL: He put a hurt on me, but good.

1157
01:09:42,845 --> 01:09:47,473
They must've seen everything because
they knew what we had done all day.

1158
01:09:48,100 --> 01:09:51,102
I wasn't hard to find,
wearing that red raincoat.

1159
01:09:51,228 --> 01:09:53,354
How many shots did you hear?

1160
01:09:53,564 --> 01:09:55,231
HILL: Four to six.

1161
01:09:55,357 --> 01:09:56,524
Impossible!

1162
01:09:57,610 --> 01:09:59,527
INTERROGATOR: You heard echoes!

1163
01:09:59,612 --> 01:10:00,904
Echoes!

1164
01:10:01,447 --> 01:10:05,116
We have three bullets and three shots
that came from the Book Depository.

1165
01:10:05,201 --> 01:10:08,036
INTERROGATOR: That's all we'll say.
HILL: No, sir.

1166
01:10:08,120 --> 01:10:13,041
I saw a man shooting from behind
that fence. What are you going to do?

1167
01:10:13,417 --> 01:10:16,544
HILL: You go out and get him!
INTERROGATOR: That's taken care of!

1168
01:10:16,629 --> 01:10:20,215
You only heard three shots,
and don't discuss this with anyone.

1169
01:10:20,966 --> 01:10:22,550
No one. Understand?

1170
01:10:22,635 --> 01:10:26,054
HILL: Which is strange 'cause it's less
than 20 minutes after the assassination.

1171
01:10:26,138 --> 01:10:27,430
Get her out of here.

1172
01:10:27,514 --> 01:10:31,059
HILL: I knew something was crooked
as a dog's hind leg.

1173
01:10:31,644 --> 01:10:35,230
When I read my testimony
in the Warren Report

1174
01:10:35,314 --> 01:10:37,482
it was a total fabrication.

1175
01:10:37,816 --> 01:10:41,986
That's what bothers me, Mr. Garrison.
They've altered my statements.

1176
01:10:42,988 --> 01:10:44,614
MERCER: This one says,

1177
01:10:44,823 --> 01:10:49,535
"Mercer couldn't identify any photograph
as being the man she observed

1178
01:10:49,620 --> 01:10:52,705
"slouched over the wheel
of the green truck. " Not true.

1179
01:10:52,831 --> 01:10:55,500
I recognized him and I told them so.

1180
01:10:56,502 --> 01:10:57,752
Take your time.

1181
01:10:57,836 --> 01:10:58,836
I'm sure.

1182
01:10:58,921 --> 01:11:00,672
MERCER: And the sheriff's report.

1183
01:11:01,131 --> 01:11:02,840
This is really strange.

1184
01:11:03,092 --> 01:11:06,261
MERCER: See that notarized signature?

1185
01:11:06,345 --> 01:11:07,929
That's not mine.

1186
01:11:08,013 --> 01:11:11,599
There wasn't any notary present
during my questioning.

1187
01:11:13,269 --> 01:11:15,853
JIM: Mrs. Mercer, as a former FBl man,

1188
01:11:17,523 --> 01:11:19,774
it's difficult to accept this.

1189
01:11:20,317 --> 01:11:23,611
LOU: Beverly, tell Mr. Garrison
about the Carousel Club.

1190
01:11:23,696 --> 01:11:25,863
[Lounge music]

1191
01:11:29,618 --> 01:11:34,038
I used to go there to see Jack
and my friend, Jatta, who danced there.

1192
01:11:34,331 --> 01:11:36,708
It was a real swinging spot in town.

1193
01:11:36,792 --> 01:11:38,126
Everybody came.

1194
01:11:38,544 --> 01:11:42,046
Businessmen, politicians from Austin,
LBJ's friends...

1195
01:11:42,381 --> 01:11:44,632
Dallas was a slowpokin' town then.

1196
01:11:44,717 --> 01:11:48,636
BEVERLY: You chewed toothpicks,
played dominoes, spit, dated policemen.

1197
01:11:48,721 --> 01:11:52,140
But Jack was exciting.
There were always cops there.

1198
01:11:52,224 --> 01:11:56,185
Jack liked them around, even though
he threw out the drunks himself.

1199
01:11:56,729 --> 01:11:58,146
He had a violent temper.

1200
01:11:59,732 --> 01:12:02,984
Everyone in those days
knew Jack was in the mob.

1201
01:12:03,736 --> 01:12:06,571
Cops back then, they were bad.

1202
01:12:06,864 --> 01:12:09,407
They'd shake you down
for the money in your pocket.

1203
01:12:12,077 --> 01:12:13,661
LOU: What about Lee?

1204
01:12:14,747 --> 01:12:16,080
BEVERLY: One time I came in.

1205
01:12:16,206 --> 01:12:20,585
Jack introduced me to two guys.
He says, "This is my friend, Lee. "

1206
01:12:21,253 --> 01:12:22,837
[Beverly laughs]

1207
01:12:22,921 --> 01:12:25,256
BEVERLY: I don't remember
the other guy's name.

1208
01:12:25,382 --> 01:12:29,218
He was a weird-looking guy.
He had these eyebrows.

1209
01:12:29,845 --> 01:12:32,055
And he looked like a buzzard.

1210
01:12:34,350 --> 01:12:36,934
Lee didn't make much of an impression.

1211
01:12:37,853 --> 01:12:39,896
He wasn't very handsome.

1212
01:12:40,105 --> 01:12:43,816
He didn't look like he had any money,
and he was in a bad mood.

1213
01:12:43,901 --> 01:12:45,943
So, I didn't pay him much mind.

1214
01:12:47,863 --> 01:12:51,407
I may not remember a name,
but I always remember a face.

1215
01:12:52,785 --> 01:12:55,203
Later, when I saw him on television,

1216
01:12:56,622 --> 01:12:59,123
I screamed, "My God, that's him!

1217
01:12:59,458 --> 01:13:01,459
"That's Jack's friend!"

1218
01:13:02,795 --> 01:13:04,796
Will you testify, Beverly?

1219
01:13:06,799 --> 01:13:10,385
BEVERLY: I don't think so.
LOU: I thought we had an agreement.

1220
01:13:12,137 --> 01:13:13,638
[Beverly sighs]

1221
01:13:13,806 --> 01:13:15,723
I don't want to be another statistic.

1222
01:13:15,808 --> 01:13:17,975
LOU: We could call you in.

1223
01:13:18,310 --> 01:13:21,938
If they can kill the President
of the United States,

1224
01:13:23,482 --> 01:13:27,360
you think they'll think twice
about a two-bit showgirl like me?

1225
01:13:33,325 --> 01:13:35,743
I understand the pressure you're under.

1226
01:13:36,495 --> 01:13:38,496
Don't think that I don't.

1227
01:13:39,498 --> 01:13:40,915
We both do.

1228
01:13:46,839 --> 01:13:52,009
RUBY: Mr. Chief Justice, do you
understand I can't tell the truth in Dallas?

1229
01:13:53,470 --> 01:13:56,848
RUBY: There are people here
who do not want me to tell the truth.

1230
01:13:57,015 --> 01:13:59,267
Who don't want me to have a retrial.

1231
01:13:59,810 --> 01:14:01,894
Why don't you just tell us now?

1232
01:14:02,438 --> 01:14:04,105
My life is in danger!

1233
01:14:04,356 --> 01:14:06,941
RUBY: If you request
that I go to Washington.

1234
01:14:07,025 --> 01:14:10,403
That is, if you want to hear
further testimony from me.

1235
01:14:10,487 --> 01:14:12,029
Can you take me with you?

1236
01:14:12,114 --> 01:14:13,948
CHIEF JUSTICE: No. It can't be done.

1237
01:14:14,491 --> 01:14:16,534
There would be no safe place for you.

1238
01:14:16,660 --> 01:14:19,203
We're not law-enforcement officers.

1239
01:14:20,164 --> 01:14:23,291
There's a great deal at stake in this matter.

1240
01:14:24,501 --> 01:14:26,335
If I'm eliminated,

1241
01:14:26,670 --> 01:14:31,174
there won't be any way of knowing
any bit of truth pertaining to my situation.

1242
01:14:32,843 --> 01:14:36,762
Consequently, a whole new form
of government will take over.

1243
01:14:37,639 --> 01:14:41,851
And I won't live to see you
some other time.

1244
01:14:42,394 --> 01:14:44,061
RUBY: I want to tell the truth.

1245
01:14:44,229 --> 01:14:45,396
And then

1246
01:14:45,564 --> 01:14:47,231
leave this world.

1247
01:14:49,526 --> 01:14:53,029
LOU: The Zapruder film establishes
three shots in 5.6 seconds.

1248
01:14:56,492 --> 01:14:57,825
LOU: I'm Oswald.

1249
01:14:58,911 --> 01:15:00,203
Time me.

1250
01:15:01,246 --> 01:15:02,371
JIM: Go.

1251
01:15:07,753 --> 01:15:08,753
LOU: Time?

1252
01:15:08,837 --> 01:15:10,421
JIM: Between six and seven seconds.

1253
01:15:10,589 --> 01:15:12,006
LOU: Without really aiming.

1254
01:15:12,090 --> 01:15:15,927
The second and third shots came
almost right on top of each other.

1255
01:15:16,553 --> 01:15:18,679
It takes a minimum of

1256
01:15:18,764 --> 01:15:21,265
2.3 seconds to recycle this thing.

1257
01:15:21,767 --> 01:15:24,268
LOU: The other problem is,
there was a tree

1258
01:15:24,436 --> 01:15:28,272
blocking the first two shots
when fired in the Zapruder film.

1259
01:15:29,107 --> 01:15:32,777
Didn't Hoover say something
about leaves falling in November?

1260
01:15:33,278 --> 01:15:35,613
LOU: It was Texas live oak, Chief.

1261
01:15:35,948 --> 01:15:38,574
It sheds its leaves in early March.

1262
01:15:38,951 --> 01:15:42,370
Take this Carcano,
world's worst shoulder weapon,

1263
01:15:42,579 --> 01:15:46,916
and try to hit a moving target
at 88 yards through heavy foliage.

1264
01:15:47,709 --> 01:15:48,960
No way.

1265
01:15:51,880 --> 01:15:54,131
FBl tried two sets of tests.

1266
01:15:54,258 --> 01:15:57,593
Not one sharpshooter could match
Oswald's performance.

1267
01:15:57,803 --> 01:15:59,095
Not one.

1268
01:15:59,221 --> 01:16:01,722
Oswald was at best a medium shot.

1269
01:16:02,307 --> 01:16:04,642
The scope was defective on it too.

1270
01:16:04,935 --> 01:16:07,895
This is the whole essence
of the case to me.

1271
01:16:08,105 --> 01:16:10,606
LOU: The guy couldn't do the shooting.

1272
01:16:11,066 --> 01:16:12,483
LOU: Nobody could.

1273
01:16:12,734 --> 01:16:15,361
LOU: They sold this lemon
to the American public.

1274
01:16:17,155 --> 01:16:20,241
The Zapruder film was the proof
they didn't count on.

1275
01:16:21,159 --> 01:16:22,994
We must get hold of it.

1276
01:16:24,288 --> 01:16:27,248
It means we'll have to subpoena Time-Life.

1277
01:16:28,625 --> 01:16:30,334
JIM: Let me ask you something.

1278
01:16:30,669 --> 01:16:33,004
Why not just shoot Kennedy on Houston?

1279
01:16:33,422 --> 01:16:35,006
Plenty of time.

1280
01:16:36,341 --> 01:16:39,343
- He's out in the open.
- I keep asking myself the same thing.

1281
01:16:39,428 --> 01:16:41,846
- Frontal shot.
- Even if you miss him once,

1282
01:16:42,014 --> 01:16:44,265
if he accelerates, you get a second shot.

1283
01:16:44,349 --> 01:16:46,684
LOU: The only reason to get him on Elm

1284
01:16:47,102 --> 01:16:49,854
is you got him in a triangulated crossfire.

1285
01:16:51,023 --> 01:16:53,858
You put a team there down at the fence.

1286
01:16:53,942 --> 01:16:56,694
LOU: Frontal shot. Flat, low trajectory.

1287
01:16:57,154 --> 01:17:00,656
Put a third team down in this building

1288
01:17:00,741 --> 01:17:01,949
on a low floor.

1289
01:17:02,034 --> 01:17:05,202
When Kennedy gets in the kill zone,
it's a turkey shoot.

1290
01:17:08,123 --> 01:17:09,498
How many men?

1291
01:17:11,168 --> 01:17:15,212
One shooter. One spotter on a radio.
Maybe three teams.

1292
01:17:17,507 --> 01:17:20,718
LOU: These are professional riflemen.
Serious people.

1293
01:17:21,970 --> 01:17:23,137
Hunters.

1294
01:17:24,973 --> 01:17:26,223
Patient.

1295
01:17:28,226 --> 01:17:30,478
It takes skill to kill with a rifle.

1296
01:17:33,607 --> 01:17:38,319
That's why no chief executive's
been executed with one in 200 years.

1297
01:17:41,907 --> 01:17:43,199
LOU: Three,

1298
01:17:43,909 --> 01:17:45,034
two,

1299
01:17:46,536 --> 01:17:47,536
one.

1300
01:17:48,205 --> 01:17:49,747
[Tires squeal]

1301
01:17:49,831 --> 01:17:51,123
[Distorted screams]

1302
01:17:51,541 --> 01:17:53,209
[Trigger clicks]

1303
01:17:57,339 --> 01:17:59,340
Main Street's over there.

1304
01:18:00,175 --> 01:18:02,885
Original parade route on the way
to the Trade Mart,

1305
01:18:03,720 --> 01:18:05,096
is too far, right?

1306
01:18:05,180 --> 01:18:06,263
Too far.

1307
01:18:06,390 --> 01:18:10,351
Impossible shot,
so they change the parade route.

1308
01:18:10,686 --> 01:18:13,604
Bring him down here.
Moving at a normal 25 mph.

1309
01:18:13,689 --> 01:18:16,941
They knew the motorcade would have
to slow down to about 10 mph

1310
01:18:17,067 --> 01:18:20,194
to make that turn there.
And that's where they got him.

1311
01:18:27,619 --> 01:18:30,204
Who do you think changed
the parade route?

1312
01:18:30,288 --> 01:18:33,290
Beats me. Secret Service,
city officials, Dallas Police.

1313
01:18:34,126 --> 01:18:36,127
You know who was the mayor at the time?

1314
01:18:36,211 --> 01:18:37,378
LOU: Roy Cabell.

1315
01:18:37,754 --> 01:18:39,880
- Guess who his brother is?
- Who?

1316
01:18:40,757 --> 01:18:42,466
General Charles Cabell.

1317
01:18:42,968 --> 01:18:44,802
Deputy director of the CIA.

1318
01:18:44,886 --> 01:18:48,055
Kennedy fired him in '61
because of the Bay of Pigs fiasco.

1319
01:18:49,307 --> 01:18:52,309
Moved back to the Pentagon
and called Kennedy a traitor.

1320
01:18:52,644 --> 01:18:54,395
When he came to New Orleans

1321
01:18:54,479 --> 01:18:58,566
to address the Foreign Policy
Association, know who introduced him?

1322
01:18:59,276 --> 01:19:00,901
Our friend, Clay Shaw.

1323
01:19:00,986 --> 01:19:02,194
LOU: Didn't the Warren Commission
call him?

1324
01:19:02,821 --> 01:19:04,905
JIM: His boss was the one
on the Commission

1325
01:19:04,990 --> 01:19:07,241
who handled the leads
in the intelligence community.

1326
01:19:07,325 --> 01:19:10,536
LOU: Allen Dulles?
JIM: Head of the CIA since '53.

1327
01:19:11,621 --> 01:19:13,456
Kennedy fired them both.

1328
01:19:14,583 --> 01:19:17,168
Cabell was his Deputy for nine years.

1329
01:19:18,503 --> 01:19:21,422
Talk about the fox investigating
the chicken coop.

1330
01:19:22,966 --> 01:19:25,593
Now, we'll have to subpoena them both.

1331
01:19:26,178 --> 01:19:28,345
[Band plays Dixieland music]

1332
01:19:37,856 --> 01:19:40,357
MOBSTER: Clay Bertrand?
Sure, I know him.

1333
01:19:40,525 --> 01:19:42,109
Comes to the Quarter.

1334
01:19:42,277 --> 01:19:46,197
Who is he? I've been to all the bars.
Nobody wants to talk.

1335
01:19:47,532 --> 01:19:49,658
Why should they talk to you?

1336
01:19:50,702 --> 01:19:54,497
I told your uncle, I never met a lawman
who wasn't a punk.

1337
01:19:58,543 --> 01:20:01,629
A big-shot businessman.
I seen him on the TV news

1338
01:20:01,713 --> 01:20:03,964
with all the other big shots.

1339
01:20:04,299 --> 01:20:06,383
The guy's a fag, you know?

1340
01:20:06,718 --> 01:20:08,344
Goes by another name.

1341
01:20:08,553 --> 01:20:09,970
What name?

1342
01:20:10,806 --> 01:20:11,806
Shaw.

1343
01:20:11,890 --> 01:20:13,307
Clay Shaw.

1344
01:20:13,642 --> 01:20:15,476
Clay Bertrand is Clay Shaw?

1345
01:20:16,228 --> 01:20:18,813
Guy who ran the International Trade Mart?

1346
01:20:19,314 --> 01:20:22,650
What's the mystery?
Everybody down here knows him.

1347
01:20:23,819 --> 01:20:26,237
BILL: Then why does he
call himself Bertrand?

1348
01:20:26,363 --> 01:20:29,031
Who gives a shit what he calls himself?

1349
01:20:29,407 --> 01:20:33,077
Will you give us a little help
on that grand jury thing?

1350
01:20:33,453 --> 01:20:35,329
MOBSTER: I hope so. We could use it.

1351
01:20:36,081 --> 01:20:37,998
SUSIE: Your hunch was right, Boss.

1352
01:20:38,083 --> 01:20:40,000
But it's even spookier than we thought.

1353
01:20:40,085 --> 01:20:44,839
Starting in September '63 on,
two months before the assassination,

1354
01:20:45,090 --> 01:20:48,259
there are sightings of Oswald
all over Dallas.

1355
01:20:48,385 --> 01:20:53,639
Buying ammunition,
getting a telescopic sight fixed.

1356
01:20:53,723 --> 01:20:54,932
Going to rifle ranges.

1357
01:20:55,058 --> 01:20:59,103
Early November,
at a downtown Dallas Lincoln dealership,

1358
01:20:59,229 --> 01:21:02,690
- he tells the salesman...
- Let's take it over for a test drive.

1359
01:21:02,774 --> 01:21:06,777
Despite the fact he has no license,
and doesn't know how to drive,

1360
01:21:07,112 --> 01:21:10,364
he hits the curves like A.J. Foyt
at the Indy 500.

1361
01:21:10,532 --> 01:21:13,784
Beauregard later told his boss
that he drove like a madman.

1362
01:21:13,952 --> 01:21:17,705
$300 down now, Mr. Oswald,
you can drive out of here.

1363
01:21:17,789 --> 01:21:19,915
What? For this heap?

1364
01:21:20,876 --> 01:21:24,879
No honest working man can afford to buy
a car in this goddamn country anymore.

1365
01:21:24,963 --> 01:21:27,256
Maybe I'll go to Russia and buy one.

1366
01:21:27,382 --> 01:21:31,510
Really dumb dialogue like he's trying
to draw attention to himself.

1367
01:21:32,637 --> 01:21:38,309
Salesman remembers him as about 5' 7",
but his draft card says he's actually 5' 11 ".

1368
01:21:38,810 --> 01:21:42,146
Other witnesses see him on several
separate days at different firing ranges.

1369
01:21:43,148 --> 01:21:45,149
One time, November 9,

1370
01:21:45,317 --> 01:21:48,736
he decides to practice
on the next guy's target.

1371
01:21:48,987 --> 01:21:52,948
I didn't pay for a target
just to have you shoot at it!

1372
01:21:53,909 --> 01:21:56,160
I'm sorry, buddy.

1373
01:21:56,995 --> 01:22:00,456
I thought I was shooting
at that son of a bitch Kennedy.

1374
01:22:00,749 --> 01:22:03,834
As subtle as a cockroach
crawling across a white rug.

1375
01:22:04,002 --> 01:22:06,462
Then he shows up at Sylvia Odio's,

1376
01:22:06,838 --> 01:22:10,466
a Cuban lady in Dallas
in the anti-Castro underground.

1377
01:22:10,592 --> 01:22:13,594
The two Cubans introduce him
as Leon Oswald.

1378
01:22:16,014 --> 01:22:18,098
Something about the man bothers her.

1379
01:22:18,183 --> 01:22:21,268
48 hours later, one of the Cubans calls her.

1380
01:22:21,686 --> 01:22:23,729
What did you think
of Leon Oswald last night?

1381
01:22:24,022 --> 01:22:25,439
I don't care about Oswald.

1382
01:22:25,523 --> 01:22:29,068
You know what he said to us?
"Cubans don't have guts, 'cause Kennedy

1383
01:22:29,152 --> 01:22:32,154
"should have been killed
after the Bay of Pigs by a Cuban. "

1384
01:22:32,238 --> 01:22:35,950
SUSIE: It's like he's giving her information
she doesn't even ask for.

1385
01:22:36,034 --> 01:22:38,369
She's scared and doesn't see him again

1386
01:22:38,453 --> 01:22:41,330
till she sees Oswald's picture
in the paper.

1387
01:22:41,665 --> 01:22:43,958
But the Warren Commission
says that Sylvia

1388
01:22:44,042 --> 01:22:47,795
has bad eyesight because
they have Oswald in Mexico

1389
01:22:48,171 --> 01:22:50,547
trying to get back into Cuba.

1390
01:22:51,049 --> 01:22:54,218
The CIA has a camera
outside the Cuban Embassy.

1391
01:22:54,469 --> 01:22:56,220
And they say that this

1392
01:22:57,222 --> 01:22:59,223
is Oswald in Mexico.

1393
01:23:00,809 --> 01:23:03,852
OSER: If this is Oswald,
it must be our third Oswald.

1394
01:23:04,396 --> 01:23:08,565
JIM: The Warren Commission made great
efforts to make him a Communist.

1395
01:23:08,900 --> 01:23:14,113
I think the point of the Mexican episode
was to lay the blame on Fidel Castro.

1396
01:23:15,198 --> 01:23:17,950
If Oswald, or someone purporting
to be Oswald,

1397
01:23:18,034 --> 01:23:21,870
had gotten into Cuba, come back,
and then killed the President,

1398
01:23:22,706 --> 01:23:25,749
the American public would've supported
a Cuban invasion.

1399
01:23:25,834 --> 01:23:28,752
I even have doubts about this photo, Boss.

1400
01:23:29,337 --> 01:23:32,506
This convicted Oswald in the public's mind.

1401
01:23:32,590 --> 01:23:36,635
But Oswald told Capt. Fritz
that the photo was a fake.

1402
01:23:36,720 --> 01:23:38,012
This is not me!

1403
01:23:38,096 --> 01:23:41,682
- That came from Janet Williams' garage.
- I never saw this picture.

1404
01:23:41,766 --> 01:23:46,520
It's my face but it's superimposed.
The rest is not me.

1405
01:23:46,604 --> 01:23:50,274
OSWALD: I know photographic work.
That was made by someone else!

1406
01:23:50,358 --> 01:23:52,526
SUSIE: I took this picture to two experts.

1407
01:23:53,194 --> 01:23:55,612
Look at how the shadows on the nose

1408
01:23:56,072 --> 01:23:58,365
fall in a straight line, like it's high noon.

1409
01:23:58,450 --> 01:24:02,119
SUSIE: The shadow on the ground
reads like late afternoon or early morning.

1410
01:24:02,203 --> 01:24:03,704
It's not the same time.

1411
01:24:03,788 --> 01:24:06,123
And see the crop marks across the chin?

1412
01:24:06,291 --> 01:24:09,084
SUSIE: This head is pasted
onto another body.

1413
01:24:09,419 --> 01:24:11,962
Implicating him with the rifle and the gun.

1414
01:24:12,047 --> 01:24:15,257
CAPT. FRITZ: Who the hell are you?
Alex Hidell or Lee Oswald?

1415
01:24:18,928 --> 01:24:20,888
You're the policeman, you work it out.

1416
01:24:20,972 --> 01:24:23,474
SUSIE: Now it gets positively spooky.

1417
01:24:23,933 --> 01:24:28,812
In January 1961, in New Orleans,
at the Bolton Ford dealership,

1418
01:24:29,105 --> 01:24:31,982
when the Oswald we know is in Russia

1419
01:24:32,317 --> 01:24:35,694
there is a man using the name of Oswald
to buy trucks

1420
01:24:35,820 --> 01:24:37,821
for the Friends of Democratic Cuba.

1421
01:24:37,906 --> 01:24:39,740
SUSIE: Salesman never sees him again.

1422
01:24:39,824 --> 01:24:44,495
But who's on the Articles Of Incorporation
of the Friends of Democratic Cuba?

1423
01:24:45,413 --> 01:24:46,872
Guy Banister.

1424
01:24:47,332 --> 01:24:51,502
SUSIE: Banister has someone using
the name Oswald to buy the trucks.

1425
01:24:52,003 --> 01:24:55,964
Hoover at the FBl has a memo
dated June of 1960

1426
01:24:56,257 --> 01:24:59,843
that someone may be using
Oswald's passport and identity.

1427
01:25:00,136 --> 01:25:02,513
JIM: They created Oswald from day one.

1428
01:25:03,014 --> 01:25:07,267
Like a dummy corporation in the Bahamas.
Just move him around a board.

1429
01:25:07,477 --> 01:25:09,144
Anybody want to quit?

1430
01:25:11,648 --> 01:25:14,149
Dumb question. Put your hands down.

1431
01:25:15,860 --> 01:25:17,736
I found Clay Bertrand.

1432
01:25:18,696 --> 01:25:21,031
Grab your socks and hose and pull.

1433
01:25:21,324 --> 01:25:23,158
Clay Bertrand is Clay Shaw.

1434
01:25:24,119 --> 01:25:27,412
SUSIE: Director of the Trade Mart?
BILL: Former director.

1435
01:25:27,539 --> 01:25:28,956
SUSIE: Incredible.

1436
01:25:29,040 --> 01:25:31,208
Can you get some sworn statements?

1437
01:25:31,459 --> 01:25:33,961
That'll be tough. Nobody's talking.

1438
01:25:35,130 --> 01:25:37,548
JIM: Let's have him in for a chat.

1439
01:25:37,632 --> 01:25:39,716
LIZ: I hate to get him dragged into this.

1440
01:25:39,801 --> 01:25:43,053
He's done so much for the city,
restoring the Quarter.

1441
01:25:43,513 --> 01:25:47,516
Remember, we saw him at a fund-raiser.
Seems like such a nice man.

1442
01:25:47,725 --> 01:25:51,395
It'll be off the record.
I'll bring him in on a Sunday.

1443
01:25:53,231 --> 01:25:55,691
A quiet little chat between gentlemen.

1444
01:25:57,902 --> 01:26:00,028
[March music]

1445
01:26:12,333 --> 01:26:14,126
NEWSMAN: In heavy fighting
in Vietnam today

1446
01:26:14,210 --> 01:26:17,504
seven more American soldiers died
and 23 were wounded.

1447
01:26:17,589 --> 01:26:20,507
The body count for this week
now stands at 67 Americans

1448
01:26:20,592 --> 01:26:23,260
and 626 enemy soldiers killed in action.

1449
01:26:24,220 --> 01:26:28,599
President Johnson said he regretted
there's no end in sight to the war

1450
01:26:28,850 --> 01:26:31,268
where 500,000 US troops
are now fighting.

1451
01:26:31,603 --> 01:26:33,770
LYNDON JOHNSON: We face more cost,

1452
01:26:33,897 --> 01:26:35,230
more loss

1453
01:26:35,773 --> 01:26:37,232
and more agony.

1454
01:26:37,442 --> 01:26:39,776
LIZ: Come hunt for Easter eggs.

1455
01:26:40,069 --> 01:26:44,948
JIM: That's the kids' job. You know
I don't like these tribal rituals, anyway.

1456
01:26:45,200 --> 01:26:47,618
I'm talking to Clay Shaw this morning.

1457
01:26:47,785 --> 01:26:50,287
LIZ: We're going to Antoine's with the kids!

1458
01:26:50,371 --> 01:26:52,539
I told you I was talking to Shaw.

1459
01:26:52,624 --> 01:26:55,334
In the middle of Easter Sunday?

1460
01:26:55,418 --> 01:26:58,045
When I scheduled it,
I didn't know it was a holiday.

1461
01:26:58,129 --> 01:27:00,547
Look at the calendar!

1462
01:27:00,632 --> 01:27:02,799
You said a Sunday, not Easter Sunday.

1463
01:27:03,593 --> 01:27:05,135
Clay Shaw is important.

1464
01:27:05,261 --> 01:27:07,804
LIZ: And we're not.
JIM: I didn't say that.

1465
01:27:08,890 --> 01:27:10,307
I didn't say that.

1466
01:27:11,434 --> 01:27:14,394
You're missing most of your life
and you don't know it.

1467
01:27:14,646 --> 01:27:16,813
LIZ: The kids are missing out, too.

1468
01:27:17,315 --> 01:27:18,732
You're not the only one making sacrifices.

1469
01:27:18,816 --> 01:27:21,652
JIM: I'll be there by 2:00, I promise.

1470
01:27:22,654 --> 01:27:24,321
Just start without me.

1471
01:27:27,158 --> 01:27:30,077
[Dramatic instrumental music]

1472
01:27:33,831 --> 01:27:36,500
CLAY: What can I do for you
on Easter Sunday?

1473
01:27:36,626 --> 01:27:39,086
I'm sorry to interrupt this holiday.

1474
01:27:39,170 --> 01:27:43,507
But this conversation is best kept out
of the everyday bustle of this office.

1475
01:27:43,841 --> 01:27:45,342
I don't understand.

1476
01:27:45,426 --> 01:27:49,513
JIM: In an investigation we're conducting,
your name keeps coming up.

1477
01:27:49,764 --> 01:27:50,764
Can't imagine where.

1478
01:27:51,516 --> 01:27:55,143
JIM: We've talked to a number of men
who claim to know you.

1479
01:27:55,353 --> 01:27:57,187
JIM: Do you know a David Logan?

1480
01:27:57,313 --> 01:27:59,314
CLAY: No. Never heard of him.

1481
01:28:00,191 --> 01:28:01,275
Perry Russo?

1482
01:28:01,359 --> 01:28:02,359
No.

1483
01:28:03,486 --> 01:28:05,028
JIM: Willie O'Keefe?

1484
01:28:05,154 --> 01:28:06,363
[Doorbell rings]

1485
01:28:06,489 --> 01:28:08,991
I don't know anyone by that name.

1486
01:28:09,200 --> 01:28:13,370
Mr. O'Keefe told us he met you
at the Masquerade Bar in the Quarter.

1487
01:28:13,997 --> 01:28:17,874
JIM: Then you had him over for dinner
at your apartment on Dauphine Street.

1488
01:28:17,959 --> 01:28:21,336
JIM: Do you recall that?
CLAY: I don't know this man.

1489
01:28:22,005 --> 01:28:23,505
Be still my heart.

1490
01:28:23,881 --> 01:28:26,300
Obviously, I wouldn't have him over.

1491
01:28:26,384 --> 01:28:28,051
CLAY: Hope you like squab.

1492
01:28:28,303 --> 01:28:29,886
[Clay chuckles]

1493
01:28:30,013 --> 01:28:31,388
CLAY: Champagne?

1494
01:28:31,723 --> 01:28:36,226
JIM: Perhaps a few more details about
the evening will refresh your memory.

1495
01:28:36,519 --> 01:28:37,978
[Bell rings]

1496
01:28:38,229 --> 01:28:40,981
[Soft instrumental music]

1497
01:28:42,358 --> 01:28:47,195
JIM: Mr. O'Keefe told us dinner was served
by a uniformed waiter, a colored man.

1498
01:28:47,739 --> 01:28:52,075
You sat at one end and he at the other,
which he found unusual

1499
01:28:52,577 --> 01:28:54,745
because the table was so long.

1500
01:28:55,204 --> 01:28:56,413
How was your mousse?

1501
01:28:56,581 --> 01:28:58,957
JIM: Bring back memories
of Willie O'Keefe?

1502
01:28:59,042 --> 01:29:00,334
Not at all.

1503
01:29:01,044 --> 01:29:02,669
But I do have

1504
01:29:02,754 --> 01:29:05,339
a lovely Chippendale dining table.

1505
01:29:05,423 --> 01:29:09,092
I often have a friend sit at one end
while I sit at the other.

1506
01:29:09,177 --> 01:29:13,013
It's precisely the point
of a long dining table.

1507
01:29:13,181 --> 01:29:16,183
CLAY: The splendor of the meal
adds to its enjoyment.

1508
01:29:16,267 --> 01:29:18,268
JIM: I imagine a uniformed waiter helps.

1509
01:29:18,394 --> 01:29:20,854
It adds elegance, for which I confess

1510
01:29:21,105 --> 01:29:23,106
a weakness now and then.

1511
01:29:23,441 --> 01:29:24,941
I call him Smedley.

1512
01:29:25,943 --> 01:29:30,238
CLAY: His real name's Frankie Jenkins,
but it would be so uncouth during dinner

1513
01:29:31,032 --> 01:29:33,200
to turn toward the kitchen and holler,

1514
01:29:33,284 --> 01:29:34,534
"Frankie!"

1515
01:29:34,619 --> 01:29:36,119
[Clay laughs]

1516
01:29:39,791 --> 01:29:41,958
Where is all this leading to?

1517
01:29:42,126 --> 01:29:43,877
After dinner, you paid him to have sex.

1518
01:29:45,546 --> 01:29:47,631
[Percussion beat]

1519
01:29:47,799 --> 01:29:49,925
That is absolute nonsense.

1520
01:29:50,635 --> 01:29:54,805
The Quarter is filled
with vivid imaginations, dear Mr. Garrison.

1521
01:29:55,098 --> 01:29:58,392
Grimy young hoodlums who will say
and do anything!

1522
01:29:58,559 --> 01:30:00,477
JIM: Mr. O'Keefe told us

1523
01:30:00,561 --> 01:30:03,814
David Ferrie came to the house
with another young man.

1524
01:30:04,148 --> 01:30:05,816
[Informal greetings exchanged]

1525
01:30:05,942 --> 01:30:07,818
CLAY: Who?
JIM: David Ferrie.

1526
01:30:08,986 --> 01:30:10,570
I don't know that name.

1527
01:30:11,155 --> 01:30:14,741
CLAY: Never having met Mr. O'Keefe,
I couldn't have met Mr. Ferrie.

1528
01:30:26,337 --> 01:30:28,130
[Distorted sound effects]

1529
01:30:28,423 --> 01:30:30,173
FERRIE: You're mine, Mary.

1530
01:30:30,675 --> 01:30:33,677
The four of you partied early
into the morning hours.

1531
01:30:33,970 --> 01:30:35,637
Look at this picture.

1532
01:30:36,472 --> 01:30:39,474
CLAY: I've never met anyone
of such bizarre appearance.

1533
01:30:39,642 --> 01:30:41,810
[March music plays in film]

1534
01:30:48,192 --> 01:30:52,279
FERRIE: Only way you get this,
you do exactly what I say. I'm the man.

1535
01:30:54,031 --> 01:30:56,283
You know the name Clay Bertrand?

1536
01:30:56,492 --> 01:30:57,993
Clay Bertrand.

1537
01:30:58,995 --> 01:31:02,330
A man with a similar name worked
at the Chamber of Commerce.

1538
01:31:02,498 --> 01:31:05,709
CLAY: That the man you had in mind?
JIM: No, it was not.

1539
01:31:06,210 --> 01:31:08,378
JIM: Can you identify this man?

1540
01:31:08,880 --> 01:31:12,924
Naturally. You claim Mr. Oswald
also had dinner with me?

1541
01:31:13,009 --> 01:31:16,136
JIM: Have you ever met
Lee Harvey Oswald?

1542
01:31:16,220 --> 01:31:19,890
You have me consorting
with a sordid cast of characters.

1543
01:31:20,057 --> 01:31:22,851
JIM: Please answer the question.
CLAY: 'Course not.

1544
01:31:23,060 --> 01:31:24,895
The assassination was such a pity.

1545
01:31:24,979 --> 01:31:28,732
In fact I admired Kennedy.
Man of true panache.

1546
01:31:28,816 --> 01:31:30,650
Wife of impeccable taste.

1547
01:31:31,194 --> 01:31:34,446
LIZ: Let's order without your daddy.
He won't mind.

1548
01:31:34,739 --> 01:31:36,573
VIRGINIA: I want a Shirley Temple!

1549
01:31:36,741 --> 01:31:39,075
LIZ: Kids, put your water guns away.

1550
01:31:39,494 --> 01:31:41,077
When's Daddy coming?

1551
01:31:42,079 --> 01:31:43,663
He's coming soon.

1552
01:31:43,873 --> 01:31:47,209
He's sorry he's late,
but he promised he'd be here.

1553
01:31:47,376 --> 01:31:49,920
Daddy never keeps his promises.

1554
01:31:54,175 --> 01:31:56,843
JIM: This Italian newspaper article says

1555
01:31:57,512 --> 01:32:01,264
you were a board member
of Centro Mondo Commerciale in Italy.

1556
01:32:01,432 --> 01:32:05,519
This company was created by the CIA
for the transfer of funds in Italy

1557
01:32:05,603 --> 01:32:08,522
for illegal political-espionage activities.

1558
01:32:08,606 --> 01:32:12,692
JIM: Says that this company was expelled
from Italy for those activities.

1559
01:32:12,777 --> 01:32:14,194
CLAY: I'm well aware
of that asinine article.

1560
01:32:14,278 --> 01:32:17,113
I'm thinking of suing that rag.

1561
01:32:17,198 --> 01:32:21,034
JIM: It also says this company is linked
to the Schlumberger Tool Company

1562
01:32:21,118 --> 01:32:24,913
in Louisiana, which provided arms
to David Ferrie and his Cubans.

1563
01:32:24,997 --> 01:32:26,665
You're reaching.

1564
01:32:26,749 --> 01:32:27,707
JIM: Am I?

1565
01:32:27,792 --> 01:32:31,461
I'm an international businessman.
The Trade Mart I founded

1566
01:32:31,546 --> 01:32:36,258
is America's commercial pipeline
to Latin America. I trade everywhere.

1567
01:32:36,467 --> 01:32:40,220
Like all businessmen,
I am accused of all things.

1568
01:32:40,304 --> 01:32:44,599
CLAY: I go about my business,
make money, help society the best I can

1569
01:32:44,684 --> 01:32:47,310
and try to promote free trade
in this world.

1570
01:32:47,395 --> 01:32:51,690
Have you ever been a contract agent
for the CIA?

1571
01:32:52,441 --> 01:32:53,900
[Clay sighs]

1572
01:32:56,612 --> 01:32:58,154
And if I were

1573
01:32:58,823 --> 01:33:02,409
do you believe I would be here today

1574
01:33:03,327 --> 01:33:05,620
talking to somebody like you?

1575
01:33:11,127 --> 01:33:13,753
JIM: People like you don't have to.
CLAY: May I go?

1576
01:33:13,838 --> 01:33:16,840
People like you walk
between the raindrops.

1577
01:33:17,842 --> 01:33:19,175
[Whispers] May I go?

1578
01:33:21,304 --> 01:33:22,429
JIM: Yes.

1579
01:33:23,681 --> 01:33:25,098
[Rattling]

1580
01:33:30,646 --> 01:33:35,567
CLAY: Regardless of what you may think
of me, I am a patriot first and foremost.

1581
01:33:35,651 --> 01:33:38,028
JIM: I've spent half my life in the military,

1582
01:33:38,154 --> 01:33:39,946
defending my country.

1583
01:33:40,031 --> 01:33:44,284
You're the first person I've met who
considers it patriotic to kill the President.

1584
01:33:44,368 --> 01:33:46,453
You are way out of line.

1585
01:33:46,787 --> 01:33:50,081
It's getting late.
That's all the questions we have.

1586
01:33:50,541 --> 01:33:53,209
Thank you for your honesty
and for coming in.

1587
01:33:53,294 --> 01:33:55,128
I enjoyed meeting with you.

1588
01:33:56,213 --> 01:33:59,215
CLAY: And you, Miss Cox.
It's been most pleasant.

1589
01:34:04,722 --> 01:34:09,434
I extend to you and your families
my best wishes for a happy Easter.

1590
01:34:18,361 --> 01:34:21,363
"One may smile, and smile
and be a villain. "

1591
01:34:22,365 --> 01:34:24,491
Goddamn it! We've got one of them.

1592
01:34:24,575 --> 01:34:25,575
See that?

1593
01:34:42,927 --> 01:34:44,886
JIM: Hi, honey.
LIZ: Hi.

1594
01:34:49,058 --> 01:34:50,183
JIM: Tough day.

1595
01:34:50,351 --> 01:34:51,935
Where you been?

1596
01:34:52,895 --> 01:34:54,354
LIZ: My sympathies.

1597
01:34:54,438 --> 01:34:57,941
JIM: I'm sorry, the meeting took
much longer than expected.

1598
01:34:58,192 --> 01:34:59,693
JIM: Just a second.

1599
01:34:59,777 --> 01:35:02,779
LIZ: We waited for hours, Jim!

1600
01:35:04,115 --> 01:35:06,032
You could've telephoned.

1601
01:35:06,117 --> 01:35:10,745
JIM: I can only say I'm sorry.
I just don't have rabbits on my mind.

1602
01:35:11,706 --> 01:35:13,289
You know what I think?

1603
01:35:13,374 --> 01:35:16,876
You care more about John Kennedy
than your own family.

1604
01:35:16,961 --> 01:35:21,381
All day the kids asked, "Where's Daddy?"
What should I tell them?

1605
01:35:21,799 --> 01:35:23,299
JIM: I don't know!

1606
01:35:23,467 --> 01:35:26,469
The truth! I'm doing my job
to make sure they grow up

1607
01:35:26,595 --> 01:35:30,807
in a country where justice won't be
a vanished idea in history books

1608
01:35:30,891 --> 01:35:33,059
like dinosaurs or Atlantis.

1609
01:35:33,144 --> 01:35:36,104
It doesn't replace a husband
or a father on Easter Sunday.

1610
01:35:36,230 --> 01:35:38,189
It's going to get worse!

1611
01:35:43,821 --> 01:35:46,156
BILL: I beat you again,
you must give me a raise.

1612
01:35:46,282 --> 01:35:48,032
Who can you brag to?

1613
01:35:48,159 --> 01:35:49,784
[Bill chuckles]

1614
01:35:50,786 --> 01:35:54,080
Who killed President Kennedy?
Was there a conspiracy here?

1615
01:35:54,331 --> 01:35:56,416
I don't know what you're talking about.

1616
01:35:56,500 --> 01:35:57,584
[Reporters talk at once]

1617
01:35:57,668 --> 01:36:00,003
Clear the door! Watch out! Move!

1618
01:36:02,923 --> 01:36:05,133
LOU: Congratulations. You're Page One.

1619
01:36:05,342 --> 01:36:10,680
Ain't nice, it says, we've spent over $8,000
on unexplained investigative expenses

1620
01:36:10,806 --> 01:36:12,515
since November, 1966.

1621
01:36:12,683 --> 01:36:14,058
JIM: Goddamn!

1622
01:36:14,143 --> 01:36:18,313
They went to the public records, got
vouchers we requested for withdrawals.

1623
01:36:18,522 --> 01:36:20,398
SUSIE: Shaw got them on our tail.

1624
01:36:20,483 --> 01:36:23,526
It could have been Ferrie,
Martin, Andrews, any of them.

1625
01:36:23,652 --> 01:36:27,447
Or they talked to Ruby 'cause of
they're on our asses for a measly $8,000.

1626
01:36:27,531 --> 01:36:29,699
They're hunting the news,
it's their business.

1627
01:36:29,784 --> 01:36:32,494
You'd think they'd understand
what we're doing.

1628
01:36:32,703 --> 01:36:35,538
Getting angry doesn't accomplish
a damn thing.

1629
01:36:37,541 --> 01:36:38,792
Son of a bitch.

1630
01:36:39,835 --> 01:36:41,961
This changes everything now.

1631
01:36:42,546 --> 01:36:43,880
What do you mean?

1632
01:36:46,383 --> 01:36:50,094
Either we pull out now
or we go through heavy flak together.

1633
01:36:52,848 --> 01:36:56,976
Bear in mind, this may affect
the rest of your careers, your lives.

1634
01:36:58,062 --> 01:37:00,313
Anyone who wants to pull out now

1635
01:37:00,564 --> 01:37:05,985
I assure you there will be no ill feelings
and I will reassign you to regular duties.

1636
01:37:09,406 --> 01:37:11,699
There it is then, thank you.

1637
01:37:12,201 --> 01:37:14,077
It means a great deal to me.

1638
01:37:17,248 --> 01:37:21,084
I'm giving this office $6,000
from my National Guard savings account.

1639
01:37:21,836 --> 01:37:23,586
So we can continue.

1640
01:37:24,046 --> 01:37:27,340
I'll make speeches where I can
and make additional money.

1641
01:37:27,842 --> 01:37:30,844
What shall I tell them?
Their piling up outside the door.

1642
01:37:30,928 --> 01:37:33,680
They want a statement.
The phones are going crazy.

1643
01:37:33,764 --> 01:37:36,766
JIM: I won't confirm, deny nor discuss,
Sharon.

1644
01:37:38,394 --> 01:37:40,353
Goodbye, ladies and gentlemen.

1645
01:37:42,398 --> 01:37:45,191
I'm going home
to get a decent day's work done.

1646
01:37:45,276 --> 01:37:49,195
TV COMMENTATOR: Mr. Garrison's silence
has raised some interesting questions.

1647
01:37:49,280 --> 01:37:52,198
With taxpayer money,
has he uncovered valuable new evidence?

1648
01:37:52,283 --> 01:37:53,324
[Phone rings]

1649
01:37:53,409 --> 01:37:55,451
TV COMMENTATOR: Or is he
merely saving the information

1650
01:37:55,536 --> 01:37:58,371
to gain exposure at a national level?

1651
01:37:58,455 --> 01:38:00,707
Mr. Garrison should have
some explanation.

1652
01:38:00,791 --> 01:38:03,793
FERRIE: Did your office plant
that garbage in the paper?

1653
01:38:03,878 --> 01:38:06,004
LOU: Who is this?
FERRIE: You know damn well.

1654
01:38:06,088 --> 01:38:08,214
LOU: Dave?
FERRIE: You got it. Listen.

1655
01:38:08,299 --> 01:38:10,383
You're the only straight-shooter there.

1656
01:38:10,467 --> 01:38:12,635
FERRIE: I want an answer!
Did you plant it?

1657
01:38:12,720 --> 01:38:16,598
LOU: [On phone] Do you think we're nuts?
It's been a zoo since that broke.

1658
01:38:16,682 --> 01:38:18,725
Reporters everywhere.
Do you think we want that?

1659
01:38:18,809 --> 01:38:21,561
FERRIE: Somebody planted
that fucking story!

1660
01:38:21,645 --> 01:38:25,398
I'm one of fucking Garrison's suspects.
I can't go home!

1661
01:38:25,482 --> 01:38:28,568
FERRIE: The maggots are everywhere!
Do you know what you've done?

1662
01:38:28,652 --> 01:38:29,986
Calm down.

1663
01:38:30,070 --> 01:38:31,237
FERRIE: From here on

1664
