02:05:12,838 --> 02:05:16,174
- In our time, in our country!
- They've done it throughout history.

2133
02:05:16,258 --> 02:05:19,677
Kings are killed. Politics is power,
nothing more!

2134
02:05:20,763 --> 02:05:24,182
Don't take my word for it.
Do your own thinking.

2135
02:05:26,685 --> 02:05:28,269
The size of this is

2136
02:05:29,104 --> 02:05:30,438
beyond me.

2137
02:05:31,148 --> 02:05:32,273
Testify.

2138
02:05:32,608 --> 02:05:34,108
- Me?
- Testify.

2139
02:05:35,444 --> 02:05:37,028
No chance in hell.

2140
02:05:37,780 --> 02:05:42,116
No, I'd be arrested and gagged.
Maybe sent to an institution.

2141
02:05:42,243 --> 02:05:43,618
Maybe worse. You too.

2142
02:05:44,453 --> 02:05:48,540
MR. X: I can give you the background.
You find the foreground, the little things.

2143
02:05:48,707 --> 02:05:52,377
Dig, you're the only one to bring a trial
in Kennedy's murder.

2144
02:05:52,753 --> 02:05:55,463
MR. X: That's important. It's historic.

2145
02:05:55,631 --> 02:05:57,131
I haven't yet.

2146
02:05:57,883 --> 02:06:00,134
I don't have much of a case.

2147
02:06:01,220 --> 02:06:03,304
You don't have a choice anymore.

2148
02:06:03,639 --> 02:06:07,559
MR. X: You're a significant threat
to the national security structure.

2149
02:06:07,643 --> 02:06:10,645
They'd have killed you already,
but there's light on you.

2150
02:06:10,729 --> 02:06:12,897
So they'll destroy your credibility.

2151
02:06:12,982 --> 02:06:14,983
They already have in many circles.

2152
02:06:15,484 --> 02:06:16,985
MR. X: Be honest.

2153
02:06:17,069 --> 02:06:21,322
Your only chance is to come up
with a case. Something. Anything.

2154
02:06:22,032 --> 02:06:24,784
Make arrests. Stir the shitstorm.

2155
02:06:25,244 --> 02:06:27,078
MR. X: Hope to start

2156
02:06:27,162 --> 02:06:29,706
a chain reaction
of people coming forward.

2157
02:06:29,915 --> 02:06:32,000
Then the government will crack.

2158
02:06:32,084 --> 02:06:35,169
Fundamentally, people are suckers
for the truth.

2159
02:06:35,421 --> 02:06:38,006
And the truth is on your side, bubba.

2160
02:06:45,014 --> 02:06:46,472
I just hope you get a break.

2161
02:06:49,852 --> 02:06:52,562
[Dramatic music plays softly]

2162
02:07:32,061 --> 02:07:33,061
LOU: Mr. Shaw?

2163
02:07:33,896 --> 02:07:36,481
You are under arrest for conspiracy

2164
02:07:36,565 --> 02:07:40,902
and entering into agreement with others
for the purpose of murdering

2165
02:07:41,070 --> 02:07:42,945
President John F. Kennedy.

2166
02:07:43,030 --> 02:07:45,573
We have a warrant to search the premises.

2167
02:07:45,908 --> 02:07:47,492
LOU: It's my duty to inform you

2168
02:07:47,576 --> 02:07:48,618
[Camera clicks]

2169
02:07:48,702 --> 02:07:51,079
you have the right to remain silent.

2170
02:07:51,246 --> 02:07:52,747
OFFICER HABIGHORST: Name?

2171
02:07:52,831 --> 02:07:54,499
Clay LaVerne Shaw.

2172
02:07:56,960 --> 02:07:58,086
HABIGHORST: Address?

2173
02:07:58,170 --> 02:08:01,089
1313 Dauphine Street, New Orleans.

2174
02:08:02,424 --> 02:08:04,509
HABIGHORST: Ever use any aliases?

2175
02:08:04,593 --> 02:08:06,135
Clay Bertrand.

2176
02:08:07,930 --> 02:08:10,181
[Reporters all talk at once]

2177
02:08:12,518 --> 02:08:16,688
REPORTER 1: Mr. Clark, are you aware
of the charges filed by DA Garrison?

2178
02:08:16,772 --> 02:08:20,316
ATTORNEY GENERAL: Yes, Mr. Shaw was
included in our investigation.

2179
02:08:20,401 --> 02:08:22,694
No connection was found at all.

2180
02:08:23,445 --> 02:08:26,948
JIM: If the FBl did investigate him,
why is his name not mentioned

2181
02:08:27,032 --> 02:08:29,826
in the entire 26 volumes
of the Warren Report

2182
02:08:29,910 --> 02:08:32,245
even if it is to clear his name?

2183
02:08:32,955 --> 02:08:36,666
I doubt this Attorney General
would qualify for my staff.

2184
02:08:37,042 --> 02:08:40,962
CHIEF JUSTICE: Mr. Garrison has
presented absolutely nothing publicly

2185
02:08:41,046 --> 02:08:43,589
which would contradict our findings.

2186
02:08:44,216 --> 02:08:47,677
I know of no fact which would refute

2187
02:08:48,053 --> 02:08:50,138
the Commission's conclusion

2188
02:08:50,389 --> 02:08:53,391
that Lee Oswald was the lone killer.

2189
02:08:55,686 --> 02:08:59,480
I congratulate Mr. Shaw.
Most defendants must wait for trial

2190
02:08:59,565 --> 02:09:03,401
before they produce sacred cows
like a Chief Justice

2191
02:09:03,485 --> 02:09:04,944
as a character witness,

2192
02:09:05,028 --> 02:09:08,364
who is not under oath
and therefore free from perjury.

2193
02:09:08,741 --> 02:09:11,159
REPORTER: Even if it's partly true,

2194
02:09:11,243 --> 02:09:15,371
you realize you're damaging
the credibility of the country?

2195
02:09:15,456 --> 02:09:19,709
Is a government worth preserving
when it lies to the people?

2196
02:09:20,836 --> 02:09:23,004
It's become a dangerous country

2197
02:09:23,088 --> 02:09:26,883
when you cannot trust anyone.
When you cannot tell the truth.

2198
02:09:28,093 --> 02:09:31,429
I say let justice be done,
though the heavens fall!

2199
02:09:31,513 --> 02:09:33,765
[Reporters all talk at once]

2200
02:09:37,561 --> 02:09:40,938
TV ANNOUNCER: The JFK Conspiracy:
The Case of Jim Garrison.

2201
02:09:41,440 --> 02:09:42,648
LIZ: This is about you.

2202
02:09:42,733 --> 02:09:45,276
STONER: [On TV] After an investigation
in New Orleans

2203
02:09:45,360 --> 02:09:46,986
reporters have learned

2204
02:09:47,070 --> 02:09:50,156
that District Attorney Jim Garrison
and his staff

2205
02:09:50,449 --> 02:09:54,160
have intimidated,
bribed and even drugged witnesses

2206
02:09:54,244 --> 02:09:59,290
to attempt to prove a conspiracy
involving businessman Clay Shaw

2207
02:09:59,750 --> 02:10:02,293
in the murder of John F. Kennedy.

2208
02:10:02,586 --> 02:10:07,048
John Chancler was a cellmate
of Willie O'Keefe's at Angola.

2209
02:10:07,132 --> 02:10:10,593
He said he'd be cut loose
if he copped to the DA's office.

2210
02:10:10,761 --> 02:10:12,929
JIM: I sent him up for burglary.

2211
02:10:13,972 --> 02:10:16,307
And there's his old buddy Miguel Torres.

2212
02:10:16,767 --> 02:10:18,392
JIM: We sent him up too.

2213
02:10:18,477 --> 02:10:22,730
They wanted me to say Shaw
was Bertrand. They'd get me a pardon.

2214
02:10:22,940 --> 02:10:26,067
STONER: Janet Williams comments
on Willie O'Keefe's

2215
02:10:26,151 --> 02:10:28,653
descriptions of having met Oswald.

2216
02:10:28,821 --> 02:10:30,488
REPORTER: Was he a homosexuaI?

2217
02:10:30,572 --> 02:10:33,074
JANET: Not the Lee I knew.
Absolutely not.

2218
02:10:33,450 --> 02:10:36,994
Mr. O'Keefe must have seen someone
he thought was Lee Oswald.

2219
02:10:37,162 --> 02:10:40,832
ANDREWS: I didn't talk to nobody.
I was on drugs at the hospital.

2220
02:10:41,458 --> 02:10:45,211
I told the FBl that call was a figment
of my imagination.

2221
02:10:45,379 --> 02:10:47,588
CLAY: I think he's quite ill, mentally.

2222
02:10:47,798 --> 02:10:51,801
With one half of his mind,
he is able to fabricate evidence

2223
02:10:52,511 --> 02:10:56,848
then he convinces the other half
that the fabrication is the truth.

2224
02:10:57,266 --> 02:11:01,561
Don't worry. There's only 20
or 30 million people watching this tonight.

2225
02:11:03,939 --> 02:11:07,316
My reputation's all right
with the people watching Laugh In.

2226
02:11:07,401 --> 02:11:10,194
STONER: Has he ignored the Mafia
connections to this conspiracy

2227
02:11:10,279 --> 02:11:13,406
because he's indebted to the mob?

2228
02:11:13,490 --> 02:11:16,951
The more one looks at Jim Garrison,
the more one finds

2229
02:11:17,119 --> 02:11:22,206
he has destroyed reputations, spread fear
and suspicion, and worst of all,

2230
02:11:22,416 --> 02:11:25,459
exploited this nation's sorrow and doubt.

2231
02:11:25,711 --> 02:11:27,628
Jim Garrison has said,

2232
02:11:28,839 --> 02:11:32,008
"Let justice be done,
though the heavens fall. "

2233
02:11:32,175 --> 02:11:34,510
He seeks the truth. So do we.

2234
02:11:34,803 --> 02:11:37,805
[Melancholic instrumental music]

2235
02:11:46,857 --> 02:11:49,400
REPORTER: [On TV]
Dr. Martin Luther King's beautiful dream

2236
02:11:49,484 --> 02:11:50,484
expressed so dramatically

2237
02:11:50,569 --> 02:11:53,195
during the 1963 march on Washington,

2238
02:11:53,280 --> 02:11:56,699
was shattered tonight in Memphis,
Tennessee by an assassin's bullet.

2239
02:11:56,783 --> 02:11:59,994
Police think the single shot came
from across the street.

2240
02:12:00,203 --> 02:12:04,457
They found a Browning automatic rifle,
fitted with a marksman's scope.

2241
02:12:04,541 --> 02:12:05,833
[Phone rings]

2242
02:12:05,918 --> 02:12:07,543
VIRGINIA: I'll get it.

2243
02:12:10,047 --> 02:12:13,633
BEAUTY CONTEST MAN: [On phone]
Hello, is this Jim Garrison's daughter?

2244
02:12:13,717 --> 02:12:15,635
Virginia or Elizabeth?

2245
02:12:17,054 --> 02:12:19,430
Virginia, you're a lucky little girl.

2246
02:12:19,514 --> 02:12:23,684
Your daddy's entered you
in a beauty contest. Like to be in one?

2247
02:12:24,770 --> 02:12:26,062
VIRGINIA: I don't know.

2248
02:12:26,146 --> 02:12:28,940
My God! What have they done?

2249
02:12:29,691 --> 02:12:31,525
MATTIE: It's lynching time.

2250
02:12:34,071 --> 02:12:35,863
VIRGINIA: That sounds fun.

2251
02:12:36,156 --> 02:12:38,532
BEAUTY CONTEST MAN:
You get out of school at 3:00?

2252
02:12:38,617 --> 02:12:39,867
Who are you talking to?

2253
02:12:39,952 --> 02:12:42,203
BEAUTY CONTEST MAN:
That's all I need to know.

2254
02:12:42,287 --> 02:12:44,997
VIRGINIA: Mommy,
I'm going to be in a beauty contest.

2255
02:12:45,415 --> 02:12:47,458
Who is this? Who is this?

2256
02:12:47,626 --> 02:12:49,043
[Dial tone]

2257
02:12:50,087 --> 02:12:52,880
LIZ: Did you enter Virginia
in a beauty contest?

2258
02:12:52,965 --> 02:12:55,716
A man called and asked her height,
her weight...

2259
02:12:55,801 --> 02:12:58,594
Some crackpot.
Martin Luther King was killed.

2260
02:12:58,679 --> 02:13:00,721
Her life's been threatened!

2261
02:13:00,806 --> 02:13:03,933
A crank making calls.
Happens a dozen times a day at the office.

2262
02:13:04,017 --> 02:13:06,644
Our home! A kidnapper, a murderer!

2263
02:13:06,728 --> 02:13:08,813
Only cowards make crank calls.

2264
02:13:08,897 --> 02:13:10,398
Nothing will happen.

2265
02:13:10,816 --> 02:13:15,403
LIZ: You don't know what goes on here
anymore! You're busy making speeches!

2266
02:13:15,737 --> 02:13:18,489
Getting every crazed Klansman after us!

2267
02:13:18,573 --> 02:13:23,244
I'm taking the kids and I'm leaving!
I can't stand it anymore!

2268
02:13:23,328 --> 02:13:25,913
- The government wants us scared.
- You and your government!

2269
02:13:25,998 --> 02:13:29,917
They want everybody too scared
to speak out. They count on it.

2270
02:13:30,002 --> 02:13:33,004
- There's nothing to fear!
- Don't you have feelings?

2271
02:13:34,840 --> 02:13:36,590
LIZ: Your own daughter!

2272
02:13:37,009 --> 02:13:39,135
LIZ: What kind of a man are you?

2273
02:13:42,514 --> 02:13:46,600
I'll take them to my mother's.
You spend a week.

2274
02:13:46,810 --> 02:13:49,603
I'll change the locks, the phones.
I'll get a bodyguard.

2275
02:13:49,688 --> 02:13:51,689
Get a hold of yourself!

2276
02:13:52,024 --> 02:13:55,651
Before this Kennedy thing,
your children mattered most.

2277
02:13:56,028 --> 02:13:58,988
The other night you didn't
even notice Jasper.

2278
02:13:59,072 --> 02:14:01,073
He came to me bawling his eyes out.

2279
02:14:01,158 --> 02:14:04,577
I promise I'll make more time for Jasper.

2280
02:14:04,661 --> 02:14:06,412
Is it such a chore?

2281
02:14:06,496 --> 02:14:10,708
Goddamn it! If I said I'll spend
more time with him, I will!

2282
02:14:11,001 --> 02:14:13,127
I cannot fight you and the whole world too!

2283
02:14:13,211 --> 02:14:15,963
I'm not fighting you!
I'm trying to reach you.

2284
02:14:16,548 --> 02:14:19,383
- You've changed.
- Of course I've changed!

2285
02:14:20,135 --> 02:14:21,927
My eyes have opened.

2286
02:14:22,220 --> 02:14:25,139
And what once looked normal
seems insane.

2287
02:14:25,223 --> 02:14:28,684
And now King. Don't you think
this has something to do with that?

2288
02:14:28,894 --> 02:14:30,019
Can't you see?

2289
02:14:30,103 --> 02:14:34,065
LIZ: I don't want to see, goddamn it!
I'm tired. I've had enough!

2290
02:14:34,733 --> 02:14:38,611
You're ruining this man Shaw's life
because he's a homosexual.

2291
02:14:38,695 --> 02:14:40,362
That's not why!

2292
02:14:40,655 --> 02:14:43,949
LIZ: Did you ever once stop
to consider his feelings?

2293
02:14:44,034 --> 02:14:45,409
[Liz sobs]

2294
02:14:46,119 --> 02:14:47,745
You don't believe me?

2295
02:14:48,205 --> 02:14:50,998
LIZ: I don't know!
JIM: You never believed me?

2296
02:14:52,084 --> 02:14:55,836
I just want to raise our children
and live a normal life.

2297
02:14:55,962 --> 02:14:57,963
LIZ: I want my life back!

2298
02:14:58,882 --> 02:15:00,716
So do I, goddamn it!

2299
02:15:01,301 --> 02:15:03,344
I had a life too, you know!

2300
02:15:03,720 --> 02:15:07,515
You can't bury your head in the sand
like an ostrich, Liz!

2301
02:15:07,766 --> 02:15:12,436
It's not about our well-being, our two cars,
our TVs and your kitchen!

2302
02:15:14,231 --> 02:15:17,483
It's about our kids growing up
in a shithole of lies. I'm angry!

2303
02:15:17,567 --> 02:15:19,693
My life is fucked because of it.

2304
02:15:19,986 --> 02:15:23,155
If you could see it that way,
you'd see your life is fucked too.

2305
02:15:23,240 --> 02:15:24,990
You never talked to me this way.

2306
02:15:25,075 --> 02:15:27,201
If you don't want to support me, fine.

2307
02:15:27,285 --> 02:15:30,204
But don't make threats
about taking the children.

2308
02:15:30,288 --> 02:15:31,664
LIZ: I'm leaving you!

2309
02:15:31,957 --> 02:15:34,500
LIZ: I'm taking the children!
JIM: Go on! Get out!

2310
02:15:34,584 --> 02:15:36,127
LIZ: I am!
JIM: Go hide!

2311
02:15:36,211 --> 02:15:38,420
JIM: Join the rest! They'll say I'm crazy.

2312
02:15:38,505 --> 02:15:41,298
Plenty of people will tell you I'm crazy.

2313
02:15:42,884 --> 02:15:46,262
You won't have any problems
filling out divorce papers.

2314
02:15:47,305 --> 02:15:49,807
But somebody's got to try, goddamn it!

2315
02:15:50,100 --> 02:15:51,433
Somebody!

2316
02:15:55,647 --> 02:15:57,731
Are we going away, Daddy?

2317
02:16:05,115 --> 02:16:06,907
JIM: I don't know, Jasper.

2318
02:16:07,659 --> 02:16:09,076
JASPER: Because of Kennedy?

2319
02:16:09,786 --> 02:16:12,371
Will the same people kill us, Papa?

2320
02:16:15,125 --> 02:16:16,959
JIM: Nobody will kill us.

2321
02:16:17,627 --> 02:16:19,128
JASPER: I'm scared.

2322
02:16:20,005 --> 02:16:23,257
VIRGINIA: I don't like it
when you and Mommy fight.

2323
02:16:25,802 --> 02:16:28,012
JIM: I don't like it either, honey.

2324
02:16:28,930 --> 02:16:31,098
VIRGINIA: Why do we have to leave?

2325
02:16:31,683 --> 02:16:33,809
Don't you love us anymore?

2326
02:16:36,646 --> 02:16:38,522
Daddy loves you both.

2327
02:16:40,192 --> 02:16:43,569
There's nothing wrong
with feeling a little scared, Jasper.

2328
02:16:43,820 --> 02:16:47,114
Telling the truth can be
a scary thing sometimes.

2329
02:16:47,991 --> 02:16:51,160
It scared President Kennedy,
and he was a brave man.

2330
02:16:51,995 --> 02:16:54,663
But if you let yourself be too scared

2331
02:16:54,873 --> 02:16:58,000
then you let the bad guys
take over the country.

2332
02:16:59,586 --> 02:17:01,587
Then everybody gets scared.

2333
02:17:02,505 --> 02:17:04,131
Stay with Mom, Papa.

2334
02:17:04,341 --> 02:17:05,591
Please.

2335
02:17:13,266 --> 02:17:14,642
OSER: Here's another.

2336
02:17:14,726 --> 02:17:18,103
The US Attorney in Washington declines
to serve our subpoena

2337
02:17:18,188 --> 02:17:22,566
on Allen Dulles, Charles Cabell,
CIA Director Richard Helms, any FBl agent.

2338
02:17:22,692 --> 02:17:25,361
JIM: What'd you expect from a pig
but a grunt?

2339
02:17:25,570 --> 02:17:29,865
OSER: Now it'll be near impossible
to prove Shaw's connection to the CIA.

2340
02:17:30,033 --> 02:17:31,408
What's going on?

2341
02:17:31,576 --> 02:17:34,995
We've never been refused
an extradition request.

2342
02:17:35,080 --> 02:17:37,164
OSER: Let's get Julia Ann Mercer in here.

2343
02:17:37,249 --> 02:17:39,124
JIM: No, she could get hurt.

2344
02:17:39,834 --> 02:17:41,835
Look what's happening to other people.

2345
02:17:41,920 --> 02:17:43,837
She's the best witness we have.

2346
02:17:43,922 --> 02:17:47,007
I just don't want to do it. Now, what else?

2347
02:17:48,301 --> 02:17:52,137
NUMA: You got your hate mail here.
And your fan mail here.

2348
02:17:52,973 --> 02:17:57,851
The bad news is that the IRS requested
an audit of your income from this office.

2349
02:17:58,561 --> 02:18:02,398
I expected that two months ago.
They're wasting their time.

2350
02:18:05,235 --> 02:18:09,405
The bad news is the National Guard
just asked me to resign after 18 years.

2351
02:18:10,615 --> 02:18:14,285
Maybe that's the good news.
Never was as good as combat.

2352
02:18:15,453 --> 02:18:16,495
But this is.

2353
02:18:16,955 --> 02:18:17,955
[All chuckle]

2354
02:18:18,081 --> 02:18:19,873
Any more on Oswald or Shaw?

2355
02:18:20,041 --> 02:18:24,545
They were seen together in Clinton
in early September.

2356
02:18:25,046 --> 02:18:28,841
The Civil Rights Movement
was running a voter's registration drive.

2357
02:18:29,259 --> 02:18:32,970
Rumor is, Shaw was working
on some arms deal

2358
02:18:33,054 --> 02:18:35,472
to discredit the Civil Rights Movement.

2359
02:18:35,557 --> 02:18:38,684
Nobody really knows
what they were doing there, but

2360
02:18:38,768 --> 02:18:40,936
hell, they stood out like cotton balls.

2361
02:18:41,021 --> 02:18:43,731
I got whites and coloreds
that saw them there.

2362
02:18:43,815 --> 02:18:47,276
Last time I checked,
it was not illegal to register to vote.

2363
02:18:48,194 --> 02:18:49,903
BILL: We still got the

2364
02:18:50,238 --> 02:18:54,742
the junkie, Vernon Bundy,
who saw him talking at the sea wall.

2365
02:18:55,368 --> 02:18:58,120
This is tough.
No one wants to talk about Shaw.

2366
02:18:58,455 --> 02:18:59,997
You keep saying that.

2367
02:19:00,582 --> 02:19:02,833
- I keep saying what?
- You're not digging deep enough.

2368
02:19:02,917 --> 02:19:06,003
You want to do my job!
You do my job, I'll do your job.

2369
02:19:06,087 --> 02:19:08,964
JIM: I think Clinton is a breakthrough now.

2370
02:19:10,050 --> 02:19:12,426
Shaw denies ever knowing Oswald, right?

2371
02:19:13,595 --> 02:19:15,304
That proves he's a liar.

2372
02:19:17,265 --> 02:19:19,266
- Keep on it, Bill.
- This is the interesting part.

2373
02:19:19,809 --> 02:19:22,144
Oswald went to see the FBl two weeks

2374
02:19:22,395 --> 02:19:23,896
before the assassination.

2375
02:19:23,980 --> 02:19:25,856
OSWALD: May I see Special Agent Hosty?

2376
02:19:25,940 --> 02:19:27,858
FBl RECEPTIONIST: He's not in.
Can someone else help you?

2377
02:19:27,942 --> 02:19:32,237
SUSIE: Special Agent Hosty made
three visits to Janet Williams' house

2378
02:19:32,322 --> 02:19:34,990
to keep an eye on Marina. He left a note.

2379
02:19:35,075 --> 02:19:38,077
Hosty told a newspaperman
it was a warning

2380
02:19:38,328 --> 02:19:42,039
to stop questioning Marina
when Oswald was not present.

2381
02:19:42,123 --> 02:19:46,794
She was not a citizen, so possibly
he was threatening to deport her to Russia.

2382
02:19:47,379 --> 02:19:49,546
But what the note really said,
no one knows.

2383
02:19:50,090 --> 02:19:52,716
SUSIE: Hosty tore it up and flushed it
down the toilet.

2384
02:19:52,801 --> 02:19:54,426
JIM: This is just speculation.

2385
02:19:54,594 --> 02:19:58,722
But what if the note described
the assassination attempt on JFK?

2386
02:20:04,979 --> 02:20:06,605
Come on, think!

2387
02:20:06,940 --> 02:20:09,274
That's the only reason to destroy it.

2388
02:20:09,609 --> 02:20:13,529
If it was a threat like Hosty said,
they would have kept it.

2389
02:20:13,988 --> 02:20:17,783
It makes their case against the angry,
lone nut that much stronger.

2390
02:20:18,701 --> 02:20:20,494
JIM: Remember the meeting
with Agent Quigley

2391
02:20:20,578 --> 02:20:22,079
the day he was arrested?

2392
02:20:22,163 --> 02:20:24,998
Quigley destroyed the notes
from the interview.

2393
02:20:25,291 --> 02:20:29,336
We can raise the possibility
that Oswald was not only an informant

2394
02:20:29,921 --> 02:20:34,800
but he may have been the original source
for the telex dated November 17

2395
02:20:35,301 --> 02:20:39,388
warning of Kennedy's assassination
in Dallas on November 22.

2396
02:20:41,808 --> 02:20:46,353
JIM: William Walter, the FBl night clerk,
gave me a copy.

2397
02:20:46,438 --> 02:20:49,064
It went all over the country.
Nothing was done.

2398
02:20:49,149 --> 02:20:52,693
The motorcade went ahead on schedule.
The Warren Report didn't mention it.

2399
02:20:52,777 --> 02:20:57,281
OSER: "A militant group may attempt
to assassinate President Kennedy

2400
02:20:57,365 --> 02:20:59,324
"on his proposed trip to Dallas, Texas. "

2401
02:20:59,701 --> 02:21:01,285
JIM: Shortly after the assassination

2402
02:21:01,369 --> 02:21:05,664
Walter says the telex was removed
from all the files

2403
02:21:05,748 --> 02:21:08,542
as an obvious embarrassment
to the Bureau.

2404
02:21:09,711 --> 02:21:12,212
I believe Oswald sent information
through Hosty.

2405
02:21:12,630 --> 02:21:16,341
JIM: I have a hunch Oswald
had infiltrated this group:

2406
02:21:16,509 --> 02:21:18,677
Cubans or right-wing extremists.

2407
02:21:19,471 --> 02:21:22,931
He was told to be
at the Book Depository that day

2408
02:21:23,308 --> 02:21:26,435
to either prevent the assassination
or take part in it.

2409
02:21:26,811 --> 02:21:30,314
JIM: Either they told him
they'd close down the plotters

2410
02:21:31,316 --> 02:21:32,774
or simulate an attack

2411
02:21:32,859 --> 02:21:35,235
on Kennedy to whip up public opinion

2412
02:21:35,320 --> 02:21:38,822
so Kennedy would have to reverse
his policies on communism.

2413
02:21:39,324 --> 02:21:41,742
JIM: What they told him doesn't matter.

2414
02:21:42,035 --> 02:21:43,535
He was under orders.

2415
02:21:43,620 --> 02:21:45,496
He was a foot soldier.

2416
02:21:48,041 --> 02:21:51,001
You can't miss. He is a dead duck.

2417
02:21:52,045 --> 02:21:53,337
BILL: I don't buy it.

2418
02:21:53,796 --> 02:21:55,756
Why would the FBl cover it up?

2419
02:21:56,049 --> 02:21:59,760
A telex disappears from every FBl office
in this country?

2420
02:22:00,345 --> 02:22:01,970
JIM: There's a word, Bill.

2421
02:22:02,055 --> 02:22:04,223
JIM: Orders.
SUSIE: Or a cover-up.

2422
02:22:05,099 --> 02:22:08,101
Don't you have enough proof
of the FBl's complicity yet?

2423
02:22:08,228 --> 02:22:10,562
I respect this country's institutions!

2424
02:22:12,815 --> 02:22:15,692
How the hell can you keep
a conspiracy going

2425
02:22:15,777 --> 02:22:21,281
between the mob, CIA, FBl, Army
intelligence and who knows what else,

2426
02:22:21,366 --> 02:22:25,244
when you can't keep a secret
in this room between 12 people?

2427
02:22:25,453 --> 02:22:27,454
I mean, we got leaks everywhere.

2428
02:22:27,539 --> 02:22:30,332
We are going to trial, y'all!

2429
02:22:30,416 --> 02:22:32,584
What the hell do we really got?

2430
02:22:32,835 --> 02:22:35,921
Oswald, Ruby, Banister,
and Ferrie are dead.

2431
02:22:36,464 --> 02:22:39,258
Maybe Shaw is an agent. I don't know.

2432
02:22:39,384 --> 02:22:41,218
But as a covert operator

2433
02:22:41,302 --> 02:22:44,429
he is wide open for blackmail
because of his homosexuality.

2434
02:22:44,514 --> 02:22:48,642
JIM: Shaw's our toehold.
I don't know or care exactly how he fits.

2435
02:22:49,310 --> 02:22:51,979
JIM: But he's lying through his teeth.
I won't let go of him.

2436
02:22:52,063 --> 02:22:55,190
That's why you're going to trial
against Clay Shaw?

2437
02:22:55,275 --> 02:22:56,817
You will lose!

2438
02:22:57,110 --> 02:22:59,987
BILL: We should investigate
our Mafia leads here.

2439
02:23:00,071 --> 02:23:03,282
I can buy that easier
than I can the government.

2440
02:23:04,576 --> 02:23:08,161
BILL: Ruby is all mob,
knows Oswald, sets him up.

2441
02:23:08,746 --> 02:23:12,749
Hoffa, Trafficante, Marcello,
they hire some guns and do Kennedy.

2442
02:23:13,084 --> 02:23:16,336
The government doesn't want
to open up a whole can of worms

2443
02:23:16,421 --> 02:23:19,673
because it used the mob
to try to get Castro.

2444
02:23:20,383 --> 02:23:23,885
Castro being assassinated
by the mob by us

2445
02:23:23,970 --> 02:23:25,971
sounds wild to John Q. Citizen.

2446
02:23:26,055 --> 02:23:28,599
So they close the book on JFK.

2447
02:23:30,101 --> 02:23:31,602
Makes perfect sense to me.

2448
02:23:31,686 --> 02:23:34,688
I don't doubt their involvement
at a low level.

2449
02:23:35,481 --> 02:23:37,858
Could the mob change the parade route?

2450
02:23:38,234 --> 02:23:41,194
JIM: Or eliminate the protection
for the President?

2451
02:23:41,362 --> 02:23:44,698
Could the mob send Oswald to Russia
and get him back?

2452
02:23:44,866 --> 02:23:48,994
Get the FBl, the CIA and the Dallas Police
to mess up the investigation?

2453
02:23:49,078 --> 02:23:52,414
Get the Warren Commission appointed
to cover it up?

2454
02:23:53,458 --> 02:23:57,753
Wreck the autopsy? Influence
the national media to go to sleep?

2455
02:23:58,046 --> 02:24:01,548
Since when has the mob used anything
but. 38's for hits up close?

2456
02:24:03,384 --> 02:24:07,679
The mob wouldn't have the guts or
the power for something of this magnitude.

2457
02:24:07,805 --> 02:24:09,848
Assassins need payrolls,

2458
02:24:10,391 --> 02:24:12,476
schedules, times, orders.

2459
02:24:13,394 --> 02:24:16,104
This was a military-style ambush.

2460
02:24:16,189 --> 02:24:19,691
A coup d'tat with Lyndon Johnson
waiting in the wings.

2461
02:24:19,984 --> 02:24:23,779
You're saying Lyndon Johnson
was involved? The President?

2462
02:24:24,322 --> 02:24:27,783
Johnson got $1 billion for his friends,
Brown and Root

2463
02:24:27,867 --> 02:24:30,202
to dredge Cam Ranh Bay in Vietnam.

2464
02:24:30,453 --> 02:24:33,664
Boss, are you calling the President
a murderer?

2465
02:24:33,831 --> 02:24:37,501
If I'm so far from the truth,
why is the FBl bugging our offices?

2466
02:24:37,585 --> 02:24:40,128
Why are witnesses being bought off
and murdered?

2467
02:24:40,546 --> 02:24:44,174
Why are federal agencies blocking
our extraditions and subpoenas?

2468
02:24:44,342 --> 02:24:46,259
[Stammers] I don't know.

2469
02:24:46,344 --> 02:24:49,262
Maybe there's some rogue element
in the government.

2470
02:24:49,347 --> 02:24:51,515
JIM: With a full-blown cover-up?

2471
02:24:52,892 --> 02:24:54,893
You ever read Shakespeare?

2472
02:24:56,187 --> 02:24:57,354
Yeah.

2473
02:24:57,605 --> 02:24:58,772
I do.

2474
02:24:59,440 --> 02:25:00,941
JIM: Julius Caesar?

2475
02:25:01,693 --> 02:25:04,986
"Brutus and Cassius,
they too are honorable men. "

2476
02:25:05,738 --> 02:25:07,406
Who killed Caesar?

2477
02:25:08,199 --> 02:25:10,200
Ten or twelve Senators.

2478
02:25:10,410 --> 02:25:12,703
All it takes is one Judas.

2479
02:25:13,246 --> 02:25:16,581
JIM: A few people on the inside.
Pentagon, CIA.

2480
02:25:16,666 --> 02:25:18,458
This is Louisiana.

2481
02:25:18,918 --> 02:25:23,296
How do you know who your daddy is?
'Cause your mama told you so.

2482
02:25:24,424 --> 02:25:26,883
BILL: You are taking a crap in the wind.

2483
02:25:27,135 --> 02:25:30,053
And I am not going along on this one.

2484
02:25:31,013 --> 02:25:32,305
[Banging]

2485
02:25:40,064 --> 02:25:42,899
I've had my doubts all along about Bill.

2486
02:25:43,443 --> 02:25:45,360
He's been fighting us.

2487
02:25:46,863 --> 02:25:48,238
We need him back.

2488
02:25:48,448 --> 02:25:50,824
OSER: He wasted a month
trying to prove

2489
02:25:50,908 --> 02:25:54,661
that mob boys like Jack Ruby
are hooked up with Hunt Oil.

2490
02:25:54,871 --> 02:25:57,038
LOU: I don't trust him.
JIM: I will not hear this.

2491
02:25:57,123 --> 02:26:00,000
I value Bill as much as any person here.

2492
02:26:01,335 --> 02:26:05,338
It's time we made room
for someone else's ideas, including me.

2493
02:26:06,591 --> 02:26:09,593
Maybe Oswald is what everyone says he is,
and I'm

2494
02:26:10,136 --> 02:26:12,053
just plain dumb about it.

2495
02:26:12,138 --> 02:26:14,890
OSER: I've seen him copying files here
late at night.

2496
02:26:14,974 --> 02:26:17,434
LOU: I don't trust him.
JIM: Did you two hear me?

2497
02:26:17,518 --> 02:26:20,228
I won't tolerate staff infighting.

2498
02:26:20,313 --> 02:26:23,648
I'm afraid I cannot work
with Bill Broussard anymore.

2499
02:26:24,942 --> 02:26:26,610
Is this an ultimatum?

2500
02:26:28,279 --> 02:26:29,988
JIM: Are you giving me an ultimatum?

2501
02:26:30,072 --> 02:26:32,282
If that's what you want to call it.

2502
02:26:34,494 --> 02:26:36,661
I never thought it'd come to this.

2503
02:26:40,374 --> 02:26:41,541
I guess I am.

2504
02:26:42,835 --> 02:26:47,547
I won't have any ultimatum put to me, Lou.
I'll accept your resignation.

2505
02:26:51,636 --> 02:26:53,178
You sure got it.

2506
02:26:58,559 --> 02:27:01,186
You are one stubborn son of a bitch.

2507
02:27:03,481 --> 02:27:05,649
LOU: You're making a big mistake.

2508
02:27:12,782 --> 02:27:15,492
SUSIE: Boss, aren't you being a little hard?

2509
02:27:16,744 --> 02:27:18,495
No, I don't think I am.

2510
02:27:20,081 --> 02:27:21,456
Anyone else?

2511
02:27:26,379 --> 02:27:29,172
Now, Jerry, here's Jim Garrison,

2512
02:27:29,715 --> 02:27:32,759
the District Attorney
of New Orleans, Louisiana.

2513
02:27:47,441 --> 02:27:49,693
Welcome, District Attorney Garrison.

2514
02:27:50,027 --> 02:27:54,406
You're investigating the murder
of President Kennedy.

2515
02:27:54,574 --> 02:27:58,034
We have heard some strange things
coming out of your office.

2516
02:27:58,661 --> 02:28:02,372
First, we heard that Cuban exiles
killed the President.

2517
02:28:02,456 --> 02:28:03,915
Then the mob.

2518
02:28:04,125 --> 02:28:08,920
Your latest theory seems to be
that the CIA and the FBl

2519
02:28:09,005 --> 02:28:10,338
and the Pentagon

2520
02:28:10,423 --> 02:28:15,594
and the White House all combined
in an elaborate conspiracy to kill Kennedy.

2521
02:28:17,388 --> 02:28:19,681
Is there anyone
besides Lee Harvey Oswald

2522
02:28:19,765 --> 02:28:22,976
who you think didn't conspire
to kill the President?

2523
02:28:25,521 --> 02:28:27,480
Let's just say this, Jerry,

2524
02:28:28,190 --> 02:28:29,774
I've stopped beating my wife.

2525
02:28:32,069 --> 02:28:35,363
Maybe you should ask Lyndon Johnson.
He has some answers.

2526
02:28:38,784 --> 02:28:42,579
There have been a number of reports
in reputable news media,

2527
02:28:42,872 --> 02:28:45,248
Time, Newsweek, our own NBC,

2528
02:28:45,666 --> 02:28:49,628
that you've gone beyond legal means
as a prosecutor,

2529
02:28:50,546 --> 02:28:53,548
that you've intimidated,
even drugged witnesses,

2530
02:28:53,633 --> 02:28:56,760
bribed them, and urged them
to commit perjury.

2531
02:28:57,511 --> 02:28:58,720
Do you have a response?

2532
02:28:58,846 --> 02:29:01,598
Your faith in the veracity
of the major media is touching.

2533
02:29:02,266 --> 02:29:05,268
It indicates that the age of innocence
is not yet over.

2534
02:29:05,353 --> 02:29:06,937
But ask yourself,

2535
02:29:07,021 --> 02:29:09,940
if we had learned
on November 22, 1963,

2536
02:29:10,024 --> 02:29:13,151
that the Russian Premier had been shot
from a Moscow building

2537
02:29:13,235 --> 02:29:15,195
by a lonely capitalist sympathizer

2538
02:29:15,279 --> 02:29:19,574
who, himself, was then liquidated
by a patriotic Muscovite within 48 hours

2539
02:29:19,659 --> 02:29:21,451
while surrounded by armed police.

2540
02:29:21,535 --> 02:29:23,995
I think it would be apparent to anyone

2541
02:29:24,080 --> 02:29:28,375
that a coup d'tat and a transfer
of power had just taken place.

2542
02:29:28,834 --> 02:29:32,712
And we would not ask questions
or attack Jim Garrison.

2543
02:29:33,047 --> 02:29:35,256
We would, in a free-thinking society,

2544
02:29:35,383 --> 02:29:39,552
be asking why he was killed,
and what forces opposed him.

2545
02:29:39,887 --> 02:29:43,556
There are some people who might say
that you are paranoid.

2546
02:29:43,724 --> 02:29:47,268
I should show you some pictures
so you can understand

2547
02:29:47,520 --> 02:29:49,312
what I'm talking about.

2548
02:29:50,481 --> 02:29:52,065
These are arrests.

2549
02:29:52,483 --> 02:29:56,403
These arrests were photographed
minutes after the assassination.

2550
02:29:56,570 --> 02:29:58,405
They were never shown to the public.

2551
02:29:58,531 --> 02:30:00,740
I'm sorry,
these pictures can't be shown on TV.

2552
02:30:00,825 --> 02:30:03,368
- Sure they can.
- No, I'm sorry. They can't.

2553
02:30:03,786 --> 02:30:06,538
- The camera can pick these up.
- Jim, I'm sorry.

2554
02:30:06,789 --> 02:30:09,749
They can't. We have libel laws.

2555
02:30:10,251 --> 02:30:13,837
Those men you just saw were arrested
in Dallas minutes after the assassination.

2556
02:30:13,921 --> 02:30:15,547
They were never seen again.

2557
02:30:15,631 --> 02:30:18,717
No record of arrest,
no mug shots, no fingerprints.

2558
02:30:19,010 --> 02:30:20,260
Hold that thought.

2559
02:30:20,344 --> 02:30:23,138
We'll be back,
right after these commercials.

2560
02:30:34,316 --> 02:30:36,526
Bill, what the hell are you doing here?

2561
02:30:36,610 --> 02:30:40,780
I'm sorry about the other day.
I didn't mean to walk out on you like that.

2562
02:30:41,741 --> 02:30:44,409
You came all this way
to tell me the obvious?

2563
02:30:44,869 --> 02:30:46,119
No. Look,

2564
02:30:46,495 --> 02:30:50,665
I just heard of an attempt to kill you
between here and New Orleans.

2565
02:30:51,125 --> 02:30:54,461
A mob guy was brought down by Shaw
from Canada.

2566
02:30:54,795 --> 02:30:57,922
This is serious.
You'll need a bodyguard tonight.

2567
02:30:58,549 --> 02:31:02,469
When you were in the Army,
did you ever find out what an order meant?

2568
02:31:02,678 --> 02:31:07,098
Do you remember my orders
about passing on rumors

2569
02:31:07,183 --> 02:31:08,600
about someone going to be killed?

2570
02:31:08,684 --> 02:31:11,061
- Yes, I do, but this is...
- No, there is no "but. "

2571
02:31:11,145 --> 02:31:13,813
There is no "but" in a military situation!

2572
02:31:14,356 --> 02:31:17,484
I don't appreciate you dumping
this paranoid garbage on me,

2573
02:31:17,568 --> 02:31:19,986
nor your inability
to follow a simple order

2574
02:31:20,071 --> 02:31:24,657
especially when it means I have to pay
for your flight back to New Orleans.

2575
02:31:25,242 --> 02:31:26,951
Let's get you a ticket.

2576
02:31:28,579 --> 02:31:31,581
Boss, I'm sorry.
I'm just looking out for you.

2577
02:31:31,957 --> 02:31:33,416
Get a receipt.

2578
02:32:20,756 --> 02:32:22,465
Come on, come on. He's out here.

2579
02:32:22,550 --> 02:32:25,760
Jim, where are you going?
It's me, Samuel.

2580
02:32:34,436 --> 02:32:38,523
- Hey, how long were you in that restroom?
- None of your goddamn business.

2581
02:33:27,740 --> 02:33:30,283
Jim, bad news, Bill's turned.

2582
02:33:30,492 --> 02:33:33,119
I think he's given everything we've got
to the feds.

2583
02:33:33,204 --> 02:33:36,497
We studied the memos
and there was nothing there. Nothing.

2584
02:33:36,582 --> 02:33:40,251
We went to confront him and the landlady
said the son of a bitch just left.

2585
02:33:40,336 --> 02:33:41,711
Left everything.

2586
02:33:42,296 --> 02:33:44,005
It's unbelievable. I'm sorry.

2587
02:33:44,089 --> 02:33:47,008
Mattie, could you get Mr. Garrison
a drink, please?

2588
02:33:47,259 --> 02:33:48,760
Something sure scared him.

2589
02:33:48,844 --> 02:33:52,096
Bill doesn't scare that easy.
Somebody got to his thinking.

2590
02:33:52,181 --> 02:33:55,308
- He was never that good a thinker.
- He sure fooled us.

2591
02:33:56,393 --> 02:33:59,812
No, no, leave it. Don't turn it down.
I want to see this.

2592
02:34:00,940 --> 02:34:03,358
You know what's happening, he's winning.

2593
02:34:05,653 --> 02:34:07,612
He'll never make it.

2594
02:34:08,364 --> 02:34:12,033
If he wins, they'll kill him.
He'll stop the war.

2595
02:34:13,786 --> 02:34:16,704
They'll kill him
before they let him be President.

2596
02:34:21,043 --> 02:34:24,337
With Broussard, they have everything,

2597
02:34:24,838 --> 02:34:27,298
all our witnesses,
our strategies for the trial.

2598
02:34:27,383 --> 02:34:29,133
We got to double check his work.

2599
02:34:29,218 --> 02:34:32,095
There could be false leads.
We can't go to trial!

2600
02:34:32,263 --> 02:34:33,638
We don't have a prayer!

2601
02:34:33,722 --> 02:34:36,849
- I don't think so, Al.
- I have to agree with Al, Boss.

2602
02:34:37,434 --> 02:34:39,894
This is not one we'll come out on.

2603
02:34:39,979 --> 02:34:43,314
You remember the Hemingway story,
The Old Man and the Sea?

2604
02:34:44,275 --> 02:34:47,527
The old fisherman manages
to catch this great fish,

2605
02:34:47,820 --> 02:34:51,823
a fish so huge, that he has to tie it
to the boat to get it back in.

2606
02:34:52,157 --> 02:34:53,950
By the time it reached shore

2607
02:34:54,034 --> 02:34:57,203
the fish had long since been picked apart
by sharks.

2608
02:35:00,874 --> 02:35:02,625
Nothing was left, but the skeleton.

2609
02:35:02,710 --> 02:35:06,671
- And that's what will happen to us.
- Then what did we do this for?

2610
02:35:06,755 --> 02:35:08,423
It's a means to an end.

2611
02:35:08,924 --> 02:35:10,883
This war has two fronts.

2612
02:35:12,303 --> 02:35:16,514
In a court of law,
we hope to get Clay Shaw for conspiracy.

2613
02:35:16,682 --> 02:35:20,601
In the court of public opinion,
it could take another 25, 30 years

2614
02:35:20,811 --> 02:35:22,770
for the truth to come out.

2615
02:35:24,857 --> 02:35:27,442
At least we'll strike the first blow.

2616
02:35:29,236 --> 02:35:30,737
What if you're wrong?

2617
02:35:34,658 --> 02:35:37,285
I never thought for a second I was.

2618
02:35:41,290 --> 02:35:43,416
Will you come to the trial?

2619
02:35:44,543 --> 02:35:45,543
I don't think so.

2620
02:35:47,629 --> 02:35:50,131
NEWSMAN 1:
With 53% of the precincts reporting,

2621
02:35:50,215 --> 02:35:53,384
Sen. Kennedy has a 48% to 41% lead

2622
02:35:53,469 --> 02:35:54,802
over Sen. McCarthy.

2623
02:35:54,928 --> 02:35:57,513
CBS News projects Sen. Robert Kennedy

2624
02:35:57,598 --> 02:35:59,849
the winner of the California primary.

2625
02:36:00,142 --> 02:36:04,562
ROBERT KENNEDY: [On TV]
Within the United States over the period

2626
02:36:04,646 --> 02:36:09,400
the division, the violence,
the disenchantment with our society,

2627
02:36:09,485 --> 02:36:11,444
the divisions between blacks
and whites,

2628
02:36:11,528 --> 02:36:14,822
the poor and the affluent,
between age groups

2629
02:36:14,907 --> 02:36:17,784
or Vietnam, we can work together.

2630
02:36:17,868 --> 02:36:21,871
We are a great country, an unselfish,
compassionate country.

2631
02:36:21,955 --> 02:36:23,873
That's my basis for running.

2632
02:36:23,957 --> 02:36:25,500
[Crowd on TV cheers]

2633
02:36:28,212 --> 02:36:31,422
Thank you all.
It's on to Chicago and let's win there.

2634
02:36:31,632 --> 02:36:33,216
[Gunshots on TV]

2635
02:36:34,093 --> 02:36:36,719
[Chaotic reactions from crowd on TV]

2636
02:36:44,853 --> 02:36:47,647
REPORTER 1:
Senator Kennedy has been shot!

2637
02:36:48,816 --> 02:36:51,734
[Dramatic instrumental music]

2638
02:37:29,857 --> 02:37:31,399
They killed him, honey.

2639
02:37:31,483 --> 02:37:32,900
[Liz moans]

2640
02:37:34,069 --> 02:37:35,236
He won

2641
02:37:35,946 --> 02:37:38,281
and they killed Robert Kennedy.

2642
02:37:38,866 --> 02:37:39,866
No.

2643
02:37:39,950 --> 02:37:41,451
They shot him down.

2644
02:37:42,244 --> 02:37:43,661
[Liz sighs]

2645
02:37:44,037 --> 02:37:45,496
LIZ: Oh, my God!

2646
02:37:48,208 --> 02:37:49,625
Both of them?

2647
02:37:50,461 --> 02:37:51,878
Both brothers?

2648
02:37:51,962 --> 02:37:54,672
[Dramatic music plays softly]

2649
02:37:57,384 --> 02:37:58,885
You were right.

2650
02:38:00,888 --> 02:38:02,722
It hasn't ended yet.

2651
02:38:10,397 --> 02:38:12,148
For the first time

2652
02:38:13,859 --> 02:38:15,860
I feel really scared.

2653
02:38:28,332 --> 02:38:30,666
JIM: I wish I could've loved you more.

2654
02:38:33,629 --> 02:38:38,132
Sometimes I feel like
I didn't ever love you

2655
02:38:39,301 --> 02:38:41,302
or the children enough.

2656
02:38:43,263 --> 02:38:44,597
JIM: I'm sorry.

2657
02:38:53,232 --> 02:38:55,858
[Dramatic instrumental music]

2658
02:38:56,068 --> 02:38:58,319
[Reporters all talk at once]

2659
02:39:24,096 --> 02:39:25,638
[Gavel bangs]

2660
02:39:28,350 --> 02:39:29,684
Please rise.

2661
02:39:32,062 --> 02:39:35,606
BAILIFF: The Criminal District Court for
Orleans Parish, Section H

2662
02:39:35,691 --> 02:39:37,066
is now in session.

2663
02:39:37,276 --> 02:39:41,320
Honorable Judge Edward A. Haggerty, Jr.
presiding. Be seated.

2664
02:39:46,785 --> 02:39:48,119
O'KEEFE: That's Clay Bertrand.

2665
02:39:48,203 --> 02:39:50,162
That's who I saw at Ferrie's.

2666
02:39:50,289 --> 02:39:52,164
DYMOND: That's who you say you saw.

2667
02:39:53,292 --> 02:39:55,001
DYMOND: A confessed homosexuaI.

2668
02:39:56,169 --> 02:39:58,546
Convicted of pandering and soliciting.

2669
02:39:59,381 --> 02:40:01,716
A man who has lied about everything

2670
02:40:02,134 --> 02:40:04,427
and now wants to be taken at his word.

2671
02:40:04,511 --> 02:40:07,513
That man, right there. Yes, sir.

2672
02:40:07,723 --> 02:40:10,057
He was at the Pontchartrain wall

2673
02:40:10,726 --> 02:40:13,144
with the man who shot the President.

2674
02:40:14,146 --> 02:40:16,606
I remember him because of his limp.

2675
02:40:16,732 --> 02:40:19,650
A heroin addict injecting himself
at the wall.

2676
02:40:20,068 --> 02:40:22,278
DYMOND: Barely conscious
of his surroundings.

2677
02:40:22,529 --> 02:40:25,406
- Is that the man?
- That was the man, right there.

2678
02:40:25,782 --> 02:40:27,908
He dropped Oswald off on the voter's line.

2679
02:40:28,493 --> 02:40:31,662
I remember 'cause they were the only
white strangers around that day.

2680
02:40:31,747 --> 02:40:35,499
That big black Cadillac of his
made me think they might be FBl.

2681
02:40:35,584 --> 02:40:38,794
Welcome to Clinton.
If you need any help, let us know.

2682
02:40:38,879 --> 02:40:42,798
He said he was a representative
of Warren International Trade Mart.

2683
02:40:43,300 --> 02:40:45,968
More than five years ago,
for two minutes?

2684
02:40:46,637 --> 02:40:48,846
It's fair to say you could be mistaken.

2685
02:40:48,930 --> 02:40:51,182
ANDREWS: Just a figment
of my imagination.

2686
02:40:51,391 --> 02:40:54,352
The cat's stewing you, I told him.

2687
02:40:54,436 --> 02:40:57,229
You got the right ta-ta,
but the wrong ho-ho.

2688
02:40:57,564 --> 02:41:01,233
Bertrand is not Shaw, scout's honor.
And you can tell him I said so.

2689
02:41:01,318 --> 02:41:02,485
SUSIE: Objection, Your Honor!

2690
02:41:02,569 --> 02:41:06,030
Andrews has been convicted of perjury
on this matter.

2691
02:41:06,114 --> 02:41:08,574
DYMOND: Exception taken.
That case is on appeal.

2692
02:41:09,868 --> 02:41:11,077
Mr. Goldberg,

2693
02:41:11,411 --> 02:41:14,455
you claim you met Ferrie and Shaw
on a vacation trip

2694
02:41:14,539 --> 02:41:16,540
from your accounting business
in New York.

2695
02:41:16,625 --> 02:41:18,000
You had drinks,

2696
02:41:18,085 --> 02:41:20,294
and while drunk,
discussed killing Kennedy.

2697
02:41:20,379 --> 02:41:22,588
- Is that not so?
- Yes, I did.

2698
02:41:22,673 --> 02:41:27,259
DYMOND: Is it true that you fingerprinted
your daughter when she went to college?

2699
02:41:27,552 --> 02:41:28,761
GOLDBERG: Yes, sir, I did.

2700
02:41:28,887 --> 02:41:32,765
DYMOND: Is it also true that you
fingerprinted her when she returned?

2701
02:41:32,974 --> 02:41:34,100
Yes, I did.

2702
02:41:34,476 --> 02:41:35,518
DYMOND: Why?

2703
02:41:35,894 --> 02:41:39,146
I wanted to make sure
she was the same girl I sent away.

2704
02:41:42,359 --> 02:41:44,443
He was one of Broussard's witnesses.

2705
02:41:44,528 --> 02:41:47,405
He was totally sane
when we took his affidavit.

2706
02:41:47,489 --> 02:41:51,784
JIM: Your Honor, we call Police Officer
Aloysius Habighorst to the stand.

2707
02:41:52,077 --> 02:41:54,578
JUDGE: I must ask the jury
to leave the court.

2708
02:41:54,746 --> 02:41:57,123
BAILIFF: Gentlemen,
please rise and follow me.

2709
02:41:57,207 --> 02:42:00,292
- Name?
- Clay LaVerne Shaw.

2710
02:42:00,502 --> 02:42:02,461
Defendant didn't have his lawyer present.

2711
02:42:02,546 --> 02:42:05,881
It's standard booking procedure
to ask an alias!

2712
02:42:05,966 --> 02:42:07,216
JUDGE: I call them as I see them!

2713
02:42:07,300 --> 02:42:08,592
HABIGHORST: Any aliases?

2714
02:42:08,677 --> 02:42:09,677
Clay Bertrand.

2715
02:42:09,970 --> 02:42:11,345
[Shouting]

2716
02:42:12,222 --> 02:42:14,932
It's not constitutionally required
that a lawyer be present!

2717
02:42:15,016 --> 02:42:19,395
JUDGE: I'm ruling that inadmissible!
JIM: That's our case!

2718
02:42:19,896 --> 02:42:22,148
JUDGE: Then you didn't have a case.

2719
02:42:22,566 --> 02:42:25,484
I wouldn't believe anything
Habighorst said anyway.

2720
02:42:25,569 --> 02:42:27,653
I can't believe you're saying this!

2721
02:42:27,821 --> 02:42:29,947
JUDGE: I am saying it. Bring in the jury.

2722
02:42:30,532 --> 02:42:31,991
[Gavel bangs]

2723
02:42:34,035 --> 02:42:36,245
DYMOND: Oswald?
CLAY: No, I did not.

2724
02:42:37,539 --> 02:42:40,666
DYMOND: Ever call Dean Andrews?
CLAY: No, I did not.

2725
02:42:42,169 --> 02:42:44,462
Have you ever met David Ferrie?

2726
02:42:44,546 --> 02:42:49,175
CLAY: Wouldn't even know what
he looked like if I hadn't seen pictures.

2727
02:42:50,844 --> 02:42:53,053
DYMOND: Did you ever use the alias,
Clay Bertrand?

2728
02:42:53,138 --> 02:42:55,347
No, I did not.

2729
02:42:56,516 --> 02:42:58,309
Thank you, Mr. Shaw.

2730
02:42:58,393 --> 02:43:01,312
[Dramatic instrumental music]

2731
02:43:01,563 --> 02:43:04,982
A very great actor has just given us
a great performance.

2732
02:43:05,066 --> 02:43:07,526
But we are nowhere closer to the truth.

2733
02:43:08,195 --> 02:43:12,239
My office is charging Clay Shaw
with outright perjury

2734
02:43:12,324 --> 02:43:16,368
on 15 answers he's given today,
not one word being true.

2735
02:43:16,745 --> 02:43:19,288
You're out of order! Now, sit down!

2736
02:43:19,581 --> 02:43:21,457
That's the man right there.

2737
02:43:24,503 --> 02:43:26,045
[Various voices shouting]

2738
02:43:26,671 --> 02:43:27,755
[Gavel bangs]

2739
02:43:28,423 --> 02:43:31,967
JIM: To prove there was a conspiracy
involving Clay Shaw

2740
02:43:32,093 --> 02:43:36,430
we must prove there was more than
one man involved in the assassination.

2741
02:43:37,140 --> 02:43:38,224
To do that

2742
02:43:38,308 --> 02:43:41,894
we must look at the Zapruder film
which my office subpoenaed.

2743
02:43:42,604 --> 02:43:44,939
The American public has not seen

2744
02:43:47,025 --> 02:43:52,613
has not seen the film. It's been locked
in a vault the last five years

2745
02:43:52,948 --> 02:43:55,491
in the Time-Life Building in New York.

2746
02:43:56,451 --> 02:43:58,536
JIM: There's a reason for that.

2747
02:43:59,454 --> 02:44:00,621
Watch.

2748
02:44:50,797 --> 02:44:53,132
JIM: "The picture speaks 1,000 words. "

2749
02:44:54,968 --> 02:44:57,970
The Warren Commission thought they had
an open-and-shut case.

2750
02:44:58,054 --> 02:45:00,180
Three bullets, one assassin.

2751
02:45:01,016 --> 02:45:04,560
Two unpredictable things happened
that day to make it impossible.

2752
02:45:04,644 --> 02:45:10,107
One, the film shot by Abraham Zapruder
while standing near the grassy knoll.

2753
02:45:10,692 --> 02:45:14,695
Two, the third wounded man,
James Teague, nicked by a fragment

2754
02:45:15,196 --> 02:45:17,656
while standing near the triple underpass.

2755
02:45:17,866 --> 02:45:21,577
The time frame, 5.6 seconds,
established by the Zapruder film

2756
02:45:21,828 --> 02:45:24,455
left no possibility of a fourth shot.

2757
02:45:24,706 --> 02:45:28,834
So the shot of fragment that left
a superficial wound on Teague's cheek

2758
02:45:29,210 --> 02:45:33,547
came from one of the three bullets
fired from the Depository's sixth floor.

2759
02:45:34,257 --> 02:45:36,216
That leaves just two bullets.

2760
02:45:36,718 --> 02:45:40,262
We know one was the fatal head shot
that killed Kennedy.

2761
02:45:42,057 --> 02:45:43,891
So a single bullet remains.

2762
02:45:44,142 --> 02:45:48,854
A single bullet must account for the seven
wounds in Kennedy and Connally.

2763
02:45:49,689 --> 02:45:52,775
Rather than admit to a conspiracy
or investigate further,

2764
02:45:52,859 --> 02:45:55,235
the Warren Commission
endorsed the theory

2765
02:45:55,320 --> 02:45:58,781
put forth by an ambitious attorney,
Arlen Spector.

2766
02:45:58,865 --> 02:46:02,368
One of the grossest lies ever forced
on the American people.

2767
02:46:03,912 --> 02:46:06,205
It's known as the "magic bullet" theory.

2768
02:46:07,082 --> 02:46:08,582
The magic bullet

2769
02:46:08,750 --> 02:46:13,170
enters the President's back,
headed downward at a 17-degree angle.

2770
02:46:13,713 --> 02:46:18,467
It then moves upwards to leave Kennedy's
body from the front of his neck,

2771
02:46:19,052 --> 02:46:20,552
wound number 2,

2772
02:46:21,012 --> 02:46:23,097
where it waits 1.6 seconds,

2773
02:46:23,723 --> 02:46:27,685
presumably in midair,
where it turns right, then left

2774
02:46:28,353 --> 02:46:30,396
right, then left,

2775
02:46:30,689 --> 02:46:34,108
and continues
into Connally's right armpit.

2776
02:46:34,401 --> 02:46:35,943
Wound number 3.

2777
02:46:36,361 --> 02:46:41,073
The bullet then heads down at an angle
of 27 degrees, shattering his rib

2778
02:46:41,908 --> 02:46:45,703
and exiting from the right side
of his chest. Wound number 4.

2779
02:46:46,413 --> 02:46:51,083
The bullet turns right, reentering
Connally's body at his right wrist.

2780
02:46:51,793 --> 02:46:53,127
Wound number 5.

2781
02:46:53,795 --> 02:46:55,587
Shattering the radius bone,

2782
02:46:55,755 --> 02:46:58,674
the bullet exits Connally's wrist,
wound number 6,

2783
02:46:59,175 --> 02:47:03,762
makes a dramatic U-turn,
then buries itself in Connally's left thigh.

2784
02:47:04,097 --> 02:47:07,057
Wound number 7,
from which it later falls out

2785
02:47:07,600 --> 02:47:10,352
and is found
in almost pristine condition

2786
02:47:10,770 --> 02:47:13,939
on a stretcher in a corridor
of Parkland Hospital.

2787
02:47:16,359 --> 02:47:17,818
Some bullet.

2788
02:47:19,529 --> 02:47:22,698
Any combat vet can tell you,
never in the history of gunfire

2789
02:47:22,782 --> 02:47:25,451
has there been a bullet this ridiculous.

2790
02:47:26,327 --> 02:47:31,165
The government says it can prove it
with some fancy physics in a nuclear lab.

2791
02:47:31,666 --> 02:47:33,125
Of course they can.

2792
02:47:33,418 --> 02:47:36,628
Theoretical physics can prove
an elephant can hang from a cliff

2793
02:47:36,713 --> 02:47:38,630
with his tail tied to a daisy.

2794
02:47:38,798 --> 02:47:39,882
[Crowd chuckles]

2795
02:47:39,966 --> 02:47:42,468
But use your eyes, your common sense.

2796
02:47:42,761 --> 02:47:46,972
The Army wound ballistics experts
fired some comparison bullets.

2797
02:47:47,557 --> 02:47:50,142
Not one of them looked anything like this.

2798
02:47:51,644 --> 02:47:53,812
Take a look at CE-856.

2799
02:47:54,773 --> 02:47:56,440
An identical bullet

2800
02:47:56,608 --> 02:47:59,443
fired through the wrist
of a human cadaver,

2801
02:48:00,028 --> 02:48:03,363
just one of the bones smashed
by the magic bullet.

2802
02:48:04,157 --> 02:48:05,991
Seven wounds, gentlemen.

2803
02:48:06,076 --> 02:48:07,409
Tough skin,

2804
02:48:07,869 --> 02:48:09,286
dense bones.

2805
02:48:10,663 --> 02:48:12,915
This single-bullet explanation

2806
02:48:12,999 --> 02:48:17,127
is the foundation of the Warren
Commission's claim of one assassin.

2807
02:48:17,545 --> 02:48:19,004
And once you conclude

2808
02:48:19,089 --> 02:48:22,091
the magic bullet couldn't create
all seven wounds

2809
02:48:22,342 --> 02:48:26,386
you must conclude there was
a fourth shot and a second rifleman.

2810
02:48:26,721 --> 02:48:27,805
[Dramatic instrumental music]

2811
02:48:27,889 --> 02:48:29,848
And if there was a second rifleman,

2812
02:48:30,642 --> 02:48:33,977
then by definition there had
to be a conspiracy

2813
02:48:34,395 --> 02:48:37,648
which we believe
involves the accused, Clay Shaw.

2814
02:48:38,441 --> 02:48:43,195
Fifty-one witnesses thought
they heard shots from the grassy knoll

2815
02:48:43,905 --> 02:48:47,074
which is to the right,
in front of the President.

2816
02:48:48,118 --> 02:48:49,868
Key witnesses that day?

2817
02:48:50,537 --> 02:48:52,788
Charles Brehm, a combat vet.

2818
02:48:53,414 --> 02:48:55,582
Jean Hill and Mary Moorman.

2819
02:48:56,626 --> 02:48:59,294
S. M. Holland, Richard Dodd,
James Simmons,

2820
02:48:59,587 --> 02:49:02,214
standing on the overpass. J.C. Price,

2821
02:49:02,298 --> 02:49:04,049
overlooking the plaza.

2822
02:49:04,926 --> 02:49:07,219
William Newman, father of two children.

2823
02:49:07,846 --> 02:49:10,389
He hit the deck on the north side of Elm.

2824
02:49:11,724 --> 02:49:13,392
Abraham Zapruder.

2825
02:49:22,819 --> 02:49:24,528
[Gunshot, crowd screams]

2826
02:49:30,076 --> 02:49:33,203
Each of these key witnesses
has no doubt whatsoever

2827
02:49:33,288 --> 02:49:36,456
one or more shots came
from behind the picket fence.

2828
02:49:37,333 --> 02:49:40,669
Twenty-six trained medical personnel
at Parkland Hospital

2829
02:49:40,753 --> 02:49:44,464
saw the back of the President's head
blasted out!

2830
02:49:46,759 --> 02:49:48,343
Doctor Peters.

2831
02:49:48,928 --> 02:49:53,640
There was a large 7 cm opening
at the right occipital parietal area.

2832
02:49:53,725 --> 02:49:56,643
A considerable portion
of the brain was missing.

2833
02:49:58,188 --> 02:50:01,690
MCCLELLAND: A fifth or possibly
a quarter of the back of the head

2834
02:50:01,774 --> 02:50:03,108
had been blasted out

2835
02:50:03,276 --> 02:50:05,402
along with the underlying brain tissue.

2836
02:50:05,486 --> 02:50:08,530
DOCTOR: When's the proper time
to declare one dead?

2837
02:50:08,615 --> 02:50:10,532
MCCLELLAND: There was also
a large fragment of skull

2838
02:50:10,617 --> 02:50:12,701
attached to a flap of the scalp.

2839
02:50:12,911 --> 02:50:16,914
The exit hole in the rear of his head
measured about 120 mm,

2840
02:50:17,248 --> 02:50:18,790
or five inches, across.

2841
02:50:18,875 --> 02:50:22,878
JIM: Not one of the civilian doctors
who examined the President

2842
02:50:23,171 --> 02:50:26,465
regarded his throat wound as anything
but an entry wound.

2843
02:50:27,342 --> 02:50:30,928
But then the body was illegally moved
to Washington for the autopsy.

2844
02:50:31,012 --> 02:50:33,263
Because when a coup d'tat has occurred

2845
02:50:33,348 --> 02:50:37,768
there's a big difference between
an autopsy performed by civilian doctors

2846
02:50:37,852 --> 02:50:41,438
and one that is performed
by military doctors under orders.

2847
02:50:42,523 --> 02:50:47,569
The departure of Air Force One, Friday
afternoon was not so much a takeoff

2848
02:50:47,737 --> 02:50:50,864
as it was a getaway,
with the newly sworn in President.

2849
02:50:50,949 --> 02:50:52,074
DYMOND: Objection!

2850
02:50:52,158 --> 02:50:53,116
Sustained.

2851
02:50:53,201 --> 02:50:55,619
JIM: On the plane,
the White House Situation Room

2852
02:50:55,703 --> 02:50:57,788
announced Oswald's guilt

2853
02:50:57,872 --> 02:51:01,667
to all passengers before any kind
of investigation had begun.

2854
02:51:02,168 --> 02:51:04,878
The "angry lone nut" solution
is beginning to take shape.

2855
02:51:04,963 --> 02:51:07,798
DYMOND: Objection, Your Honor.
JUDGE: Sustained.

2856
02:51:09,384 --> 02:51:11,260
Please bottle the acid.

2857
02:51:13,513 --> 02:51:18,308
JIM: The three Bethesda doctors picked by
the military left something to be desired.

2858
02:51:18,393 --> 02:51:22,020
None of them had experience
with combat-gunfire wounds.

2859
02:51:22,480 --> 02:51:27,025
Through their autopsy, we've been able
to justify eight wounds from two bullets.

2860
02:51:27,151 --> 02:51:29,361
Three to Kennedy, five to Connally.

2861
02:51:29,612 --> 02:51:31,947
One of them being the "magic bullet. "

2862
02:51:32,031 --> 02:51:33,615
FINCK: FBl?
FBl AGENT: Here.

2863
02:51:33,700 --> 02:51:37,661
JIM: Col. Finck, are you saying someone
told you not to dissect the neck?

2864
02:51:37,745 --> 02:51:40,539
I was told the family wanted
the examination of the head.

2865
02:51:41,499 --> 02:51:42,666
Oh, Christ.

2866
02:51:42,750 --> 02:51:44,543
PATHOLOGIST:
Looks like half his brain is gone.

2867
02:51:44,627 --> 02:51:47,087
FINCK: Weigh it.
PATHOLOGIST: 653 grams.

2868
02:51:47,171 --> 02:51:50,299
JIM: As a pathologist,
it was your obligation to explore

2869
02:51:50,383 --> 02:51:52,342
all possible causes of death.

2870
02:51:52,427 --> 02:51:53,927
I had the cause of death.

2871
02:51:54,012 --> 02:51:57,472
JIM: Your Honor, please direct the witness
to answer my question.

2872
02:51:58,391 --> 02:52:01,685
JIM: Why didn't Colonel Finck dissect
the tract of the bullet wound?

2873
02:52:01,769 --> 02:52:03,937
FINCK: I heard Dr. Humes stating.

2874
02:52:04,022 --> 02:52:06,148
HUMES: That's enough. That's enough.

2875
02:52:06,232 --> 02:52:07,649
It's duly noted.

2876
02:52:08,109 --> 02:52:09,985
FINCK: Let's check the back.

2877
02:52:10,278 --> 02:52:13,196
[Dramatic instrumental music]

2878
02:52:17,535 --> 02:52:19,953
HUMES: I can feel the end of the wound
with my finger.

2879
02:52:20,038 --> 02:52:21,955
That won't be necessary.

2880
02:52:22,373 --> 02:52:24,541
[Military drumbeat]

2881
02:52:24,625 --> 02:52:26,168
FINCK: Watch the ear!

2882
02:52:27,545 --> 02:52:29,880
Shot in the back. Cheap crime.

2883
02:52:30,173 --> 02:52:31,340
FINCK: He said...

2884
02:52:31,424 --> 02:52:33,258
Who's in charge here?

2885
02:52:33,509 --> 02:52:34,593
I am.

2886
02:52:35,928 --> 02:52:37,929
FINCK: I don't remember his name.

2887
02:52:38,014 --> 02:52:39,765
It was quite crowded.

2888
02:52:40,058 --> 02:52:43,810
And when you are called to look
at the wounds of the dead President

2889
02:52:43,895 --> 02:52:46,980
you don't ask people for their names
and who they are.

2890
02:52:47,065 --> 02:52:51,276
JIM: But you were a qualified pathologist.
Was the Army General?

2891
02:52:51,778 --> 02:52:52,903
FINCK: No.

2892
02:52:53,488 --> 02:52:54,863
JIM: But you took his orders.

2893
02:52:55,448 --> 02:52:56,531
Yes.

2894
02:52:56,616 --> 02:52:59,117
- So he was directing the autopsy.
- No.

2895
02:52:59,243 --> 02:53:00,911
There were others.

2896
02:53:02,163 --> 02:53:03,955
There were admirals.

2897
02:53:06,000 --> 02:53:08,919
When you're a Lieutenant Colonel,
you follow orders.

2898
02:53:09,003 --> 02:53:10,587
ADMIRAL KENNEY: It isn't our business

2899
02:53:10,671 --> 02:53:13,590
to discuss this with anyone
outside this room.

2900
02:53:13,674 --> 02:53:16,676
As I recall, Admiral Kenney,
Navy Surgeon General,

2901
02:53:17,011 --> 02:53:19,971
specifically told us
not to discuss the case.

2902
02:53:23,101 --> 02:53:26,395
JIM: A lot of people were deciding
what was private,

2903
02:53:26,687 --> 02:53:29,272
none of the American people's business.

2904
02:53:29,482 --> 02:53:31,441
The chief pathologist, Commander Humes

2905
02:53:31,526 --> 02:53:35,237
by his own admission,
voluntarily burned his autopsy notes.

2906
02:53:35,655 --> 02:53:38,198
President Johnson orders
the blood-soaked limousine

2907
02:53:38,282 --> 02:53:41,993
filled with bullet holes and clues
to be washed and rebuilt.

2908
02:53:42,203 --> 02:53:45,330
He sends Connally's bloody suit
to the cleaners.

2909
02:53:46,207 --> 02:53:50,544
The Justice Department denied this office
access to the autopsy photos.

2910
02:53:51,295 --> 02:53:55,674
When we finally get a court order
to examine Kennedy's brain

2911
02:53:56,092 --> 02:53:59,636
in the hopes of finding
from which direction the bullet came,

2912
02:53:59,720 --> 02:54:01,054
we're told,

2913
02:54:01,889 --> 02:54:05,892
by your government that
the President's brain has disappeared.

2914
02:54:06,018 --> 02:54:07,561
[Jury murmurs]

2915
02:54:09,272 --> 02:54:12,899
JIM: That's not all that's disappeared.
With it, the concept ofjustice.

2916
02:54:12,984 --> 02:54:17,571
DYMOND: Objection. Mr. Garrison is
insulting the federal government...

2917
02:54:18,156 --> 02:54:19,781
JUDGE: Overruled!

2918
02:54:26,873 --> 02:54:29,332
So, what really happened that day?

2919
02:54:29,584 --> 02:54:32,502
Let's just for a moment speculate,
shall we?

2920
02:54:32,670 --> 02:54:34,838
We have the epileptic seizure

2921
02:54:35,590 --> 02:54:39,718
distracting the police and allowing
the shooters to get into place.

2922
02:54:40,595 --> 02:54:44,723
The epileptic later vanished,
never checking into the hospital.

2923
02:54:45,933 --> 02:54:49,060
The A-team goes to the sixth floor
of the Depository.

2924
02:54:49,187 --> 02:54:51,813
They were refurbishing the floors
of the Depository that week,

2925
02:54:51,898 --> 02:54:54,649
allowing unknown workmen
in the building.

2926
02:54:54,734 --> 02:54:55,775
[Orders given over radio]

2927
02:54:55,860 --> 02:54:59,362
JIM: They move quickly into position,
minutes before the shooting.

2928
02:54:59,822 --> 02:55:04,409
The second spotter, talking by radio to
the other teams, has the best overall view.

2929
02:55:05,036 --> 02:55:06,286
The God spot.

2930
02:55:06,662 --> 02:55:11,625
B- team, one rifleman and one spotter
with access to the building

2931
02:55:11,709 --> 02:55:14,628
moves into a low floor
of the Dal-Tex building.

2932
02:55:15,630 --> 02:55:20,550
The third team, C-team, moves in
behind the fence above the grassy knoll

2933
02:55:20,760 --> 02:55:25,013
where the shooter and the spotter
are first seen by the late Lee Bowers.

2934
02:55:26,098 --> 02:55:28,099
They have the best position.

2935
02:55:28,643 --> 02:55:31,770
Kennedy is close and on a flat,
low trajectory.

2936
02:55:32,480 --> 02:55:34,314
Part of this team is a coordinator

2937
02:55:34,398 --> 02:55:38,527
who flashed security credentials
at people, chasing them from the area.

2938
02:55:38,611 --> 02:55:39,736
[Crowd cheers]

2939
02:55:39,820 --> 02:55:43,698
Probably two to three more men
are in the crowd.

2940
02:55:43,908 --> 02:55:47,577
Ten to twelve men.
Three teams. Three shooters.

2941
02:55:48,120 --> 02:55:52,999
The triangulation of fire Clay Shaw and
David Ferrie discussed two months before.

2942
02:55:53,793 --> 02:55:55,627
They blocked the plaza.

2943
02:55:55,920 --> 02:55:57,712
They know every inch.

2944
02:55:59,674 --> 02:56:03,468
They've calibrated their sights.
Practiced on moving targets.

2945
02:56:04,512 --> 02:56:05,762
They're ready.

2946
02:56:06,681 --> 02:56:10,225
Kennedy's motorcade makes a turn
from Main onto Houston.

2947
02:56:10,851 --> 02:56:12,936
It's going to be a turkey shoot.

2948
02:56:14,647 --> 02:56:16,690
They don't shoot him on Houston,

2949
02:56:16,774 --> 02:56:20,318
the easiest shot for a single shooter
in the Depository.

2950
02:56:20,528 --> 02:56:24,281
They wait till he gets to the killing zone
between three rifles.

2951
02:56:25,616 --> 02:56:28,660
Kennedy makes the turn
from Houston onto Elm.

2952
02:56:29,579 --> 02:56:32,872
Slowing down to some 11 miles an hour.

2953
02:56:33,541 --> 02:56:37,377
The shooters across Dealey Plaza tighten,
taking their aim.

2954
02:56:39,213 --> 02:56:42,340
Waiting for the radio to say,
"Green! Green!"

2955
02:56:43,301 --> 02:56:45,552
Or, "Abort! Abort!"

2956
02:56:48,097 --> 02:56:51,016
[Dramatic instrumental music]

2957
02:56:51,976 --> 02:56:53,476
The first shot rings out.

2958
02:56:53,561 --> 02:56:54,561
[Gunshot]

2959
02:56:54,645 --> 02:56:57,856
Sounding like a backfire,
it misses the car completely.

2960
02:56:58,274 --> 02:57:01,359
Frame 161, Kennedy stops waving
as he hears something.

2961
02:57:02,028 --> 02:57:04,696
Connally's head turns slightly to the right.

2962
02:57:04,947 --> 02:57:08,867
Frame 193, the second shot hits Kennedy
in the throat from the front.

2963
02:57:09,577 --> 02:57:12,912
Frame 225, Kennedy emerges
from behind the road sign.

2964
02:57:13,247 --> 02:57:16,708
He's been hit, raising his hands
to his throat.

2965
02:57:17,335 --> 02:57:18,793
The third shot, frame 232,

2966
02:57:18,878 --> 02:57:19,878
[Gunshot]

2967
02:57:19,962 --> 02:57:23,465
hits Kennedy in the back,
pulling him downward and forward.

2968
02:57:23,674 --> 02:57:26,843
Connally, you will notice,
shows no sign of being hit.

2969
02:57:27,094 --> 02:57:31,139
He is holding his Stetson, which is
impossible if his wrist is shattered.

2970
02:57:31,265 --> 02:57:33,099
Connally is turning now.

2971
02:57:33,184 --> 02:57:35,352
Frame 238. The fourth shot.

2972
02:57:35,770 --> 02:57:38,104
It misses Kennedy and takes Connally
in the back.

2973
02:57:38,189 --> 02:57:39,314
[Gunshot]

2974
02:57:39,398 --> 02:57:42,275
This is the shot that proves
there were two rifles.

2975
02:57:42,360 --> 02:57:45,862
Connally yells, "My God!
They're going to kill us all!"

2976
02:57:46,113 --> 02:57:49,491
Around this time,
another shot misses the car completely

2977
02:57:49,617 --> 02:57:52,202
striking James Teague by the underpass.

2978
02:57:53,120 --> 02:57:54,371
The car brakes.

2979
02:57:54,622 --> 02:57:56,373
The sixth and fatal shot.

2980
02:57:56,540 --> 02:58:00,001
Frame 313, takes Kennedy in the head
from the front.

2981
02:58:00,086 --> 02:58:01,419
[Gunshot]

2982
02:58:01,754 --> 02:58:03,338
This is the key shot.

2983
02:58:03,798 --> 02:58:06,424
The President going back and to his left,

2984
02:58:07,009 --> 02:58:09,177
shot from the front and right.

2985
02:58:10,137 --> 02:58:12,931
Totally inconsistent with the shot
from the Depository.

2986
02:58:13,015 --> 02:58:14,057
[Panicked screaming]

2987
02:58:14,141 --> 02:58:15,266
Again.

2988
02:58:18,688 --> 02:58:20,605
Back, and to the left.

2989
02:58:21,982 --> 02:58:23,817
Back, and to the left.

2990
02:58:25,152 --> 02:58:26,945
Back, and to the left.

2991
02:58:29,323 --> 02:58:31,157
So what happens then?

2992
02:58:31,242 --> 02:58:33,326
[Panicked screams from crowd]

2993
02:58:33,577 --> 02:58:34,828
Pandemonium.

2994
02:58:37,748 --> 02:58:39,582
A- TEAM ASSASSIN:
Let's go! We got him!

2995
02:58:40,000 --> 02:58:43,503
[Fast-paced, dramatic instrumental music]

2996
02:58:45,172 --> 02:58:48,049
JIM: The shooters quickly disassemble
their various weapons

2997
02:58:48,134 --> 02:58:49,968
except the Oswald rifle.

2998
02:59:01,188 --> 02:59:04,649
Patrolman Smith rushes to the parking lot
behind the fence.

2999
02:59:05,192 --> 02:59:06,568
He smells gunpowder.

3000
02:59:06,694 --> 02:59:10,530
He produced credentials showing him
to be Secret Service.

3001
02:59:11,532 --> 02:59:14,367
SMITH: Let's see your ID.
See anyone else up here?

3002
02:59:15,369 --> 02:59:18,329
SMITH: I accepted that and let him go.

3003
02:59:18,706 --> 02:59:21,332
I regretted it. He looked like a mechanic.

3004
02:59:22,543 --> 02:59:26,713
He had on a sports shirt and pants,
but he had dirty fingernails.

3005
02:59:28,549 --> 02:59:31,468
Afterward, it didn't ring true.
But at the time

3006
02:59:31,635 --> 02:59:33,678
we were so pressed for time.

3007
02:59:34,472 --> 02:59:37,640
JIM: All Secret Servicemen
in Dallas are accounted for.

3008
02:59:38,434 --> 02:59:41,352
None were on foot in Dealey Plaza
before or after the shooting

3009
02:59:41,437 --> 02:59:45,523
till the Dallas Secret Service chief
returned at 12:55.

3010
02:59:46,317 --> 02:59:50,028
The Dallas police took at least 12 people
into custody.

3011
02:59:51,071 --> 02:59:52,614
No record of their arrest.

3012
02:59:52,782 --> 02:59:56,367
JIM: Men acting like hoboes
were pulled off trains,

3013
02:59:56,660 --> 02:59:59,162
marched through Dealey Plaza,
photographed.

3014
02:59:59,246 --> 03:00:01,498
Yet there's no record of their arrest.

3015
03:00:01,582 --> 03:00:05,335
Men identifying themselves
as Secret Service agents were everywhere.

3016
03:00:06,253 --> 03:00:08,296
But who was impersonating them?

3017
03:00:08,589 --> 03:00:10,173
Where was Oswald?

3018
03:00:10,841 --> 03:00:14,761
Around 12:15, leaving the building
to see the motorcade,

3019
03:00:14,845 --> 03:00:18,264
Carolyn Arnold sees Oswald
in the second-floor snack room,

3020
03:00:18,349 --> 03:00:20,600
where he said he went for a Coke.

3021
03:00:21,268 --> 03:00:24,521
CAROLYN: He was in a booth
on the right side of the room.

3022
03:00:25,022 --> 03:00:28,691
He was by himself as usual,
appeared to be having lunch.

3023
03:00:29,026 --> 03:00:32,028
I didn't speak to him,
but I recognized him clearly.

3024
03:00:32,363 --> 03:00:34,531
JIM: At the same time,
Bonnie Ray Williams is

3025
03:00:34,615 --> 03:00:37,450
supposedly eating lunch
in the sixth floor.

3026
03:00:37,660 --> 03:00:40,537
He's there until 12:15, maybe 12:20.

3027
03:00:41,163 --> 03:00:42,705
He sees nobody.

3028
03:00:43,374 --> 03:00:47,836
Arnold Rowlands, on the street, looks up,
sees two men in the sixth-floor windows,

3029
03:00:47,920 --> 03:00:51,422
presumably after Williams
finished his lunch and left.

3030
03:00:52,049 --> 03:00:55,969
John Powell, a prisoner on the sixth floor
of the county jail, sees them.

3031
03:00:56,053 --> 03:00:57,512
POWELL: Many ofus saw them.

3032
03:00:57,596 --> 03:01:01,850
Everyone was hollering and yelling.
We thought they was security guys.

3033
03:01:02,226 --> 03:01:06,855
If Oswald was the assassin, he was
nonchalant about moving into position.

3034
03:01:07,481 --> 03:01:11,192
JIM: Later, he told police he was
in the second-floor snack room.

3035
03:01:11,443 --> 03:01:14,612
Probably told to wait there
by his handler for a call.

3036
03:01:16,156 --> 03:01:18,241
But the phone call never came.

3037
03:01:18,826 --> 03:01:21,494
Maximum 90 seconds
after Kennedy is shot,

3038
03:01:21,579 --> 03:01:25,540
Patrolman Marrion Baker sees Oswald
in that second-floor lunchroom.

3039
03:01:27,001 --> 03:01:28,668
BAKER: Is this man an employee?

3040
03:01:28,752 --> 03:01:31,462
Yes. The President's been shot.

3041
03:01:31,797 --> 03:01:33,673
JIM: The Commission would
have us believe

3042
03:01:33,757 --> 03:01:37,302
that after firing three bolt-action shots
in 5.6 seconds

3043
03:01:37,803 --> 03:01:42,348
Oswald then leaves three cartridges
neatly side-by-side in the firing nest,

3044
03:01:42,433 --> 03:01:47,020
wipes fingerprints off the rifle,
stashes it on the other side of the loft,

3045
03:01:48,022 --> 03:01:50,356
sprints down five flights of stairs

3046
03:01:50,441 --> 03:01:53,943
past Victoria Adams and Sandra Styles
who never see him,

3047
03:01:54,695 --> 03:01:59,198
then shows up, cool and calm, on the
second floor in front of Patrolman Baker.

3048
03:02:00,701 --> 03:02:04,037
All this within a maximum of 90 seconds
of the shooting.

3049
03:02:04,622 --> 03:02:06,664
BAKER: Is this man an employee?

3050
03:02:06,749 --> 03:02:08,833
Yes. The President's been shot.

3051
03:02:09,001 --> 03:02:10,793
JIM: Is he out of breath?

3052
03:02:11,170 --> 03:02:13,671
According to Baker, absolutely not.

3053
03:02:14,131 --> 03:02:18,885
Assuming he is the sole assassin,
Oswald is free to leave the building.

3054
03:02:19,470 --> 03:02:24,057
The longer he delays, the more chance
the building will be sealed by police.

3055
03:02:24,725 --> 03:02:28,102
Is he guilty? Does he walk
out the nearest staircase?

3056
03:02:30,230 --> 03:02:31,940
He buys a Coke,

3057
03:02:32,191 --> 03:02:36,444
and at a slow pace, spotted by Mrs. Reid
on the second floor,

3058
03:02:36,820 --> 03:02:39,364
he strolls out
the more distant front exit

3059
03:02:39,448 --> 03:02:41,115
where cops have gathered.

3060
03:02:41,200 --> 03:02:44,285
Odd, since three shots were fired
from there,

3061
03:02:44,370 --> 03:02:47,538
nobody seals the Depository
for ten more minutes.

3062
03:02:47,748 --> 03:02:50,875
Oswald slips out,
as do several other employees.

3063
03:02:51,001 --> 03:02:55,213
When he realized something had gone
wrong and Kennedy had been killed,

3064
03:02:55,589 --> 03:02:59,425
he knew there was a problem.
Maybe even that he was the patsy.

3065
03:03:00,094 --> 03:03:04,222
An intuition, maybe. The President killed
in spite of his warning.

3066
03:03:04,306 --> 03:03:06,015
The phone call that never came.

3067
03:03:06,350 --> 03:03:09,894
Perhaps fear now came to Oswald
for the very first time.

3068
03:03:11,271 --> 03:03:14,565
Oswald returns to his rooming house
around 1:00 p.m.,

3069
03:03:14,650 --> 03:03:17,110
a half hour after the assassination.

3070
03:03:17,277 --> 03:03:19,070
EARLENE: A man shot the President!

3071
03:03:19,154 --> 03:03:22,115
JIM: He puts on his jacket,
grabs his. 38 revolver

3072
03:03:22,199 --> 03:03:23,783
and leaves at 1:04.

3073
03:03:23,867 --> 03:03:24,826
[Car honks]

3074
03:03:24,910 --> 03:03:27,912
Earlene Roberts, the housekeeper,
heard two beeps on a car horn.

3075
03:03:27,997 --> 03:03:31,457
Two uniformed cops pulled up
while Oswald was in his room.

3076
03:03:31,542 --> 03:03:33,334
Like it was a signal.

3077
03:03:34,211 --> 03:03:38,756
Officer Tippit is shot between 1:10
and 1:15, a mile away.

3078
03:03:38,841 --> 03:03:41,551
And though no one saw him walking,

3079
03:03:41,719 --> 03:03:44,470
the government says
Oswald covered that distance.

3080
03:03:44,555 --> 03:03:47,098
Giving the government the benefit
of the doubt,

3081
03:03:47,182 --> 03:03:50,309
Oswald would've had to jog a mile
in six to eleven minutes

3082
03:03:50,394 --> 03:03:53,187
then commit the murder,
reverse his direction

3083
03:03:53,272 --> 03:03:56,315
and walk three-fifths of a mile
to the Texas Theater

3084
03:03:56,400 --> 03:03:58,985
and arrive sometime before 1:30.

3085
03:03:59,194 --> 03:04:02,113
[Dramatic instrumental music]

3086
03:04:04,408 --> 03:04:06,117
It's also a useful conclusion.

3087
03:04:06,201 --> 03:04:08,745
After all, why would Oswald
kill Officer Tippit

3088
03:04:08,829 --> 03:04:11,998
unless he just shot the President
and feared arrest?

3089
03:04:12,583 --> 03:04:14,417
Domingo Benevides,

3090
03:04:16,003 --> 03:04:18,254
the closest witness to the shooting,

3091
03:04:18,338 --> 03:04:22,759
refused to identify Oswald as the killer
and was never taken to a lineup.

3092
03:04:23,052 --> 03:04:24,302
Acquilla Clemons

3093
03:04:24,386 --> 03:04:27,847
saw the killer and another man
go off in separate directions.

3094
03:04:28,640 --> 03:04:32,310
Mrs. Clemons was never taken to a lineup
or to the Warren Commission.

3095
03:04:32,811 --> 03:04:36,898
At the scene, Officer Poe marks
his initials on the shells

3096
03:04:36,982 --> 03:04:39,192
to record the chain of evidence.

3097
03:04:39,818 --> 03:04:42,820
Those initials are not
on the three cartridge cases

3098
03:04:42,905 --> 03:04:45,073
which the Warren Commission show him.

3099
03:04:45,407 --> 03:04:49,494
As early as 12:44, only 14 minutes
after the assassination

3100
03:04:49,912 --> 03:04:53,498
the police put out a description
matching Oswald's size and build.

3101
03:04:53,582 --> 03:04:54,665
[Sirens blare]

3102
03:04:54,750 --> 03:04:58,961
Oswald is next seen by a shoe salesman,
Johnny Brewer, on Jefferson Avenue.

3103
03:05:00,380 --> 03:05:04,967
Oswald is scared. He begins to realize
the full implications of this thing.

3104
03:05:05,094 --> 03:05:08,888
He goes to the Texas Theater,
possibly a prearranged meeting point.

3105
03:05:09,181 --> 03:05:13,935
Though he has $14 in his pocket,
he doesn't buy the $0.75 ticket.

3106
03:05:14,228 --> 03:05:16,521
Brewer has the cashier call the police.

3107
03:05:16,897 --> 03:05:18,856
In response to that call,

3108
03:05:19,191 --> 03:05:23,528
at least 30 officers in patrol cars descend
on the movie theater.

3109
03:05:24,029 --> 03:05:27,573
This is the most remarkable example
of police intuition

3110
03:05:27,658 --> 03:05:29,659
since the Reichstag fire.

3111
03:05:30,369 --> 03:05:31,536
I don't buy it!

3112
03:05:31,829 --> 03:05:35,206
They knew. Someone knew
Oswald would be there.

3113
03:05:36,625 --> 03:05:38,876
Brewer leads the cops into the theater,

3114
03:05:38,961 --> 03:05:41,003
and from the stage, points Oswald out.

3115
03:05:41,171 --> 03:05:42,380
There he is.

3116
03:05:42,589 --> 03:05:45,508
[Dramatic instrumental music]

3117
03:05:54,685 --> 03:05:57,228
POLICEMAN:
Sir, can I get you to stand up?

3118
03:05:59,231 --> 03:06:00,606
[Shouting]

3119
03:06:03,068 --> 03:06:07,488
OSWALD: I am not resisting arrest!
I am not resisting arrest!

3120
03:06:07,739 --> 03:06:09,157
JIM: They have their man.

3121
03:06:10,117 --> 03:06:13,202
It's already been decided in Washington.

3122
03:06:13,871 --> 03:06:16,372
When he is brought from the theater

3123
03:06:16,623 --> 03:06:19,167
a crowd is waiting to scream at him.

3124
03:06:19,251 --> 03:06:22,837
Lee Oswald must have felt like Joseph K.
in Kafka's The Trial.

3125
03:06:22,921 --> 03:06:25,381
He's never given reasons for his arrest.

3126
03:06:25,465 --> 03:06:28,551
He doesn't know the unseen forces
ranging against him.

3127
03:06:29,011 --> 03:06:32,763
At police headquarters, he was booked
for murdering Tippit.

3128
03:06:33,015 --> 03:06:34,932
No legal counsel was provided.

3129
03:06:35,017 --> 03:06:37,351
No record made of the questioning.

3130
03:06:37,436 --> 03:06:40,021
When the sun rises the next morning

3131
03:06:40,105 --> 03:06:42,732
he is booked for murdering the President.

3132
03:06:42,816 --> 03:06:46,611
The whole country, fueled by the media,
assumes he is guilty.

3133
03:06:47,446 --> 03:06:49,697
Under the guise of a patriotic club owner

3134
03:06:49,781 --> 03:06:53,201
out to spare Jackie Kennedy
from testifying at a trial,

3135
03:06:53,869 --> 03:06:56,370
Jack Ruby is let into a garage

3136
03:06:56,455 --> 03:06:59,415
by one of his inside men
on the police force.

3137
03:07:00,167 --> 03:07:04,045
Oswald is brought out
like a sacrificial lamb

3138
03:07:04,129 --> 03:07:07,298
and nicely disposed of as an enemy
of the people.

3139
03:07:08,300 --> 03:07:09,634
[Gunshot]

3140
03:07:16,808 --> 03:07:18,309
[Oswald gasps]

3141
03:07:25,943 --> 03:07:27,944
JIM: Who grieves for Lee Harvey Oswald,

3142
03:07:28,820 --> 03:07:31,822
buried in a cheap grave
under the name Oswald?

3143
03:07:32,574 --> 03:07:33,699
Nobody.

3144
03:07:33,784 --> 03:07:36,285
[Dramatic music plays softly]

3145
03:07:41,500 --> 03:07:46,003
False statements and press leaks
about Oswald circulate the globe.

3146
03:07:47,422 --> 03:07:50,675
The official legend is created
and the media takes it from there.

3147
03:07:52,344 --> 03:07:56,180
The glitter of official lies
and the epic splendor of JFK's funeral

3148
03:07:56,265 --> 03:07:59,517
confuse the eye
and confound the understanding.

3149
03:08:00,894 --> 03:08:02,353
Hitler said,

3150
03:08:02,938 --> 03:08:06,357
"The bigger the lie,
the more people will believe it. "

3151
03:08:07,567 --> 03:08:11,112
Lee Harvey Oswald, a crazed,
lonely man who wanted attention

3152
03:08:11,196 --> 03:08:15,950
and got it by killing a President
was only the first in a long line of patsies.

3153
03:08:16,451 --> 03:08:19,412
In later years, Bobby Kennedy,
Martin Luther King,

3154
03:08:19,496 --> 03:08:22,164
men whose commitment
to change and peace

3155
03:08:22,249 --> 03:08:25,876
made them dangerous to men
committed to war, would follow,

3156
03:08:26,378 --> 03:08:29,213
also killed by such lonely, crazed men.

3157
03:08:30,299 --> 03:08:34,635
Men who remove all guilt by making
murder a meaningless act of a loner.

3158
03:08:35,887 --> 03:08:40,224
We've all become Hamlets in our country,
children of a slain father-leader,

3159
03:08:40,309 --> 03:08:42,560
whose killers still possess the throne.

3160
03:08:43,145 --> 03:08:46,856
JIM: The ghost of John F. Kennedy
confronts us with the secret murder

3161
03:08:46,940 --> 03:08:49,317
at the heart of the American Dream.

3162
03:08:49,401 --> 03:08:53,904
He forces on us the appalling questions:
Of what is our Constitution made?

3163
03:08:54,531 --> 03:08:56,824
What are our lives worth?

3164
03:08:56,908 --> 03:08:59,035
What is the future of a democracy

3165
03:08:59,119 --> 03:09:03,456
where a President can be assassinated
under suspicious circumstances

3166
03:09:03,540 --> 03:09:06,584
while the machinery of legal action
scarcely trembles?

3167
03:09:07,836 --> 03:09:11,464
How many more political murders
disguised as heart attacks,

3168
03:09:11,548 --> 03:09:14,175
suicides, cancers, drug overdoses?

3169
03:09:14,259 --> 03:09:16,927
How many plane and car crashes
will occur

3170
03:09:17,012 --> 03:09:19,805
before they are exposed
for what they are?

3171
03:09:21,350 --> 03:09:24,643
"Treason doth never prosper,"
wrote an English poet.

3172
03:09:25,103 --> 03:09:26,854
"What's the reason?

3173
03:09:27,314 --> 03:09:29,607
"For if it prosper,
none dare call it treason. "

3174
03:09:30,734 --> 03:09:34,111
The American public has yet
to see the Zapruder film.

3175
03:09:34,321 --> 03:09:35,404
Why?

3176
03:09:35,906 --> 03:09:40,201
The American public has yet to see
the real X-rays and autopsy photographs.

3177
03:09:40,285 --> 03:09:41,369
Why?

3178
03:09:42,162 --> 03:09:45,456
Hundreds of documents could help prove
this conspiracy.

3179
03:09:45,540 --> 03:09:49,085
Why are they being withheld
or burned by the government?

3180
03:09:49,669 --> 03:09:54,298
When my office or you, the people, asked
those questions, demanded evidence,

3181
03:09:54,383 --> 03:09:58,094
the answer from on high
has always been, national security.

3182
03:09:59,429 --> 03:10:02,807
What kind of national security do we have
when we're robbed of our leaders?

3183
03:10:04,142 --> 03:10:06,477
What national security
permits the removal

3184
03:10:06,770 --> 03:10:09,313
of fundamental power from the people

3185
03:10:09,398 --> 03:10:13,484
and validates the ascendancy
of an invisible government in the US?

3186
03:10:14,569 --> 03:10:16,570
That kind of national security is

3187
03:10:16,655 --> 03:10:20,241
when it smells like it, feels like it,
and looks like it,

3188
03:10:20,742 --> 03:10:22,660
you call it what it is:

3189
03:10:22,953 --> 03:10:24,161
Fascism!

3190
03:10:26,415 --> 03:10:31,419
I submit to you that what took place
on November 22, 1963

3191
03:10:31,545 --> 03:10:33,212
was a coup d'tat.

3192
03:10:33,922 --> 03:10:36,257
Its most direct and tragic result

3193
03:10:36,508 --> 03:10:40,511
was the reversal of Kennedy's decision
to withdraw from Vietnam.

3194
03:10:41,763 --> 03:10:44,348
The war is the biggest business
in America

3195
03:10:44,433 --> 03:10:46,600
worth $80 billion a year.

3196
03:10:47,727 --> 03:10:50,563
President Kennedy was murdered
by a conspiracy

3197
03:10:50,647 --> 03:10:53,691
planned at the highest levels
of our government,

3198
03:10:53,775 --> 03:10:57,361
carried out by fanatical
and disciplined cold warriors

3199
03:10:57,446 --> 03:11:00,948
in the Pentagon and CIA's
covert-operation apparatus.

3200
03:11:01,032 --> 03:11:03,742
Among them, Clay Shaw, here before you.

3201
03:11:04,411 --> 03:11:07,705
It was a public execution,
and it was covered up by

3202
03:11:07,789 --> 03:11:10,749
like-minded people in the Dallas Police,

3203
03:11:10,834 --> 03:11:13,919
the Secret Service, the FBl,
and the White House,

3204
03:11:14,254 --> 03:11:17,298
up to and including J. Edgar Hoover,
and Lyndon Johnson

3205
03:11:17,382 --> 03:11:18,424
[Crowd murmurs]

3206
03:11:18,508 --> 03:11:21,051
who were accomplices after the fact.

3207
03:11:21,595 --> 03:11:25,556
The assassination reduced the President
to a transient official.

3208
03:11:26,224 --> 03:11:31,562
His job is to speak as often as possible
of the nation's desire for peace

3209
03:11:32,147 --> 03:11:34,815
while he acts as a business agent
in the Congress

3210
03:11:34,900 --> 03:11:36,984
for the military and their contractors.

3211
03:11:39,321 --> 03:11:41,363
Some people say I'm crazy.

3212
03:11:41,573 --> 03:11:42,865
[Crowd chuckles]

3213
03:11:42,949 --> 03:11:45,784
Southern caricature seeking higher office.

3214
03:11:48,121 --> 03:11:50,873
There's a simple way to determine
if I am paranoid.

3215
03:11:51,583 --> 03:11:54,251
Ask the two men who profited most
from the assassination,

3216
03:11:54,336 --> 03:11:58,255
former President Johnson
and your new President, Nixon,

3217
03:11:58,465 --> 03:12:03,219
to release the 51 CIA documents
pertaining to Lee Oswald and Jack Ruby.

3218
03:12:04,137 --> 03:12:05,888
Or the secret CIA memo

3219
03:12:05,972 --> 03:12:09,850
on Oswald's activities in Russia that
was destroyed while being photocopied.

3220
03:12:10,477 --> 03:12:12,520
These documents are yours.

3221
03:12:13,063 --> 03:12:15,689
The people's property. You pay for it.

3222
03:12:16,233 --> 03:12:18,359
But as the government sees you
as children

3223
03:12:18,443 --> 03:12:21,570
who might be too disturbed
to face this reality

3224
03:12:22,322 --> 03:12:25,115
or because you might lynch
those involved,

3225
03:12:26,076 --> 03:12:29,245
you cannot see these documents
for another 75 years.

3226
03:12:30,247 --> 03:12:31,914
I'm in my 40s

3227
03:12:33,124 --> 03:12:36,043
so I'll have "shuffled off
this mortal coil" by then.

3228
03:12:36,127 --> 03:12:40,548
But I'm telling my eight-year-old son
to keep himself physically fit

3229
03:12:41,466 --> 03:12:45,469
so that one glorious September morning,
in 2038,

3230
03:12:45,554 --> 03:12:50,307
he can go to the National Archives
and learn what the CIA and FBl knew.

3231
03:12:52,018 --> 03:12:53,477
They may push it back then.

3232
03:12:53,562 --> 03:12:59,233
It may become a generational affair.
Questions passed from parent to child.

3233
03:12:59,401 --> 03:13:03,445
But someday, somewhere,
someone may find out the damn truth.

3234
03:13:04,406 --> 03:13:05,531
We better.

3235
03:13:06,658 --> 03:13:10,369
Or we might just as well build ourselves
another government

3236
03:13:10,829 --> 03:13:15,291
like the Declaration of Independence
says to, when the old one don't work.

3237
03:13:15,375 --> 03:13:17,084
Just a bit farther out West.

3238
03:13:18,878 --> 03:13:20,879
An American naturalist wrote,

3239
03:13:21,172 --> 03:13:24,425
"A patriot must always be ready
to defend his country

3240
03:13:24,718 --> 03:13:26,677
"against its government. "

3241
03:13:28,179 --> 03:13:30,681
I'd hate to be in your shoes today.

3242
03:13:31,141 --> 03:13:35,686
You have a lot to think about. You've seen
evidence the public hasn't seen.

3243
03:13:36,896 --> 03:13:39,440
Going back to when we were children,

3244
03:13:40,108 --> 03:13:44,862
I think most of us in this courtroom
thought justice came automatically.

3245
03:13:46,031 --> 03:13:48,115
That virtue was its own reward.

3246
03:13:48,199 --> 03:13:50,367
That good triumphs over evil.

3247
03:13:51,286 --> 03:13:54,204
But as we get older
we know this isn't true.

3248
03:13:55,081 --> 03:13:59,251
Individual human beings have to create
justice, and this is not easy

3249
03:14:00,712 --> 03:14:03,839
because the truth often poses a threat
to power,

3250
03:14:04,215 --> 03:14:07,051
and one often has to fight power
at great risk to themselves.

3251
03:14:08,053 --> 03:14:10,054
People like S.M. Holland,

3252
03:14:10,555 --> 03:14:11,889
Lee Bowers,

3253
03:14:12,432 --> 03:14:14,266
Jean Hill, Willie O'Keefe,

3254
03:14:14,351 --> 03:14:17,770
have all taken that risk
and they've all come forward.

3255
03:14:17,937 --> 03:14:20,731
I have here some $8,000 in these letters

3256
03:14:21,650 --> 03:14:23,942
sent from all over the country.

3257
03:14:24,277 --> 03:14:26,945
Quarters, dimes, dollars from housewives

3258
03:14:27,614 --> 03:14:30,449
plumbers, car salesmen,
teachers, invalids.

3259
03:14:31,660 --> 03:14:35,079
These are people who cannot afford
to send money but do.

3260
03:14:35,997 --> 03:14:37,873
People who drive cabs,

3261
03:14:38,458 --> 03:14:40,084
who nurse in hospitals,

3262
03:14:40,168 --> 03:14:42,586
who see their kids go to Vietnam.

3263
03:14:43,880 --> 03:14:44,922
Why?

3264
03:14:46,549 --> 03:14:48,217
Because they care.

3265
03:14:48,968 --> 03:14:50,636
Because they want to know the truth.

3266
03:14:51,846 --> 03:14:53,847
Because they want their country back.

3267
03:14:53,932 --> 03:14:56,225
Because it still belongs to us,

3268
03:14:56,434 --> 03:15:00,688
as long as the people have the guts
to fight for what they believe in.

3269
03:15:02,941 --> 03:15:06,860
The truth is the most important value
we have because if it doesn't endure,

3270
03:15:08,279 --> 03:15:09,697
if the government murders truth,

3271
03:15:09,781 --> 03:15:12,241
if we cannot respect these people

3272
03:15:12,325 --> 03:15:17,246
then this is not the country I was born in,
or the country I want to die in.

3273
03:15:19,249 --> 03:15:20,624
Tennyson wrote,

3274
03:15:20,709 --> 03:15:23,127
"Authority forgets a dying king. "

3275
03:15:24,671 --> 03:15:27,172
This was never more true
than for John F. Kennedy,

3276
03:15:27,257 --> 03:15:30,884
whose murder was probably one
of the most terrible moments

3277
03:15:31,177 --> 03:15:33,429
in the history of our country.

3278
03:15:35,932 --> 03:15:39,893
We, the people, the jury system sitting
in judgment on Clay Shaw

3279
03:15:41,730 --> 03:15:43,397
represent the hope

3280
03:15:43,481 --> 03:15:46,066
of humanity against government power.

3281
03:15:47,318 --> 03:15:49,319
In discharging your duty

3282
03:15:49,863 --> 03:15:53,073
to bring a first conviction
in this house of cards

3283
03:15:53,491 --> 03:15:55,117
against Clay Shaw,

3284
03:15:55,827 --> 03:16:00,664
"Ask not what your country can do for
you but what you can do for your country. "

3285
03:16:01,124 --> 03:16:02,583
Do not forget

3286
03:16:03,168 --> 03:16:04,752
your dying king.

3287
03:16:06,588 --> 03:16:08,130
Show this world

3288
03:16:08,548 --> 03:16:13,385
this is still a government "of the people,
for the people and by the people. "

3289
03:16:16,097 --> 03:16:17,806
Nothing as long as you live

3290
03:16:18,141 --> 03:16:20,267
will ever be more important.

3291
03:16:23,313 --> 03:16:24,855
It's up to you.

3292
03:16:28,735 --> 03:16:31,445
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

3293
03:16:39,704 --> 03:16:41,205
[Gavel bangs]

3294
03:16:47,879 --> 03:16:50,422
JUDGE: Has the jury reached a verdict?

3295
03:16:50,507 --> 03:16:51,882
JURY FOREMAN: We have, Your Honor.

3296
03:16:51,966 --> 03:16:54,802
JUDGE: Please hand the verdict
to the clerk.

3297
03:16:54,886 --> 03:16:57,221
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

3298
03:17:03,895 --> 03:17:06,563
JUDGE: Will the defendant please rise?

3299
03:17:10,610 --> 03:17:13,320
JUDGE: The clerk will now read
the verdict.

3300
03:17:13,404 --> 03:17:15,697
CLERK: "New Orleans, Louisiana.
March 1, 1969.

3301
03:17:18,076 --> 03:17:22,788
"We, the jury, find the defendant,
Clay Shaw, not guilty. "

3302
03:17:22,872 --> 03:17:24,665
[Cheers and applause]

3303
03:17:25,041 --> 03:17:26,500
[Gavel bangs]

3304
03:17:44,769 --> 03:17:46,311
JURY FOREMAN: We believe there was
a conspiracy.

3305
03:17:46,396 --> 03:17:49,481
Whether Shaw was a part of it
is another kettle of fish.

3306
03:17:49,566 --> 03:17:50,983
MAN: There's Jim!

3307
03:17:53,570 --> 03:17:56,613
ENGLISH REPORTER: Do you agree
that this is a full vindication

3308
03:17:56,698 --> 03:17:58,699
of the Warren Commission?

3309
03:18:00,201 --> 03:18:03,203
It only proves you cannot run
an investigation

3310
03:18:03,621 --> 03:18:08,208
questioning the intelligence operations
of the US government.

3311
03:18:08,293 --> 03:18:12,170
NEWSMAN: People claim you're unfit
to hold office,

3312
03:18:12,255 --> 03:18:14,172
that you've ruined
Clay Shaw's reputation.

3313
03:18:14,257 --> 03:18:15,841
Are you going to resign?

3314
03:18:15,925 --> 03:18:19,636
Hell, no! I'm going to run again,
and I'm going to win!

3315
03:18:20,179 --> 03:18:22,097
NEWSWOMAN:
Who will you persecute next?

3316
03:18:22,181 --> 03:18:25,058
JIM: If it takes me 30 years to nail
every one of the assassins

3317
03:18:25,143 --> 03:18:27,603
then I will continue for 30 years!

3318
03:18:28,688 --> 03:18:31,523
I owe that to Jack Kennedy
and the country.

3319
03:18:31,774 --> 03:18:34,234
REPORTER: There's Clay!
There's Clay Shaw!

3320
03:18:34,652 --> 03:18:36,194
REPORTER: How does it feel
to be acquitted?

3321
03:18:36,279 --> 03:18:38,113
CLAY: It's been exhausting.

3322
03:18:38,197 --> 03:18:39,489
REPORTER 2: What'll you do now?

3323
03:18:39,574 --> 03:18:41,241
I'm going home and cook some touffe.

3324
03:18:41,326 --> 03:18:42,826
NEWSWOMAN: Were you confident
about the outcome?

3325
03:18:46,039 --> 03:18:48,081
NEWSWOMAN 2:
Do you think Garrison will be back?

3326
03:18:48,166 --> 03:18:50,042
CLAY: I'm sure he will.

3327
03:18:50,209 --> 03:18:52,628
[Military drumbeat]

